title: never-fail white sauce
directions: For thin sauce (per cup of liquid) use 1 tablespoon flour and 1 tablespoon butter.

title: shrimp-and-crab bake
directions: Do not freeze this casserole.
Prepare a day ahead and refrigerate.
Whisk together 1 can of soup and the milk in large saucepan until well blended.
Bring to a boil over medium heat. Remove from heat; stir in shrimp and rice.
Cover; let stand for 5 minutes.
Put shrimp-soup mixture in a large bowl.
Stir in crab meat, sweet pepper, peas, other can of soup, seasonings and half-and-half.
Transfer mixture to a lightly oiled 13 x 9 x 2 baking dish.
(If serving next day, cover and refrigerate overnight.)
When ready to cook, heat oven to 375°.
Bake, covered, for 55 minutes.
Uncover, scatter crackers over top.
Bake another 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Let stand for 10 minutes before serving.

title: pound cake
directions: With electric mixer, beat butter and margarine until fluffy. Add powdered sugar; beat until well mixed.
Add 3 eggs (beaten), 1/2 of flour and baking powder mixture; mix well.
Add remaining eggs and flour mixture.
Beat well and add extracts.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Line the pie shell with strawberries.
Reserve about 1 cup of the berries for glaze. Simmer 1 cup berries and water for 3-4 minutes.
Combine cornstarch and sugar.
Add this to the berries along with lemon juice
Cook the mixture until thickened and clear.
Pour over the berries in pie shell and chill.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: they're a cinch! peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large bowl, beat milk and peanut butter until smooth.
Add Bisquick and vanilla; mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in granulated sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: taco tortilla casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Drain.
Add seasoning and tomato sauce and tomatoes.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cover bottom and sides with tortillas.
Alternate meat mixture, cheese and tortillas until gone.
Top last layer with sour cream.
Cover with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: meatballs
directions: Pour all ingredients into crock-pot.
Cook on high for 3 hours.
Ready to serve.

title: cream of coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake and bake as directed.
When cake is done, take big fork and put holes all over cake.
Then put Eagle Brand condensed milk on cake, followed by cream of coconut.
Let it cool. Then put Cool Whip on and sprinkle with coconut. Keep in refrigerator.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, bell pepper and onion together.
Drain and add soups, can of milk and enchilada sauce until creamy.
In a large pan, tear tortillas in quarters, making a layer in bottom of pan.
Add half of meat sauce on top, then Velveeta cheese.
Make 2 layers of tortillas, meat sauce and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: green rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into buttered baking dish and bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: cappuccino mix
directions: Combine all ingredients, mix well.
Store in an airtight container.
(Put in smaller container for gifts).

title: ranger cookies
directions: Set oven to 375°.
Stir together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
In bowl, beat butter for 30 seconds.
Add sugars; beat until fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla; beat well.
Add dry ingredients to beaten mixture; beat until well mixed.
Stir in cereal, coconut and fruit.
Drop by teaspoon, 2 inches apart, onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool 1 minute before removing to wire rack.
Makes 48.

title: wilted lettuce
directions: Fry ham in butter.
Remove ham; keep warm.
Brown remaining juice and pour mixture of eggs, sour milk and salt and pepper into hot skillet.
Cook until thickened.
Stir often to keep from burning.
Pour over lettuce and onion.
Serve hot.

title: shrimp creole(yields 8 servings)
directions: In microwave, cook bacon for 4 to 5 minutes at Full power to render the fat.
Pour fat into large saucepan over medium heat. Add onion, celery and pepper.
Saute for 10 minutes or until tender.
Add tomato paste, tomatoes and sugar.
Cook over low heat, covered, for an hour, stirring occasionally.
Stir in shrimp and Worcestershire sauce.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cover and cook for 15 more minutes.
Serve with steamed rice.

title: chocolate turtles
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients. Fold in flour.
Bake 2 to 3 minutes on high in waffle iron.

title: "chicken lickin" good pork chops
directions: Dredge pork
chops
in	mixture
of
flour,
salt,
dry mustard and garlic powder.	Brown
in
oil in large skillet or heavy pot.	Add can of
soup. Cover and cook on low heat for 2 hours or until tender, turning a couple of times.

title: crumbs for on pies
directions: Mix altogether with fingers, until crumbs are fine.
Sprinkle over top of apple or cherry pie and bake as usual.

title: no cook divinity fudge
directions: Combine frosting mix, corn syrup, vanilla and boiling water in small mixing bowl.
Beat on high speed until stiff peaks form. Transfer to large mixing bowl; on low speed or by hand, gradually blend in confectioners sugar.
Stir in nuts.
Drop mixture by teaspoonful on wax paper.
When outside of candy feels firm, turn over and allow to dry 12 hours.
Store candy in airtight container.
Makes 5 to 6 dozen.

title: fudge oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine sugar, milk, butter and cocoa.
Bring to a full boil for one (1) minute.
Time accurately.
Remove from heat.
Add salt, vanilla, peanut butter and oats.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.
Becomes firm in fifteen (15) minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: mam-mas' texas beef casserole
directions: In skillet, cook ground beef.
Drain most of grease.
Add sauce, tomatoes, sugar and salt.
Stir well and let simmer.
In large pan, mix boiled noodles, sour cream, cream cheese and green onions.
Stir well until cheese is melted.
Add noodle mixture to skillet mixture and let simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Serves one.

title: potato hot dish
directions: Mix all ingredients; place in a greased 2-quart casserole. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: crumb chicken
directions: Mix
crumbs,
parsley,
cheese,
garlic
salt, salt and pepper.
Dip
each
piece
of
chicken in melted margarine and then crumbs.
Arrange in open shallow pan.
Pour any remaining margarine over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Do not turn chicken while baking.
This can be made in advance and frozen. To cook, thaw completely and cook as directed.

title: harvey wallbanger cake
directions: Combine cake mix and pudding in a large mixing bowl. Blend in eggs, Galliano, vodka, oil and orange juice.
Mix batter until smooth and thick.
Pour into well-greased and floured 10-inch Bundt pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 45 minutes.
Let cool in pan for 10 minutes, then remove and place on plate.
Have glaze ready to spoon on while cake is still warm.

title: baked broccoli
directions: Mix Ritz crackers and melted margarine, using 2/3 of the crumbs.
Layer on the bottom of the baking dish.
Add a layer of broccoli. Add a layer of diced cheese on top of the broccoli.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: two corn casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 2-quart casserole.
In small pan, melt margarine, add green pepper and onion.
Cook until tender.

title: vegetable medley
directions: Combine vegetables, soup, 1/2 cheese,
sour
cream
and 1/2 onions; pour in casserole dish.
Cover and cook 30 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle remaining onions and cheese over casserole; heat 5 minutes.

title: french fried onions
directions: Heat oil (1-inch) in deep fryer or Dutch oven to 375°.
Beat remaining ingredients except onion rings with hand beater until smooth.
Dip each onion ring into batter, allowing excess to drip into bowl.
Fry a few onion rings at a time in hot oil, turning once, until golden brown, about 2 minutes; drain.
Keep warm in 300° oven while frying remaining onions.

title: soy sauce marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place pork steak or other pork in marinade.
Put in fridge overnight.
Turn occasionally.
Cook as desired.
Good on grill also.

title: dilled potato salad with peas
directions: Wash new potatoes, cut into 1/4-inch slices and cook in large saucepan with boiling water to cover.
Boil gently 10 minutes or until potatoes are just tender.
Do not overcook.
Drain and cool.

title: walnuted chicken
directions: *Boil with chicken broth instead of water.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Add oats to boiling water.
Let set while you mix the remaining ingredients.
Cream together butter, brown sugar, white sugar and eggs; add this mixture to the oatmeal mixture.
Add flour, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Bake in 350° oven for about 25 to 30 minutes.
Icing for cake is a powdered sugar icing.

title: family style lasagna
directions: Brown beef in oil.
Add spaghetti mix, tomato paste and water; simmer
for
minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cook lasagna noodles
according
to
package
directions.
Drain noodles and cover
with
cold
water.
Line bottom of lightly oiled baking dish,
11 1/2 x 7 1/2-inch with a single layer of lasagna noodles. Cover
with
of the meat sauce, 1/3 cup cottage
cheese
and 1 tablespoon Parmesan cheese.
Repeat to make 4
layers
ending with
a layer of sauce.
Top with thin slivers of
Mozzarella cheese.
Bake
in
a
350° oven for 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: the best pork ribs
directions: Mix together barbecue sauce and orange juice. Lay ribs in a baking pan and pour barbecue sauce mixture over the top. The ribs should be nearly submerged in the barbecue mix. Cover pan with foil and set oven to 250°.

title: brown rice
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add chopped onion and rice. Brown 10 to 15 minutes over medium heat. Put rice mixture in casserole dish and add mushrooms and beef consomme. Stir well. Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: old-fashioned cream of tomato soup
directions: In a saucepan, combine first 6 ingredients.
Cover and simmer 1 hour.
Heat cream in top of double boiler (slowly).
Add to tomato mixture just before serving.
Makes 1 1/2 quarts.
Serves 8.

title: egg nog cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together with hand beater until blended. Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 50 minutes in a greased and floured Bundt pan.

title: meringue
directions: Beat egg whites with cream of tartar until stiff.
Gradually beat in sugar, a little at a time.
Continue beating until stiff and glossy.
Do not underbeat.
Beat until sugar is dissolved.
Add flavoring.
Pile meringue onto hot pie filling, being careful to seal edges.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes until delicately browned.

title: lumpia
directions: Saute onion; add pork and beef.
Cook until brown.
Add all the vegetables until tender.
Add seasonings.
Simmer approximately 10 minutes.
Drain.
Wrap in wong tong wrappers. Seal with water.
Deep fry.
Serve with Sweet/Sour Sauce.
Serves approximately 35.

title: oatmeal drop cookies
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and baking soda together.
Stir in oats and raisins.
Add in order, corn oil, eggs and milk; beat until blended.
Drop by teaspoonfuls, 1 1/2 inches apart, onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 400° (hot) oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: broccoli beef stir-fry
directions: In a large skillet, melt butter.
Add meat; saute until brown. Remove meat; drain skillet.
In same skillet, cook Rice-A-Roni by package directions.
Stir in 2 cups of water, onion, garlic, ginger and contents of seasoning package.
Bring to a boil over high heat; cover.
Reduce to a low heat.
Simmer for 8 minutes. Add meat, broccoli and bell pepper; cover.
Simmer for 7 minutes.

title: dirt pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, butter, sugar and Cool Whip together.
You may want to line the inside of pot with foil for easier clean-up. Save some Oreos for top.
Layer pot with cookie crumbs, filling and cherries.
Keep layering until you get to the top.
For decorations, use silk flowers and gummy bear worms or use a pail and shovel.

title: calico beans
directions: Drain the kidney beans and butter beans and place in a casserole. Add the pork and beans.
Brown the bacon, hamburger and onion.
Drain and add to the beans.
Add the remaining ingredients and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: popovers
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease six 6-ounce glass custard cups with butter.
By hand, mix eggs, milk and butter with whisk.
Sift flour and salt to mixture; mix until smooth.
In blender, blend until smooth the mixture.
Pour into custard cups, filling about half full.
Bake on a flat pan for 45 to 50 minutes. Serve hot.

title: hot choco-mallo mix
directions: Stir together dry milk, nondairy creamer, sugar and cocoa in large bowl.
Stir in marshmallows.
Spoon mix into glass jar with a tight fitting lid.
Split up into smaller jars if need be.
Attach label:
For each serving, combine 1/4 cup mix and 6 ounces boiling water in mug.
Stir and serve.
Makes 6 cups.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Put 1/2 peppers and 1/2 vinegar in blender - repeat.

title: cherries in the snow
directions: Mix milk with Dream Whip in a bowl.
Add sour cream and sugar. Mix.
Spoon over angel food cake; slice in layers.
Spoon cherry pie filling on top.

title: tuna fish casserole
directions: Empty cans of tuna in a 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Add 2 cans of mushroom soup in a mixing bowl with 1 can of water.
Stir until smooth.
Pour over tuna.
Crush potato chips and place on top of tuna.
Bake at 350° for 20 or 25 minutes.

title: chocolate trifle
directions: Bake cake according to package directions in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool; cut into small squares.
Prepare pudding according to package directions, using milk and Amaretto.
Allow pudding to thicken.
In a glass trifle dish, layer 1/2 of cake squares, 1/2 of pudding, 1/2 of Heath bars and 1/2 of whipped topping.
Repeat layers; sprinkle top with crushed Heath bits.
Cover; refrigerate for several hours or overnight.

title: holly clusters
directions: Melt marshmallows, margarine and coloring in double boiler. Stir until smooth and soft.
Pour over corn flakes and stir.
Mix well.
Drop on wax paper by teaspoons.
Add red hots (as berries on the wreaths!)
Let set until dry.

title: chocolate chip peanut cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine cake mix with eggs and water and beat until mixed.
Add peanut butter and blend; fold in chocolate chips.
Drop in teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet, about 3 inches apart.
Bake about 9 to 12 minutes.
Remove from pan while still warm.
Makes 6 dozen cookies.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together potatoes, 1/2 cup sugar, salt, vanilla, egg, melted butter and milk.
Place in a casserole dish.
Mix brown sugar, nuts, flour, coconut and 1/4 cup melted margarine.
Place on top of potato mixture.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix 1 egg, butter and dry cake mix until crumbly.
Reserve 1 cup of mix.
Pat remaining mix into a 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan. Bake 15 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: white fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk, water and salt; heat to a boil over moderate heat.
Brush sides of pan with wet pastry brush to remove sugar crystals, stirring frequently to soft ball stage (236°).
Add butter and vanilla.
Cool at room temperature, without stirring, until lukewarm.
Beat until mixture holds its shape.
Add marshmallow cream.
Beat until thick.
Spread in greased pan.

title: spaghetti with mushroom sauce
directions: Peel and mince garlic.
Heat oil in large skillet.
Add garlic and ham (medium heat).
Clean and slice mushrooms.
Add them to skillet.
Stir frequently until mushrooms lose volume and darken. Add parsley and salt and pepper to taste.
Bring large pot of water to boil.
Add 1 teaspoon salt and some butter.
Cook spaghetti until tender; drain.
Toss with mushroom sauce.
Serve topped with cheese.
Serves 3 or 4.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Sift flour with baking powder.
Add salt and work in cheese. Work in butter with fingertips and add milk.
Drop by spoonfuls onto baking sheet and bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: friendship tea
directions: Mix all the ingredients.
Store in a tightly covered container. Serve 2 to 3 teaspoons to 1 cup hot water.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil the first 6 ingredients together until it forms a soft ball.
Then add peanut butter and Marshmallow Fluff.
Spread in shallow glass pan.
Refrigerate to set.
Cut in squares.

title: lemon and lime salad mold
directions: In large bowl dissolve lemon and lime Jell-O in hot water. Set aside to chill but not set.
Add crushed pineapples (drained), evaporated milk, nuts, cottage cheese and mayonnaise.
Pour into large mold and let set several hours or overnight.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Mix together flour and sugar.
Put in saucepan and bring to a boil, butter, water and cocoa.
Pour over flour and sugar and mix well, then add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into greased cookie sheet.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: frosting for white cake
directions: Place all ingredients, except vanilla, into double boiler.
Mix thoroughly.
Cook, beating constantly, with electric beater until mixture forms peaks, about 7 minutes.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and beat until of spreading consistency.

title: stir-fried chicken and snow peas
directions: Place strips of chicken breasts in bowl; add sherry and sesame oil.
Heat peanut oil in wok and fry the garlic, ginger root and almonds for 2 minutes or until lightly browned.
Throw away the garlic and ginger and keep the almonds.
Add the chicken strips and stir-fry for 2 minutes until white and firm.
Add the snow peas and stir-fry for 1 minute.
Add chicken broth and continue stirring for 1 minute.
Stir in the cornstarch paste.
Serve as soon as the chicken broth has thickened, then garnish with the almonds.
Serves 4.

title: cheese cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, mix eggs, cream cheese, sugar and lemon juice.
Beat for 30 minutes and pour over graham cracker crust in cheese cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: fajita marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients in plastic bag with Ziploc seal.
Add flank steak (or skirt steak, or London broil); refrigerate 6 to 8 hours or overnight, turning occasionally.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° until begins to bubble.

title: sandy's fudge
directions: Butter 9 x 9-inch pan.
Combine sugar, cocoa and salt.
Stir in milk.
Cook over medium heat; stir constantly, until mixture comes to full rolling boil.
Without stirring, cook until you get a soft ball when testing in a bit of water.
Remove from heat, add butter and vanilla plus peanut butter, if desired.
Stir until it loses its gloss.
Put into pan quickly.

title: cold chicken pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions; drain.
Rinse with cold water and drain well.
Add chicken, zucchini, tomatoes and celery.
Place remaining ingredients in blender or food processor and blend until well mixed.
Chill dressing, covered, for 1 hour before adding to salad.
Toss salad, coating well.
Makes about 10 cups or 5 servings.

title: low-fat rigatoni caesar salad(yields 4 servings)
directions: Combine the tomatoes, anchovies, lemon juice, olive oil, garlic, salt and pepper in a large serving bowl.
Let stand for 20 minutes.
Meanwhile, cook the pasta according to package directions; drain.
Toss the dressing with hot pasta and Parmesan cheese.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
Stir in the romaine lettuce and serve immediately.
Garnish with shredded Parmesan cheese. Enjoy!

title: chicken pot pie
directions: In a large casserole dish, spread soup.
Add all vegetables and chicken.
Stir to mix; add a few pats of butter.
Pour reserved chicken broth (1 cup) on top.
Add pastry to top of casserole, closing in all of the top, and cut 2 to 3 slits.
Cook at 425° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: velveeta consomme noodles
directions: Cut your Velveeta cheese into chunks and slowly add to your consomme soup that you have heating over low heat.
Melt the cheese slowly, stirring constantly until all the cheese is melted and is a creamy sauce.
Cook spaghetti and drain well.
Add your sauce mix together thoroughly.
Ready to serve.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt margarine, peanut butter and chocolate chips in a medium pot.
Pour mixture over cereal; stir to coat well.
Put powdered sugar into grocery bag.
Add cereal and shake, shake, shake. Store in airtight container in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: orange colada
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in blender.
Process for 30 seconds.
Add ice and continue until liquified.
Serve with orange slice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: clam dip
directions: Combine the cream cheese and clam broth in mixing bowl, blending until smooth.
Add the clams, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Mix well.
Serve with potato chips or tortilla chips.

title: prune cream pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Mix together and blend in thoroughly the flour, sugar, salt and cinnamon.
Stir in milk, juice, vanilla and prunes.
Pour into pie pan distributing prunes evenly.
Bake until silver knife thrust into side of filling comes out clean.
Spread with sweetened whipped cream if desired.
Baking temperature: 375°.
Baking time:
50 to 60 minutes.

title: fish mold
directions: Melt cream cheese in soup.
Soften gelatine in water and dissolve in soup mixture.
Add mayonnaise, onion and celery.
Add shrimp or crab meat.
(I use broken shrimp and rinse very well with water.)
Pour in mold (fish mold is nice) and refrigerate. Serve with Ritz crackers.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Shred beef and Cheddar cheese.
Allow cream cheese to soften to room temperature.
In a large bowl, mix first 5 ingredients well and shape into 2 balls.
Roll in pecans.

title: chocolate amaretto cheesecake
directions: Sprinkle chocolate wafer crumbs in bottom of a 7-inch spring-form pan; set aside.
Position knife blade in food processor bowl.
Add cream cheese and next 7 ingredients, processing until smooth.
Add egg; process just until blended. Slowly pour mixture over crumbs in pan.
Bake at 300° for 65 to 70 minutes, or until cheesecake is set.
Let cool in pan on wire rack.
Cover; chill at least 8 hours.
Remove sides of pan; transfer cheesecake to a serving platter.
Garnish with chocolate curls, if desired.

title: hot cider punch
directions: Heat slowly, stirring, until sugar melts.
Spicy flavor improves as it stands.

title: fudge cakes
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add well beaten eggs.
Mix flour and cocoa and add dry ingredients to mixture.
Add nuts and vanilla and beat.
Bake in greased tin about 20 minutes at 300°.
Cut in squares while hot.

title: veal parmesan
directions: Dip pulverized veal cutlets in eggs and roll in bread crumbs. Pan-fry in oil and drain.

Put in casserole. Heat tomato sauce. Add garlic salt and onions. Pour sauce mixture on top of cutlets. Top cutlets with Swiss cheese and Parmesan cheese, if desired. Place in 450° oven until cheese melts.

title: green tomato pasta sauce
directions: Remove stem ends and core green tomatoes, then cut up.
In 10-quart Dutch oven, combine the tomatoes, brown sugar, salt and pepper. Bring tomato mixture to boiling, stirring occasionally. Boil gently, uncovered for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Puree cooked tomatoes through food mill.
Return to Dutch oven.
Add large onions, green pepper, crushed garlic, dill weed and bay leaves.
Bring mixture to boiling.
Boil gently, uncovered, about 1 hour more or until of desired consistency.
Discard bay leaves.

title: pepper relish
directions: Chop or grind vegetables.
Combine with all ingredients and boil 3 to 5 minutes.
Makes about 6 pints.

title: cracker jacks
directions: In large kettle, melt butter, sugar and syrup.
Boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat; add 1/2 teaspoon soda and package of peanuts.
Place corn in large baking pan, pour and stir syrup over corn until coated on all pieces.
Bake at 225° for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Cool and put in Ziploc bags.

title: lasting impression shrimp dip
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Add shrimp. Chill at least 6 hours. Yields 2 cups.

title: stir n-roll pastry
directions: Mix flour and salt.
Pour milk and oil and mix to make soft ball.
Halve mixture and roll dough between wax paper.
Put in pie pan.
Makes enough for 2 pies.

title: hot antipasto appetizer
directions: Sprinkle 8 x 8-inch baking dish with bread crumbs.
Layer 1/2 of roasted peppers, artichoke hearts, mushrooms and olives. Sprinkle with bread crumbs and garlic powder.
Repeat layer. Drizzle oil before baking over the antipasto. Sprinkle with paprika for color.
Heat in 350° oven until heated through.
Serve with garlic bread.

title: bing cherry pie
directions: Cut up Bing cherries.
Fold whipping cream into rest of mixture.
Use graham cracker crust.
Makes 1 large pie or 2 small ones.

title: chili topping
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan, over medium-low heat, stirring occasionally.
Heat 5 to 6 minutes or until mixture is warm throughout.

title: black chocolate cake
directions: Combine all ingredients, except the hot coffee.
Carefully add the cup of coffee (stir in by hand).
Pour ingredients into Bundt cake pan.
Grease and flour pan well.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool for ten minutes, then remove from pan.

title: cantaloupe bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add oil, sugar and vanilla.
Cut melon into small pieces and puree.
Add to egg mixture.
Sift in dry ingredients; add to liquid.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
(I used 3 smaller pans.) Bake at 325° for 1 hour, or test for doneness.
May be frosted.

title: beef and cream cheese dip
directions: Blend softened cream cheese and sour cream together.
Add chopped beef, bell pepper, black pepper, onion flakes and garlic salt.
Put in an oven-safe bowl.
Sprinkle with chopped pecans. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve with crackers.
(I double this for a party.)

title: ham and cheese casserole
directions: Saute onions and celery in butter until soft.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Line two 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking pans with foil.
Grease foil generously.
Divide ham mixture evenly between the two pans.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes or until brown and firm in the center.

title: mexican dip
directions: Brown hamburger with onion; drain.
Add cheese; cook until melted.
Serve or keep warm in crock-pot.

title: mama's buttermilk pancakes
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Beat egg yolks until light.
Add yolks and dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into mixture.
Pour small amounts on griddle or frying pan.
Fry until brown.
Serve with butter and your favorite syrup.

title: tuna spread
directions: Blend all ingredients with a fork.
Put in covered bowl and refrigerate.
Turn upside down on plate for serving.
Garnish with green and black olives.
Serve with crackers.

title: la gougere(burgundy cheese bread)
directions: In saucepan, combine first 4 ingredients.
Bring to boil. Remove and add flour all at once, stirring briskly.
Stir vigorously over low heat until mixture forms a ball.
Remove from heat and beat in eggs, one at a time.
Beat well; mix in grated cheese.
Let cool slightly.

title: cooked pineapple salad(heritage recipe)
directions: Boil the jello, sugar, and the undrained
pineapple for 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add
cold water, chill until partly set.

title: haystacks
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; add chili.
Place a handful of corn chips on each serving plate, followed by chili mixture, lettuce, tomatoes, cheese and olives.
Garnish with sour cream and salsa.
Fun for a party.

title: no crust coconut pie
directions: Sift flour and sugar together.
Add eggs and beat.
Add melted butter, milk, coconut and vanilla.
Grease 10-inch pie plate lightly and coat with corn meal.
Pour mixture into pie plate and bake at 325° for 60 minutes.

title: egg-cheese-ham bake
directions: Cut bread in small squares.
Put half in buttered long cake pan.
Pour half of the melted butter over the bread.
Make 2 layers:
bread, butter, 1/2 cheese, 1 can mushrooms, onions and 1/2 ham.
Mix together milk, salt, paprika and eggs.
Pour over layers.
Make the night before serving and let stand in refrigerator.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until done.

title: wacky cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients into an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Make 3 holes. Put vinegar in one hole, oil in the next and vanilla in the last hole.
Pour water over all; stir with a fork until moistened. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
My favorite!

title: banana split cake
directions: Put pudding and milk in bowl and stir for 2 minutes.
Put pudding in crust.
Slice bananas and put on top of pudding.
Add pineapple.
Put whipped cream on pineapple.
Sprinkle pecans on top.
Keep refrigerated.

title: spinach and garlic soup
directions: In heavy saucepan, heat olive oil over medium heat. Add garlic, onion, carrots, celery and basil. Stir 4 to 5 minutes, taking care not to let garlic brown. Add chicken stock, spinach and potatoes; boil gently until the potatoes are done. Serve topped with Parmesan cheese. Serves 8 to 10.

title: creamy spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions.
Drain and squeeze dry.
Combine spinach, cream cheese, 2 tablespoons butter, salt and pepper; mix well.
Spoon into a greased 1-quart baking dish.
Combine bread crumbs and sage; sprinkle over spinach mixture.
Drizzle remaining 2 tablespoons butter over bread crumbs.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes.
Garnish with egg slices, if desired.
Yields 3 servings.

title: polish mistakes
directions: Brown and drain meat well.
Combine all ingredients.
Stir until cheese melts.
Spread on party rye.
Place on a cookie sheet, freeze, then put in baggies to keep.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: oven barbecued chicken
directions: Combine salt, pepper, brown sugar, barbecue sauce, cooking oil and catsup.
Dip chicken into barbecue sauce.
Line cookie sheet and cover with foil.
Seal edges and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Makes 4 servings.

title: baked potato salad
directions: Note:
May substitute other cheeses to your taste.

title: chocolate buttersweets
directions: Cream butter. Add sugar, salt and vanilla; cream well. Gradually add flour. Shape by teaspoonfuls into balls. Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Press hole in center of each. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes until delicately browned. Fill while warm. Cool. Frost. Makes about 36 cookies.

title: pineapple chess pie
directions: Beat all ingredients together well. Add to pie shell and bake at 325° for about 45 minutes.

title: tomato quiche
directions: Line
a
10-inch
quiche dish with pastry.
Trim excess pastry around edges.
Bake at 400° for 5 minutes;
remove from oven and prick with fork. Bake an additional 5 minutes.

title: baked carrot casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and place in a greased baking dish. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Makes 6 servings.

title: kiss cookies
directions: In large mixing bowl cream butter, sugar, and vanilla. Gradually beat in flour.
Add nuts and beat on low speed until well blended.
Chill dough.
Unwrap Kisses.
After dough has chilled, shape a scant tablespoon around each Kiss, covering completely.
Roll between your palms to form a ball.
Place a few inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated 375° oven until set, 10-12 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: boiled cocoa cake
directions: Boil shortening,
butter,
cocoa
and
water; pour over flour, sugar and soda.
Add
eggs, one at a time.	Add buttermilk and vanilla.
Pour
into 11 x 15-inch greased and floured pan.	Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: curried cheese spread
directions: Mix well and refrigerate a few hours before serving.
Serve with crackers.

title: potato and pea soup
directions: Pare potatoes; cut in small chunks.
Fill a 2-quart pan about 3/4 full.
Add water to top of potatoes.
Add salt and pepper. Dice celery and onion fine; add to potatoes.
Cook about 10 minutes, but do not boil.
Put in peas and 1/2 stick of butter. Cook slowly (about 45 minutes) on low heat.

title: oriental rice
directions: Cook bacon and drain most of the fat. Mix vegetables together and fry in small amount of bacon fat. Then mix all together with rice and scrambled eggs and season with soy sauce and Accent. Add crumbled bacon and mix well.

title: homemade sausage
directions: Mix seasonings and sprinkle over meat.
Grind through a meat grinder.
Mix well and press into a bowl or jar.

title: salad pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls out on large cooking sheet and bake as directed.
Cool.

title: punch
directions: Juices must be chilled.
Dissolve Jell-O and sugar in boiling water.
Cool.
Add chilled pineapple juice and ginger ale just before serving.

title: super easy hot dish
directions: Mix croutons, hamburger and celery and place in large casserole.
Melt butter with hot milk or water and pour over mixture.
Blend the 2 cans of soup and pour over the top.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Let stand for 10 minutes before serving.

title: sourdough coffee cake
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into pie plate.

title: raspberry cobbler
directions: Drain berries; reserve syrup.
Combine 1/3 cup sugar, cornstarch and spice; stir in syrup mixture.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens.
Stir in berries; cook.
Next, combine flour, 1/2 cup sugar, baking powder and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Mix in egg, sour cream and butter.
Add to flour mix and drop by spoonfuls into bubbling mixture.

title: fish fillets with mushrooms(microwave)
directions: Arrange fish fillets in 12 x 7 x 2-inch microproof baking dish.
Dot with butter.
Stir lemon juice into wine and sprinkle with remaining ingredients over top.
Cover with wax paper.
Cook on High 5 minutes.
Let stand covered 5 minutes.
(Makes 3 to 4 servings.)

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, butter and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Spread into baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread on top of pretzels.
Mix gelatin and water.
Add strawberries.
Pour mixture onto other mixture.
Refrigerate 2 hours.
Cut into squares.

title: sandies(cookie)
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add water, vanilla and almond extract.
Mix well. Blend in flour and nuts.
Chill 4 hours. Shape into balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool slightly. Roll in powdered sugar.

title: biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 450°. Cut shortening into flour, baking powder and salt with pastry blender or two knives until mixture resembles fine crumbs. Stir in just enough milk so dough leaves side of bowl and rounds up into balls.

title: fudgsicles
directions: Bring pudding, sugar and milk to a boil.
Chill.
Whip the evaporated milk about 5 minutes and fold into pudding mixture. Pour into popsicle molds and freeze.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt 1/2 cup margarine. Add to graham cracker crumbs.
Mix well and pat into a 13 x 9 1/2 x 2-inch pan.

title: one-half pound cake
directions: Cream together sugar, butter and shortening.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add salt and flour, mixing well.
Bake 1 hour at 315° or until tests done.

title: chocolate nut cakes
directions: Mix eggs, do not beat.
Add sugar, chocolate chips and nuts. Place in cupcake liners in muffin tins.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: hamburg barbecue
directions: Mix all ingredients well with hamburg; simmer for 20 minutes. Stir frequently.

title: lime salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water with marshmallows, may have to stir over hot water until all have dissolved.
Chill until partly set. Add other 4 ingredients; stir well.
Chill 3 or 4 hours.
Serves 6.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Spread a chicken cutlet out flat between 2 pieces of waxed paper.
Using a mallet or rolling pin, pound cutlet until it's 1/2 inch thick.
Do the same with remaining cutlets.

title: chicken breasts
directions: Place chicken in a 9
x 12-inch glass baking dish.
Put one slice of cheese on each breast.
Pour soup evenly over the chicken.
Melt margarine
and mix with stuffing mix.
Sprinkle evenly over the soup.
Bake,
uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour or until chicken is tender.

title: chocolate pies
directions: Mix
cocoa, sugar, flour and eggs well and add milk and vanilla.
Cook
over medium heat until thick.
Let cool.
Pour into two 8-inch baked pie crusts.

title: tuna burgers
directions: Drain and flake tuna, add all ingredients and mix with a fork. Put on rolls.
Wrap filled rolls in foil.
Heat at 400° for 8 minutes.

title: squash casserole(even kids love this!)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Parboil squash and drain liquid.
Mix all ingredients except squash and stuffing mix.
Put a layer of stuffing mix in large baking dish, layer of squash, layer of mixed ingredients and sprinkle layer of cheese.
Repeat layers and end with stuffing mix and cheese.
Bake for 25 minutes at 375°.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix corn syrup, sugar and water in mixing bowl.
Cover with paper towel and microwave 4 minutes.
Add peanuts.
Cover and cook 4 to 5 minutes until syrup and peanuts are lightly browned to a caramel brown.
Stir in remaining ingredients until light and foamy.
Spread to 1/4-inch thickness on large, well-buttered cookie sheet.
Let harden.
Break in pieces to serve.

title: orange julius
directions: Combine orange juice, milk, egg, vanilla and ice cubes in blender.
Process until ice is crushed.
Serve immediately. Yield: 1 serving.

title: german chocolate pies
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in 3 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: classic cream pound cake(this cake has a rich flavor and velvety texture, )
directions: DO NOT preheat oven.
Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan.
In large bowl, cream butter and sugar with mixer until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Blend in vanilla.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage.
Drain and cool. Beat eggs and milk together. Add salt and mustard and beat again.
Add bread and stir until it softens.
Stir in cheese, mushrooms and sausage.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan and refrigerate overnight.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.
Let stand for a few minutes before cutting.
Serves 6.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Thaw broccoli and blend all other ingredients.
Pour into a lightly greased 2-quart or long Pyrex dish.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: whipping cream biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Spread small amount of flour on counter top to roll out biscuits. Cut with biscuit cutter. Bake until brown at 500°. Watch carefully.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Bake chicken, covered, 15 minutes in preheated 425° oven. Drain.
Combine tomatoes, cornstarch and oregano.
Cook until sauce is thickened.
Pour over chicken and top with cheese.
Bake for 5 minutes, uncovered.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt in saucepan.
Add milk and chocolate.
Bring mixture to a full boil, stirring constantly. Remove from heat.
Add butter or margarine and stir until it is melted and frosting is smooth.
While still warm, spread on cake. Decorate with coarsely chopped nuts.
Makes enough frosting to cover tops and sides of two 9-inch layers.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Add soups, sour cream and taco seasoning.
Mix together.
In a 9 x 13-inch greased pan layer 1/2 of the flour taco shells then 1/2 of the meat mixture.
Then the last of the taco shells and the last of the meat mixture. Sprinkle top with cheese and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Serve with your favorite taco toppings.

title: wild poke greens
directions: Wash
greens
and
remove
stems.
Place
greens
into boiling water
and	boil about 30 minutes and then drain water off as it
will be very strong.
Then add new water with a few pieces of	bacon and also add a little bacon drippings.
Bring to boil, cut
heat
to
simmer
and cook slowly until tender.

title: halloween cakes in a cup
directions: Mix cake according to package directions.
Fill ice cream cups with about 1/3 cup batter.
Place cups on baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Place on wire rack to cool.

title: stir-fry chicken
directions: Cut chicken pieces into small cubes and stir-fry in 1 tablespoon oil.
Add frozen vegetables and water.
Cover and cook 7 to 10 minutes over medium heat.
Stir in sauce mixture and cook until thick.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions.
Melt Velveeta and half of margarine.
Drain broccoli and put in 8-inch dish.
Pour Velveeta and margarine over broccoli.
Crush Ritz crackers and lay on top of Velveeta.
Melt rest of margarine and pour over crackers. Cook at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: potato bread
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In a medium saucepan, cook potato in the water about 12 minutes or until tender; do not drain.
Cool cubed potato mixture to 110° to 115°.
Set aside 1/2 cup of the cooking liquid.
Mash potato in the remaining liquid.
Add enough warm water to make 2 cups mashed potato mixture.

title: banana jumbos
directions: Bake at 375° for about 10 minutes.
Mix shortening, sugar and butter.
Add eggs, buttermilk, bananas and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients and stir into batter, then add nuts.
Chill.
Drop by spoonfuls on well-greased cookie sheets.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Butter a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Line with whole crackers.
Mix pudding and milk until blended.
Add Cool Whip.
Put 1/2 in 1 layer.
Add the crackers next, then the other 1/2 of the mixture. End with crackers.
Refrigerate.

title: savory grilled potatoes
directions: Mix Miracle Whip and seasonings in a large bowl until blended. Stir in potatoes and onions to coat.
Divide potato mixture evenly among six 12-inch square pieces of heavy duty foil.
Seal each to form a packet.
Place foil packets on grill over medium heat for 25 to 30 minutes, or until potatoes are tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: classic tiramisu
directions: In a small mixer bowl beat egg yolks and sugar until thick and lemon colored, about 1 minute.
Place in top of a double boiler over boiling water.
Reduce heat to low and cook 8 to 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add mascarpone cheese, beating well.
In a small mixer bowl whip cream until stiff peaks form.
Fold into egg yolk mixture; set aside.
Line bottom and side of 2 1/2 to 3-quart bowl or souffle dish with ladyfinger halves, split sides up.
Brush with coffee liqueur or Brandied Espresso.
Spoon half of egg yolk-cream mixture into ladyfinger-lined bowl.
Repeat ladyfingers, espresso and cream layer.
Garnish with Sweetened Whipped Cream, cocoa and chocolate curls.
Cover and refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Scrape carrots; cut in fourths lengthwise.
Place in heavy skillet.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook over low heat, turning often until tender and glazed.
Makes 6 servings.

title: fruit salad(from the files of louella scott williams)
directions: Drain and save juice from peaches, pears and pineapple.
Mix 2 1/2 cups of this juice with one large box of instant vanilla pudding.
Drain mandarin oranges.
Discard juice and combine all fruit and pudding mixture and add some maraschino cherries.

title: susan's hors d'oeuvres
directions: Slice baguette into 1/2 inch thick pieces.
Make a spreadable mixture of the other ingredients, adding more mayonnaise if necessary.
The curry powder is optional but adding it makes this very good.
Spread the mixture on the slices of bread and bake at 350° for a few minutes to melt the topping and heat the bread.

title: gulf coast jambalaya
directions: Use chicken, shrimp or oysters and/or a combination.
Do not precook shrimp or oysters, but sprinkle chicken with seasoned flour and lightly brown it on all sides using an iron Dutch oven. Drain chicken.
Lightly brown the rice in about 4 tablespoons oil, stir constantly with a spatula.
Add to rice, the celery, green onions and bell pepper.
Saute.
Add chicken broth, salt, garlic, pepper and chicken, seafood, etc. to rice mixture.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Fluff rice with a fork.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Fry hamburger with onion, garlic, salt and pepper; drain grease.
In 13 x 9-inch baking pan, mix in tomato soup, corn and beans.
Mash potatoes; mix in eggs, butter, milk, salt and pepper. Pile on top of meat mixture in piles, then top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: steak marinade
directions: Shake all together and pour over steaks.
Marinate for several hours.

title: muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add eggs, Crisco, buttermilk and bran. Mix well.
Store in refrigerator in covered containers.
Fill greased muffins 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: 4-ply pie
directions: Melt butter; add flour and nuts.
Pat into 9 x13-inch glass baking dish.
Bake at 350 degrees for 15 minutes.
Cool thoroughly. Mix cream cheese, sugar, and whipped cream; spread on cooled crust. Mix 2 packages pudding with milk and vanilla; spread on cream cheese layer.
Top with layer of whipped cream.
Chill.
Serves 8-10.

title: taffy crisp pecans
directions: Line an ungreased jelly roll pan with graham crackers broken in half.
Add pecans on top.
Meanwhile, melt butters and sugar. Dissolve sugar before the butters boil.
Boil for 3 minutes. Spoon over graham crackers.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes, checking often.
Cool and separate to wax paper.
Refrigerate or freeze.

title: chicken cheese ball(appetizer)
directions: Mix all ingredients together and make into a ball.
Can roll in chopped nuts (optional).
Chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: sweet-and-sour cabbage
directions: Combine vinegar, sugar and red pepper; set aside.
Heat bacon drippings in a large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add cabbage, onion, salt and nutmeg; cook 5 minutes.
Add vinegar mixture; simmer 1 to 2 minutes.
Yields 4 servings.

title: 60 minutes southern rolls
directions: Set aside 1 cup flour.
In bowl, mix remaining flour, sugar, salt, baking soda and yeast.
Heat buttermilk, water and margarine to 125 to 130°.
Stir into mixture.
Mix in enough reserved flour to make soft dough.
Knead 3 minutes.
Form into rolls and place in greased baking pan.
Let rise 1 to 2 hours; bake in 350° oven.

title: mom and dad's vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients together and fill can with homogenized milk.

title: pecan pie
directions: Lightly flour and prick pie shell with fork.
Prebake 9-inch deep-dish pie shell for 10 minutes.
Cream butter.
Add sugar. Beat well.
Beat eggs in separate dish.
Add eggs to butter and sugar mixture; mix well.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well. Pour into pie shell.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: richard's mushrooms
directions: Wipe mushrooms clean.
Leave whole but remove stems (which you can use for soup).
Lightly oil the bottom of a pan or skillet. Put garlic in bottom of pan; add mushrooms, water or wine and pepper.
Cover pan.
Stir frequently, cooking about 5 minutes. Yield:
4 servings.

title: praline grahams
directions: Separate each graham cracker into four sections.
Arrange in foil lined jelly roll pan with edges touching.

title: noodle delight
directions: Saute onions, garlic and meat in oil until meat is partially cooked.
Add tomatoes, corn and seasonings.
Simmer while boiling 12 ounces noodles.
Mix all together; add cheese last.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: peach cooler beverage
directions: Puree peaches, honey and small amount of milk.
Add remaining ingredients (adding ice cream slowly).
(May substitute for other fruits.)
Makes 5 glasses.

title: seven stripe jello salad
directions: Mix 1 cup boiling water with 1 box jello.
Pour half the jello into a Pyrex dish.
Place in the refrigerator to gel.
Mix 1/2 cup sour cream with the remaining 1/2 of the jello.
When the jello in the refrigerator is gelled, pour the sour cream-jello mixture on top and place in the refrigerator to gel.

When gelled, take the next flavor of jelly and place 1/2 of the clear jello mixture on top of the sour cream-jello mixture; let gel, then add 1/2 cup sour cream to the other 1/2 of the remaining jello, etc. Keep layering until all 7 have been used.

title: holiday ambrosia
directions: Mix sour cream and sugar together.
Mix sour cream and sugar combo with the rest of the ingredients.

title: chicken bake
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Mix 1/2 cup milk, 1 cup flour, salt and pepper.
Dip chicken in flour mixture and arrange in baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 425° for 30 minutes.
Turn chicken and cover with soup, 3/4 cup milk and 1/4 cup water mixture.
Bake 30 minutes longer at 350°.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt oleo in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix other ingredients into batter and pour over melted butter.
Add 1 large can undrained sliced peaches and spread over batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Sprinkle sugar on top after baking.

title: pancakes
directions: Mix and pour onto hot grill.

title: boiled custard
directions: Cook 1 box brownies with walnuts as shown on box. Cool and break in pieces.

title: creamy fruit salad
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Add whipped cream and sugar. Fold in fruit cocktail and marshmallows.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Heat oil in large skillet on medium high heat.
Add chicken, season to taste.
Add onion and pepper, cook and stir until chicken is cooked through.
Add corn, broth and salsa.
Bring to boil. Stir in rice, cover.
Remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes. Fluff with fork.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and let stand until cheese melts, about 2 minutes.

title: picnic potato salad
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, bring water and salt to full boil; add potatoes.
Cook over high heat until potatoes are tender (12 to 15 minutes).
Rinse under cold water.
In large bowl, stir together remaining ingredients except bacon and green onion.
Add potatoes; toss to coat.
Sprinkle with bacon and green onion.

title: fern's hamburger and gravy dinner
directions: Make hamburger into patties or balls and brown.
Pour off fat. Mix milk and mushroom soup.
Pour over patties.
Cook until gravy browns.
Turn patties over and cook a short time.

title: sandra faye's stuffed pumpkin
directions: Salt Pumpkin overnight.
Brown Meat and Onions.
Add seasoning. Add Cracker Crumbs.
Simmer meat 1 hour (covered).
Stuff Pumpkin and simmer in dutch oven for 1- 1 hours, Steaming Pumpkin.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch greased pan, put rhubarb.
Sprinkle with sugar and Jell-O, then pour the water over the Jell-O.
Add dry cake mix.
Cut oleo in small pieces and place on top.
Then add nuts.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and layer with bananas and vanilla wafers.

title: berry-berry fruit salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add cold water and cinnamon.
Stir until dissolved.
Pour into baking dish and chill until partially set.
Combine blueberry pie filling and pineapple; mix well.
Pour on top of Jell-O mixture.
Chill 4 hours or more until set.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion. Drain fat. Add all sauces and spices and simmer together.

title: sandy's oriental spinach salad
directions: Rinse, dry and chill spinach.
Fry bacon until crisp; crumble. Sprinkle bean sprouts, mushrooms, eggs and bacon over spinach in large salad bowl.
Place remaining ingredients in blender container; blend thoroughly until thick and creamy.
Refrigerate several hours.
Toss with salad just before serving.
Dressing keeps well for several months if placed in tightly sealed jar in refrigerator.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: garden lasagna sauce
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add garlic and onions until onions are clear.
Add next 7 ingredients, followed by next three. Mix well.
Add spaghetti sauce and 1 can tomato paste.
Let simmer for 10 minutes.
Let stand 10 to 15 minutes before adding beaten egg.
Use as sauce for lasagna.

title: easy chocolate sheet cake
directions: Bring to boil oleo, water, Crisco and cocoa.
Add to mixture of flour and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Put in greased sheet pan.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 400°.

title: lollipops
directions: You will also need 8 (5 ounce) or 5 (8 ounce) unwaxed paper cups and lollipop sticks.

title: cake with jello
directions: Fix Jell-O according to directions; chill.
Beat until fluffy. Fold in fruit and whipped topping. Pour over angel food cake, that is torn into small pieces.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Mix and pour into baking dish.
Top with crackers and margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: muffins
directions: Combine milk and sugar.
Stir in egg whites and butter.
Stir in vanilla.
Stir in flour, a little at a time, to make a good batter.
Drop in a greased muffin pan.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: classic pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In medium bowl, beat eggs slightly. Add sugar, corn syrup, butter and vanilla. Stir until well blended. Stir in pecans. Pour into pie crust. Bake 50 to 55 minutes. Makes 8 servings.

title: stuffed hamburgers
directions: Mix hamburger and salt.
Divide into 12 equal parts.
Flatten each between pieces of waxed paper until about 5 inches in diameter.
Leave each patty on paper.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Divide among 6 patties.
Top each with a patty and press edges together with a fork.
Broil on both sides until brown.

title: crowd pleaser potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes with bay leaf, not too soft.
Cool.
Peel and grate (on coarse grater).
Add butter to soup, sour cream, Cheddar cheese and green onions.
Add salt and pepper to sauce and mix.

title: cherry square
directions: Mix all ingredients together except pie filling to form dough; take 1/2 dough and roll on wax paper, then transfer to cookie sheet.
Dough should be big enough to cover whole cookie sheet with dough to hang over sides such as you would with a pie. Spread cherry pie filling over dough.
Take remaining dough and place on top; pinch together top and bottom dough.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain.
Mix soups and beans together and heat.
Layer chips and meat in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Top with half of soup and bean mixture.
Add second layer with remaining ingredients.
Cover top with shredded cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Serve with salad.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Heat pineapple; add Jell-O and stir until dissolved.
Cool. Add the buttermilk, Cool Whip and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour into mold and chill.

title: coconut pumpkin cream pie
directions: In a saute pan on medium heat, melt margarine, coconut, pecans and sugar.
Saute until slightly browned.
Cool.
Next blend cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip until well mixed.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix all the ingredients well and pour into a greased loaf or sheet cake pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 300° or until done.

title: sour cream banana pudding
directions: Pour milk into large bowl.
Add pudding and beat at low speed until
thick.
Beat in sour cream until smooth.
Fold in half the Cool Whip.	Layer wafers, bananas, then pudding mix, in this order until
all
pudding
mix
is used up.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with wafer crumbs.

title: chicken diable
directions: Wash chicken pieces; pat dry.
Remove skin, if you wish.
Melt oleo in shallow baking pan.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Roll chicken pieces in mixture to coat both sides, then arrange meaty side up in a single layer in same pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour; can turn halfway through.

title: sourdough starter and biscuits
directions: Combine the ingredients in a stone crock, glass or pottery bowl; beat well.
Cover with cloth; let stand 2 days in a warm place.

title: crab enchilada
directions: Chop onion and bell peppers.
Fry in oil until brown.
Add tomato puree and sauce.
Cook on slow fire for 1 hour.
Add crabs and cook another 1 1/2 hours.

title: fruit glow punch
directions: In a large punch bowl, combine concentrates and apple juice. Stir in ginger ale.
Spoon sherbet into bowl.
Serve immediately.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Combine cornmeal and buttermilk; let stand 30 minutes.
Mix remainder of ingredients while you wait.
Sift flour, sugar, salt and soda into bowl; add egg and milk.
Add chilies, pimentos, corn and cheese.
Mix well.
Bake in well-greased pan at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: enchilada squares
directions: Cook ground beef and onions until beef is cooked and onions are soft.
Drain excess fat.
Spread on bottom of 10 x 6-inch baking dish.
Beat 2 eggs, milk, tomato sauce and enchilada sauce mix.
Pour over meat.
Sprinkle with olives and top with corn chips.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until firm in center.
Sprinkle with cheese and return to oven for 3 to 5 minutes.

title: wedding cake frosting
directions: Sift sugar and salt; add Crisco and egg whites.
Beat with mixer until thick.
Add 2 tablespoons cornstarch if it isn't thick enough.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Drain off liquid of peas and asparagus.
Put in casserole dish with diced eggs.
Pour soup with just enough liquid to spread on peas and asparagus.
Top with bread crumbs.
Dot with margarine or grated cheese and cook until brown.

title: philadelphia cream cheese tarts
directions: Mix ingredients and refrigerate overnight, then cut into 2-inch squares.
Put in filling and squeeze ends together.
Bake in hot oven.
Very good with apricot or nut filling.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes on ungreased sheet.
Use 3 cans Solo for double recipe, single recipe use 1 1/2 cans.

title: cheese cake
directions: Chill Milnot; whip later.
Mix Jell-O in 1 cup hot water and let cool.
Cream together cream cheese and sugar; set aside.
Mix cheese and sugar mix with Jell-O.
Whip Milnot and fold in sugar, cream and Jell-O mixture.
Add lemon juice and pour into prepared graham cracker crust.
Top with a sprinkling of graham cracker crumbs.

title: english trifle
directions: Make up Jell-O as directed using juice from fruit salad and water.
Stir in fruit salad and ladyfingers.
Pour into large bowl (preferably glass).
Allow to set.
Use 1 1/2 packages of custard powder or 2 tablespoons sugar and small amount of milk to blend. Stir until smooth.
Boil remaining milk in pan and pour over custard mixture stirring all the time.
Return mixture to pan and bring back to boil stirring; simmer for 3 minutes.
Allow to cool. Cover with wax paper.
Smooth custard over Jell-O; refrigerate. Beat cream until thick and spread over custard.
I usually run a fork across surface of cream in both directions to create a pattern.
Decorate with halved glace cherries and slivered almonds.
Serves 12.

title: blackberry cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; add eggs and mix well.
Add blackberries and sift flour with spices and soda and add to sugar mixture, then add raisins and nuts.
Bake in 3 greased 9-inch pans at 350° for 35 minutes.
Frost with your favorite frosting.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw and pat spinach dry.
Chop spinach fine.
Mix all ingredients together.
Store in the refrigerator.
Better after it sets for a few hours.
This is good with crackers, breads or Fritos dip size chips.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Mix all ingredients, except flour. Then add flour.
Mix well with spoon.
Bake for one hour in two well greased loaf pans at 300°.
Cool thoroughly before slicing or freezing.

title: scalloped pineapple casserole
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Stir in pineapple.
Gently fold in bread cubes.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
(Great side dish with ham.)

title: senate bean soup
directions: Cover beans with water; bring to boil and boil for 2 minutes. Remove from heat.
Cover pan and let set for 1 hour.
Drain beans and measure liquid; add enough water to make 5 quarts.
Bring to boil and simmer, covered, for 2 hours.
Add remaining ingredients except salt and pepper and simmer covered 1 hour longer.
Remove bone, cut up meat and return meat to soup.
Season to taste.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Melt butter and cheese.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into large casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: onion pie
directions: Cook onions in oil until golden, but not brown.
Spread onions on bottom of pie shell.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Mix egg with cream; pour over all.
Bake until the pie is slightly brown on top.
Sprinkle crumbled bacon over the top and serve. (This may be served with a salad, a drink and dessert.)
Bake for 20 minutes at 450° or until pie is brown.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: grilled red snapper
directions: Mix together butter, lemon juice and seasoning mix.
Pour over fish and let marinate for 30 to 45 minutes, then grill over hot coals until done.
Add mixture to fish while grilling.
Serve with steamed vegetables or grilled vegetables wrapped in foil such as squash, broccoli, red bell pepper and cauliflower or zucchini.
If grilling vegetables, put butter, salt and pepper on vegetables and wrap in foil; place on grill where coals aren't so hot.

title: easy chili
directions: Combine beef and onion in a Dutch oven; cook until beef is browned, stirring to crumble meat.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients, except beans.
Continue to cook, covered, 45 minutes. Remove cover and cook an additional 15 minutes.
This is when you add beans, the last 15 minutes.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix together the sour cream and taco seasoning.
Layer all ingredients in a wide shallow bowl in the order given.
Chill well.
Serve with large bowl of taco chips, nacho chips or large Fritos.

title: almond cream tarts
directions: Place the cream cheese, milk, pudding mix and almond extract in a blender jar.
Cover and process at medium speed until smooth. Pour immediately into tart shells, distributing mixture evenly. Chill for 30 minutes, then top each tart with sliced fruit in decorative patterns.
Brush arranged fruit with the melted apricot jam and serve.
Or keep topped tarts refrigerated until ready to serve.
Yields 6 servings.

title: cauliflower cheese salad
directions: In a small bowl, combine mayonnaise and sugar; set aside.
In large bowl, combine cauliflower, green pepper, onion, bacon and cheese.
Pour dressing over vegetable mixture and refrigerate 3 to 4 hours before serving.

title: lo-cal soup
directions: Fill pot with vegetables, then fill with water.
Cook until tender (1 to 2 hours).

title: cheezie onion loaf
directions: Butter bread and mix together mayo, cheese and onion.
Spread on bread halves.
Sprinkle with whole oregano and black pepper to taste and Parmesan cheese.
Place on foil-lined cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 20 minutes until golden brown.
Let cool for 5 minutes before cutting.
Garlic may be added, if desired.

title: fresh corn salad
directions: In a pot of boiling salted water, cook corn for 3 minutes until starchiness is gone. Drain and immerse it in ice water to stop cooking and to set the color. When cool, cut kernels off the cob, cutting close to the cob. Toss the kernels in large bowl with red onions, vinegar, olive oil, salt and pepper. Just before serving, toss in fresh basil. Taste for seasonings and serve cold or at room temperature. Serves 4 to 6.

title: pretzels
directions: Melt butter in 15-inch cookie sheet.
Add pretzels.
Sprinkle soup mix.
Mix well.
Bake 1 hour at 250°.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown hamburger meat in deep skillet or frying pan.
Add peppers and onion.
Cook about 10 minutes.
Add tomato juice. When this is bubbling, add rice.
Cover and cook slowly about 30 minutes; stir occasionally.
Serve hot with garlic toast.

title: candied nuts
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook to soft ball (238°).
Add 2 1/2 cups pecans.
Stir well.
Pour out on wax paper.
Separate with a fork.

title: san antonio chicken
directions: Place each chicken breast between sheets of wax paper. Flatten chicken to 1/4 inch thickness, using a meat mallet, or rolling pin.
Season to taste.
Place jalapenos in center of chicken breast and 2 strips of cheese in center.
Roll up lengthwise and tuck edges inside.
Secure with toothpicks.
Roll chicken in the flour, packing it.
Combine egg and milk; dip chicken in egg mixture, then roll in bread crumbs.
Fry chicken in DEEP hot oil, 375 degrees, for 8 minutes or until golden brown. Drain thoroughly on paper towels and serve immediately.

title: zucker's brooklyn egg cream
directions: Pour chocolate syrup into cup, until bottom is covered.
Pour in the milk, (so the milk runs on the side of the cup). Take a spoon and pour the club sode over it. Mix quickly and Drink.

title: cherry crumb cake
directions: Combine above ingredients, except pie filling; mix thoroughly. Pour into pan; spread filling over batter.
Sprinkle crumb mixture over cherries.
(You can use any kind of pie filling.)
Bake in one 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 60 minutes or until done.

title: red beans and rice
directions: In a large frying pan, fry bacon until crisp (or sausage until brown).
Remove from pan.
Crumble and reserve.
Saute onions, celery and green pepper in bacon/sausage grease until tender.
Add rice, tomatoes, crumbled bacon and seasonings.
Cook on top of the stove for 10 minutes.
Pour into large, greased casserole dish. Cover tightly and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: ham pot pie
directions: Put ham bone in kettle with enough water to cover; simmer 2 hours.

title: crab bisque
directions: Add everything to sauteed onions.
Add crab last.
If you make it a day ahead, add crab before serving.
Can be frozen.

title: millionaire's pie
directions: Slowly beat lemon juice into the milk. Fold in whipped topping. Fold in fruit and nuts.
Pour into prepared pie crusts. Chill at least 2 hours before serving.

title: clam chowder
directions: Put onion, celery, potatoes and clams (with juice) in large pot.
Cook until tender, about 20 minutes.
In microwave, melt butter.
Add flour and stir until you have a smooth paste.
Slowly add 1/2 cup half and half into flour/butter mixture.
Stir into vegetables slowly.
Add remaining half and half and the salt, sugar and pepper.
Enjoy!

title: hash browns
directions: Defrost hash browns.
Combine next 6 ingredients. Mix with hash browns. Place in greased casserole dish, 9 x 13, and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cheese logs
directions: Grate sharp Cheddar cheese with a fine grater.
Place grated cheese in large mixing bowl and soften with cream cheese.
Add Worcestershire sauce, garlic powder, salt and cayenne pepper.
Mix well.

Divide into 3 equal parts and roll into cheese logs. Sprinkle paprika on wax paper and roll cheese logs over paprika. Wrap each cheese log individually in wax paper and store in refrigerator up to 3 weeks.

title: oven chicken barbecue
directions: Mix ketchup, honey and garlic.
Pour over chicken that has been placed in a baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, turning chicken once.

title: crabbies ii
directions: Cut English muffins in half; set aside.
Mix the butter, mayonnaise, onion salt, Cheez Whiz, garlic powder and crabmeat well.
Spread mixture on muffin halves and lay in single layer on cookie sheet.
Place in freezer for 10 minutes until slightly firm.
Cut each half into quarters and store in bag in freezer.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on package.
Boil pineapple with 1 c sugar.
Pour over cake while hot.
Cool 20 minutes.
Spread prepared pudding on cake.
Mix Cool Whip with sour cream and spread over pudding on cake.
Put pecans and coconut on cake.

title: dinner rolls
directions: In a mixing bowl, soak yeast in water for 5 minutes.
Add salt, sugar, oil, egg and 2 cups flour.
Beat 2 minutes.
Add 1 1/2 cups flour; mix in with wooden spoon.
Place dough on a floured pastry cloth.
Knead until dough is elastic, approximately 8 minutes. Place in a greased bowl.
Cover; let raise in warm spot until doubled, approximately 1 1/2 hours.
Shape into rolls and put into 2 greased (9 or 10-inch) round pans.
Raise 1 1/2 hours.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Yields 14 to 16 rolls.

title: cheese straws
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cool in refrigerator.
Shape into 3-inch strips, size of a pencil.
Bake in 350° to 400° oven for about 8 minutes.

title: turkey burgers
directions: Combine ingredients and shape into 4 to 6 patties.
Melt 1 Tbsp. butter in skillet.
Cook over medium heat 3 to 4 minutes on each side until well browned.
Do not overcook.
Serve on hamburger buns.
Good with horseradish sauce.

title: lemon angel squares
directions: Bake and cool cake as directed on package.
Pour boiling water on gelatin; stir until gelatin is dissolved.
Refrigerate until thickened but not set.
Add enough cold water to lemonade concentrate to measure 2 cups; stir into gelatin.
Beat until foamy.
Beat the whipping cream in chilled bowl until stiff; fold into gelatin.
Tear cake into gelatin mixture.
Spread in ungreased 13 x 9-inch rectangular baking dish.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours or until firm.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: cheesy ground beef casserole
directions: Cook noodles, rinse and set aside.
Saute 1/4 cup onion in margarine in large skillet until tender.
Add ground beef and cook until lightly browned; drain well.
Add tomato sauce, salt and pepper; stir and simmer 20 minutes.
Combine cottage cheese, sour cream and remaining onion; stir well and set aside.
Place noodles in a lightly greased 2 1/2-quart casserole; spoon cottage cheese mixture over noodles.
Spoon meat mixture over cheese mixture and sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes. Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: potato chowder
directions: Cut potatoes into bite size pieces and just cover with water. Cook until tender.
Saute onions and green peppers in margarine. Add potatoes (do not drain) to onions and peppers.
Add soup, corn and milk.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Easy and quick.

title: easy-do coconut fudge
directions: In medium saucepan, combine chips and butter. Stir constantly over low heat until smooth. Remove from heat.
Stir in milk, salt and vanilla. Add frosting mix; mix well.
Spread in ungreased 8 or 9-inch square pan. Refrigerate 30 minutes. Cut into squares. Store in refrigerator. Makes 64 (1 inch) squares.

title: pacific lime mold
directions: Make lime Jell-O; chill until it is the consistency of unbeaten egg white.
Beat with mixer until it gets foamy; gradually add bits of softened cream cheese and beat well.
Add sour cream and continue beating.
Blend in crushed pineapple; pour into mold and refrigerate.

title: cheesy cherry cake
directions: Cream cheese, butter sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour gradually.
Fold in nuts and cherries.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Cover with vanilla glaze.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream the butter and sugar together.
Mix in egg.
Add mashed bananas.
Add dry ingredients.
Blend in nuts.
Bake in greased loaf pan at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Use enough water to cover vegetables.
Bring to a boil for 2 to 3 minutes until vegetables are still crisp.
Drain off liquid. Cover with 1 bottle Italian dressing.
Blanch 1 pound fresh mushrooms.
Add to vegetable mixture.
Refrigerate.
Will keep for days.

title: referees' favorite potato salad
directions: Cut turkey bacon into 1/2-inch pieces.
Heat in skillet on medium 8 minutes or until lightly browned, stirring occasionally. Combine mayonnaise, mustard and garlic powder in a large bowl.
Add potatoes, turkey bacon, cucumber and onion.
Refrigerate.
Makes six 1/2 cup servings.

title: spiritual food cake
directions: You start with cup of thoughts, then add consideration for others, sacrifice, well beaten faults and forgiveness.
Now you mix them up good.
Add tears of joy, sorrow and sympathy.
Then you flavor with little gifts of love and kindly service.
Now pour in prayer and faith.
That's just to lighten the ingredients and raise the texture to great heights of character and Christian living.

title: dressing for fruit salad
directions: Blend flour into sugar.
Add water, butter, egg and vinegar. Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Cool and use as needed over a desired combination of diced apples, celery, pecans, grapes, pineapple tidbits and marshmallows.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups.

title: zesty vegetable toss
directions: Combine all vegetables in a large mixing bowl.
Add Zesty Italian dressing and mix.
Let cool in refrigerator.

title: dry seasoning marinade
directions: Mix together.
Use on fish, baked chicken or pork.
Sprinkle and leave a few hours.
If broiling, spray often with lemon water.

title: bread pudding
directions: Place bread cubes in a greased 1-quart casserole.
Combine eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla.
Gradually blend in scalded milk. Pour over bread cubes.
Set casserole in a pan of hot water and bake in a slow oven at 325° for 1 hour or until a knife inserted halfway between center and outside edge comes out clean.

title: chutney
directions: Cut up; chop fine.
Bring to boil.
Simmer 5 minutes.

title: butternut chewies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease pan with butter.
Beat eggs until light and foamy.
Beat in sugar, vanilla and butter until creamy.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; add to egg mixture.
Mix at low speed until blended.
Stir in nuts (mixture will be stiff).
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes (or until top is lightly browned).
Cool 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: venison tenderloin with crab meat stuffing
directions: Mix up 2 cups of cornmeal, 1 cup flour, 2 eggs and buttermilk to cornbread consistency.
Bake at 400 degrees until golden brown. Season tenderloin with Lawry's season salt & pepper.
Slice tenderloin down the center, crumble cornbread into bite size pieces.
Add crab meat and enough water to moisten.
Season with Lawry's & pepper.
Put stuffing down center of tenderloin and wrap with string.
Wrap strips of bacon around tenderloin and secure with toothpicks.
Place in oblong baking dish. Do not cover.
Bake at 200 degrees for 3-4 hours until center internal temperature reaches 180 degrees.
Remove from oven and let sit for 30 minutes. Slice and serve.

title: seedless green grape pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Make your favorite pie crust; stir sugar, flour and salt together.
Mix gently with washed grapes.
Pour into pastry-lined pie pan; dot with butter.
Cover with top crust; make a couple of slits and lightly sprinkle with sugar or make lattice top if preferred.
Bake for 35 to 45 minutes.
Is best served warm.

title: oven meatballs
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine milk, onion and eggs.
Add bread, let stand for 5 minutes.
Add meat and seasonings.
Mix thoroughly.
Shape into 4 dozen small balls, 1 1/2-inch diameter. Place on baking pan and bake for 20 to 30 minutes.
Yields 8 servings (6 per serving).
Each serving contains approximately (Exchanges): 2 meat, 1/2 bread.

title: tortilla roll
directions: Mix all ingredients until smooth.
Spread evenly over tortilla and roll up.

title: frozen cut corn
directions: Do not blanch corn!
Stir together all ingredients and put in freezer bags or plastic containers and freeze to enjoy later!

title: salmon spread
directions: Drain salmon; remove skin and flake.
Mix cream cheese, lemon juice, onion, horseradish, salt, Worcestershire sauce, pepper and liquid smoke.
Stir in salmon.

title: *lamb with orzo(ghela cu manestra)
directions: Heat oil in a large saucepan and brown meat and onions for 10 minutes over medium heat. Add tomato sauce, seasonings and 2 cups water. Cover and simmer for 1 1/2 hours until meat is tender.
Add remaining water and bring to a boil.
Add manestra. Stir once or twice. Simmer 20 minutes more.
Serve hot with grated cheese.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Beat eggs and add sugar.
Beat well and add butter, flour, buttermilk and vanilla; mix well.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle coconut over pies about 5 minutes before removing from oven.

title: chicken or turkey pot pie
directions: Heat butter over low heat until melted.
Blend in flour, onion, garlic and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat. Stir in broth and milk.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly. Boil and stir for 1 minute.
Stir in chicken and vegetables.
Pour into crust; top with crust and cut slits in top.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 425°.
Makes 2 pies.

title: zippy beef spread
directions: Blend together cheese, mayonnaise, sherry & onion.
Stir in finely snipped beef and chopped olives.
Serve on assorted crackers

title: good pie crust
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Roll on floured board.
Will make one 9-inch two crust pie.

title: country apple dessert
directions: Combine cake mix, oleo and egg.
Mix at low speed until crumbly.
Press into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread with pie filling.
Combine brown sugar, nuts and cinnamon; sprinkle over apples.
Blend sour cream, egg and vanilla; pour over rest.

title: fruit smash(a coffee cake)
directions: Blend all together, except pie filling, until crumbly.
Press 2/3 of mixture into bottom of lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Top with pie filling.
Crumble remaining mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, until golden.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk, lemon juice and egg yolks.
Put in pie crust.
If desired, beat egg whites and brown them on top of pie, then cool and set in refrigerator.

title: congealed lime salad
directions: Dissolve jello and cream cheese in 1 cup of hot water.
Add 1 cup of pineapple juice; let jell.
Add whipped cream, pecans and drained pineapple; beat well and let jell again.

title: rice casserole
directions: Cook celery and onions in margarine.
Mix all ingredients. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: fudge
directions: In large bowl, put all ingredients, except nuts and margarine. Mix lightly.
Lay stick of margarine on top and microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Beat well and add nuts.

title: fried chicken fingers
directions: Mix milk and egg together in bowl.
In a separate bowl mix flour, parsley flakes, salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Cut chicken into 1-inch strips.
Heat oil in skillet or use deep fryer.
Cover chicken strips in milk and egg mixture.
One strip at a time batter in flour mixture.
Cook in oil for 5 to 6 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve with favorite sauce.

title: pie crust
directions: First Mixture:
Mix flour, sugar and salt.
Cut in shortening.

title: pie crust
directions: Blend all dry ingredients.
Break one egg in one measuring cup.
Finish filling the cup with water.
Mix well.
(You may need to add a little more water.)
Bake in 325 degree oven until brown. Makes 5-6 crusts.
Keeps well in the refrigerator.
Each pie serves 6.

title: best sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs, mix well. Sift soda and cream tartar with flour. Add to the first mixture alternatively with milk and vanilla. Roll thin, cut and bake.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken until tender. Reserve broth. Chop chicken and spread in bottom of casserole dish. Drain vegetables and spread over chicken.
Mix soups with 1 1/2 cans reserved broth.
Pour over vegetables.
Make crust by mixing flour, milk, butter and pepper.
Spread over casserole.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: chili elegante
directions: Soak dry chili beans overnight. Cook in boiling, salted water until tender. Drain.
