Brown onion, green pepper and meat in hot fat. Add tomatoes, seasonings and dry sherry.
Simmer 2 hours. Add water, if necessary. Add beans and heat thoroughly. Freezes well. Serves 6.

title: layered pea salad
directions: Layer all ingredients in order given.
Do not toss. Refrigerate overnight.

title: 100 year old cake recipe
directions: Cream sugar and oleo.
Add eggs and flour, one egg at a time, with a little flour, stirring about 2 minutes for each egg.
Bake in a tube pan at 350° until brown.

title: crunchy apple crisp
directions: Place pie filling in shallow, one-quart baking pan.
In a small bowl, mix oats, flour, sugar, spice and salt.
Cut margarine in small pieces.
Mix well.
Spread topping evenly over apple filling.
Bake in oven at 375° for about 30 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.

title: pineapple delight pie
directions: This makes 2 pies (reduce ingredients in half for 1 pie).

title: refrigerator cookies
directions: Mix Crisco, sugar, eggs and vanilla together.
Measure flour with soda and salt.
Stir in with sugar and Crisco.
Form into roll 2-inches across; wrap in waxed paper.
Chill until firm.
Heat oven to 400°.
Slice 1/8-inch thick.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet; bake 8 to 10 minutes at 400°.

title: corn and sausage
directions: Lightly brown onion & links with butter.
Add corn and tomatoes.
Simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Good over rice.

title: six week muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large bowl.
Mix well, then add wet ingredients and stir well.
Store in refrigerator.
When ready to use, fill muffin pans 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes. Batter will keep in refrigerator for six weeks.

title: key lime pie
directions: Lime Mix:
Mix condensed milk with 4 egg yolks and 1/2 cup lime juice.
Beat 1 egg white stiff.
Fold into mixture.

title: spoonburgers
directions: Preheat skillet over medium heat for 3 minutes.
Add beef, onion and celery.
Brown.
Stir in flour, catsup, chili sauce, Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice and chili powder.
Blend well. Cover.
Reduce heat to low and simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Spoon mixture into buns.

title: kielbasa and sauerkraut
directions: Brown sausage in large pot or skillet.
Add sauerkraut and potatoes.
Let simmer for 1/2 hour or so and add wine.
Cover and cook until potatoes are done or you can't stand it any more and you have to have some.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together good, then put in the Rice Krispies.
Shape into balls.
Put in refrigerator until cold. Melt the paraffin and chocolate chips together.
Dip balls. Place on wax paper.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix and pour in buttered dish.

title: brownies
directions: Combine all of the ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
(I boil mine in chicken broth instead of adding margarine.)
Mix everything together.
Reserve some cheese for top.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: frozen cucumber salad
directions: Boil all ingredients together (except cukes).
Let cool.
Peel and slice the cukes and salt lightly.
Let stand for 2 hours, then squeeze well.
Put into containers, cover with cooled brine and freeze.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients (mix flour into meat for best results).
Drop meatballs in hot fat and brown. Add the mushroom soup and bouillon soup. Simmer 2 hours on stove or oven at 350°. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Beat in the eggs.
Mix in pineapple; fold in bread.
Place in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serve hot or cold.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: apple nut cake
directions: Mix together sugar, eggs and oil.
Beat in flour, salt, cinnamon and baking soda.
Fold in apples and nuts.
Put in oblong pan.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice and drain.
Add broccoli, butter, soup and cheese. Simmer until cheese is melted.
Spread cracker crumbs in bottom of casserole dish.
Top with broccoli mix.
Top with cracker crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: stuffed beef heart
directions: Prepare heart for stuffing.
Slice heart in half and remove the hard parts.
Apply salt to taste.
Close the slit with metal skewers, then lace and tie with string forming pocket.
For stuffing, cook onion in shortening until tender.
Add onion, celery, bread cubes and enough beef broth to moisten.
Fill lightly with stuffing and cover opening with foil; tie in place. Place in Dutch oven.
Cover heart with tomatoes and add remaining ingredients.
Cover; simmer 2 1/2 hours.

title: apple crumble
directions: Place apples in lightly buttered 8-inch pie pan.
Blend the remainder of the ingredients, cutting in butter.
Crumble over apples.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream or vanilla ice cream.

title: very low-fat gravy (chicken)
directions: Add bouillon to boiling water; stir to dissolve.
Combine cornstarch and cold water in shaker jar; shake well.
Remove pan with bouillon mixture from heat; add cornstarch mixture and stir with wire whisk.
Return pan to heat (medium) and cover until thickened.
Add sage; stir and serve.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown onion, hamburger and garlic.
Mix tomato sauce, water and red chili sauce.
Layer tortillas, meat, olives, some of the cheese, and chili sauce.
End with tortillas and cheese; cover with the chili sauce.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine cranberries, orange and 1 cup sugar.
Let stand 1 hour.
Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add sugar and let cool. Mix all ingredients together and congeal.

title: perfect pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add vanilla and mix well.
Add eggs one at a time beating thoroughly.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Now add a little at a time to creamed mixture alternating with the milk.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until golden brown.

title: slush
directions: Heat water and sugar.
Add green tea bags and let cool. Remove bags and add orange juice, lemonade and whiskey or brandy. Stir well and put in freezer; stir several times during next 12 hours.
Put into small containers to keep in freezer, if desired. Keep frozen until ready to serve.

title: "dear heloise's" olive nut sandwich spread
directions: Let cream cheese stand at room temperature until soft.
Mash with a fork and add mayonnaise.
Add chopped pecans, olives and olive juice.
Stir well.
Add pepper to taste.
The mixture should be mushy.
Store in pint jars for 24 to 48 hours.
It will thicken.
Good on thin toast or on thin bread and lettuce.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix all together, and shape into meatballs.
Place in a 13x9x2 inch cake pan.
These can be stacked on top of each other.

title: chocolate chip-pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Add eggs.
Add butter, pecans, chocolate chips and vanilla.
Pour into pie crust and bake 1 hour at 325°. You may substitute walnuts for the pecans.
The crust will not burn if you cover edges with aluminum foil.

title: english pea casserole
directions: Combine peas, water chestnuts, onion, soup and pimento. Sprinkle
cheese
on
top.
Combine
Ritz crackers and butter; sprinkle on top.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: beggar's chicken
directions: You will need foil, butcher paper and wet clay.

title: ginger meatballs
directions: In a medium bowl, mix all ingredients.
With a light touch, shape into about 3 dozen 1-inch balls.
Place meatballs on a round microwave rack.
Cover with paper towels.
Cook on High 5 to 7 minutes or until just cooked through.
Turn rack if meatballs appear to be cooking unevenly.

title: christmas wassail
directions: Combine and boil first 4 ingredients for 10 to 15 minutes; add juices.
Serve hot.
For decoration, can float orange slices on top.

title: sugarless sweets
directions: Run all through a food chopper, then form into balls. Dip balls into melted chocolate and drop on greased platter, or roll in dried coconut which has been slightly browned in the oven.

title: golden pumpkin bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for a glass dish).
Reserve 1/2 cup dry cake mix.
In large mixer bowl, combine remaining cake mix, oil and 1 egg; beat until crumbly.
Stir in nuts, if desired. Press firmly on bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.

title: applesauce bran muffins
directions: Stir the bran, milk, applesauce, oil and egg together.
Stir together the dry ingredients.
Add the bran mixture to the dry ingredients, stirring just to moisten.
Bake in a 375° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Raisins or nuts are optional.
Makes 24 muffins.

title: cabbage
directions: Boil cabbage 10 minutes.
Add other ingredients to cabbage. Bring to boil.

title: mock perogi
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Combine onions, margarine, mushrooms and soup.
Cook sauerkraut in its own juice, then wash and drain well.
Add sauerkraut to noodle mixture.
Place in casserole (greased) and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: potato supreme(serves 12 to 14)
directions: Defrost potatoes and combine in large bowl with butter.
Add rest of ingredients, except crumbs.
Put in 3-quart casserole dish.
Spray with Pam.
Top with crumbs or bread.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: creamy lemon pie
directions: Pour milk into large bowl. Add pudding mixes and beat with a whisk for 30 seconds. Add lemonade concentrate and beat with a whisk for 30 seconds; mixture will be thick. Immediately stir in whipped topping and spoon into crust. Refrigerate 4 hours or until set. Garnish with lemon slices if desired. Store in the refrigerator.

title: yam casserole
directions: Mix together in large mixing bowl first 7 ingredients.
Heat rum and raisins in small pan over low heat for 5 minutes.
Cool lightly and beat into yam mixture.
Grease a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan.
Pour mixture into pan and bake for 40 to 50 minutes. Remove from oven.

title: nevelle's icebox lemon pie(serves 8)
directions: Combine egg yolks and 1/2 cup sugar.
Add milk, then lemon juice.
Pour into pie shell (recipe follows).
Top with meringue (recipe follows).
Bake at 325° until light to golden brown.

title: coconut oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream
butter
and
sugar
until fluffy.
Add 1 egg and vanilla.
Beat
well.
Add
dry ingredients, oatmeal and coconut, mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on greased baking sheet. Bake about 12 minutes at about 375°.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Place slightly thawed hash browns in casserole.
Mix soup and sour cream; pour over potatoes.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
(Add instant minced onions, Nature's Seasons and seasoned salt for a more flavorful casserole.)

title: cabbage hot dish
directions: Cut cabbage.
Add soup and hamburger.
Cook in oven for 1 1/2 hours at 375°.
I also put this in the crock-pot for 5 or 6 hours.

title: monkey chips
directions: Cut each biscuit into quarters.
Toss biscuits into a cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Place into Bundt pan or casserole dish (a little spritz of nonstick spray won't hurt).
Melt the butter, Karo syrup and brown sugar.
Pour over the top of the biscuits. Bake at 350°.
Check after 30 minutes.
Put plate over top and flip immediately after taking out of the oven.
Serve warm or at room temperature.
Great to set in the middle of the table when you have a few people over for coffee.

title: aunt rita's potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees.
Place potatoes in a large pot and cover with water.
Bring water to a boil, then reduce heat, cover, and cook until done.
Peel and dice.
Put in a 9 x 13 baking dish.
Mix other ingredients except milk and cornflake crumbs.
Pour over potatoes, mixing well.
Drizzle milk over potato mixture and cover with cornflake crumbs.
Bake one hour.

title: mike's mexican chicken
directions: Rinse chicken and pat dry. Drain chilies and take out the seeds. You may want to wear rubber gloves to do this. Wrap each chicken breast in a green chili. Place in a greased casserole dish and pour salsa over them. Cover with foil and bake for about 20 to 30 minutes or until done. At this point, you may want to drain off some of the juices from the pan. Top with the cheese and put back into the oven until cheese melts. Serve over the rice.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Brown ground beef, sausage, onions and bell peppers.
Drain. Add to chicken broth.
Combine all ingredients and simmer for 3 hours.

title: chocolate congo squares
directions: Melt margarine.
Add sugar and allow to cool.
Add eggs one at a time and add flour.
Mix well.
Stir in nuts and chocolate bits. Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool.
Cut in 2-inch strips.

title: chili bake
directions: Mix chili,
beans
and	soup together.	Layer in baking dish with Fritos.
Sprinkle
cheese on top.
Bake in 350° oven until heated and cheese has melted.

title: blender breakfast
directions: Blend all ingredients until smooth.

title: no-bake chocolate cookies
directions: Add peanut butter and stir until melted.
Then add oats; mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Cook 1 bag of frozen broccoli in 1 1/2 cups water; dissolve 4 chicken bouillon cubes to make 1 1/2 cups chicken broth.
Add 1 stick oleo; simmer 1/2 hour.
Add 1 can evaporated milk; add 1 cup water.
Season with salt and/or pepper.
Thicken with cornstarch or flour.
Add cheese or croutons before serving.

title: old fashioned mashed potatoes
directions: Peel and cut potatoes into eighths.
Cook potatoes and onion in covered pan of boiling water 15 minutes or until tender.
Drain and add the rest of the ingredients and mash.

title: multi-grain scones
directions: Preheat oven to 350.

title: no fat italian sauce
directions: Mix cornstarch in some cold water.
Add remaining ingredients to pan, then cornstarch and simmer 15 to 20 minutes until desired thickness.

title: continental spritz cookies
directions: Cream butter and powdered sugar.
Beat in egg and vanilla. Sift together flour, baking soda, cream of tartar and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Chill dough.
These can be rolled for cutouts or used in cookie press.
Bake at 375° until lightly brown.

title: hot dog cheesies
directions: Cook the frankfurters.
While they're cooking, spread one side of the bread with soft butter and mustard.
Place bread slices on baking sheet and top each with one slice of cheese.
Place a frankfurter on top of each cheese slice.
Fold over to make a triangle shape.
Fasten with wooden toothpicks.
Melt 1/4 cup butter and brush on each triangle.
Broil sandwiches with tops 4 to 5-inches from heat about 2 minutes or until golden brown. Makes 8 servings.

title: crispy chicken
directions: Mix eggs and milk in small bowl.
In medium bowl with lid add all dry ingredients.
Clean chicken and remove skin if desired (I leave skin on to make crispier).
Dip one piece at a time in egg, then flour mixture.
Shake bowl with lid on and let set for 15 seconds to assure breading will hold to chicken.
Place in deep fryer or hot oil.
Repeat until each piece has been coated and cooked.

title: bacardi daiquiri
directions: Mix pudding mix with gelatin and sugar in a saucepan.
Blend in 1/2 cup of the water and the eggs.
Add remaining water and cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a full boil. Remove from heat; stir in rum.
Chill.
Fold in whipped topping. Spoon into pie crust and chill firm, about 2 hours.
Garnish with additional whipped topping and lime slices.
Very good.
Stir with a kiss and lots of love.

title: pig treats
directions: You will also need wax paper and a pig cookie cutter.

title: golden glow salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add orange juice; stir until dissolved.
Add cold water and fruits.
Pour into mold; chill.
Yield: 10 to 15 servings.

title: holiday salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water, using only 1 1/2 cups of water (as juice in pineapple and cranberry sauce is used to help dissolve gelatin).
Add sugar and other ingredients; stir well. (I leave sugar out.)

title: corn bread broccoli pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Prepare cornbread according to package directions.
Stir in Spam.
Spread into greased 9-inch pie plate. Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until corn bread is almost done.
Arrange broccoli spears on top of corn bread, sprinkle with cheese. Return to oven and bake 5 to 10 minutes or until cheese is melted and corn bread is completely baked.
Makes about six servings.

title: buttermilk cake
directions: Beat sugar, Crisco and eggs well.
Add soda to buttermilk and add to egg mixture.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together. Add to egg mixture.
Add flavoring and blend well.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie #2
directions: Beat together confectioners sugar and peanut butter until mixture is crumbly; set aside.

title: apple bread
directions: Place oil, sugar, nuts, eggs and apples in large bowl and beat by hand.
Add flour, soda, salt, vanilla and cinnamon until well mixed.
Bake in greased pans (2 loaf pans) 40 minutes at 350°.

title: boone tavern spoon bread
directions: Cook milk, butter, salt and corn meal until mush.
Put in mixing bowl.
Beat eggs in one at a time and add sugar.
Put in deep dish and bake at 350°
for 1 hour.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger and onions.
Then drain off grease real good. Put back in pan and put taco seasoning and 3/4 cup of water.
Let simmer.
When done, mix everything together and serve.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix oil, sugar and eggs together.
In separate bowl, mix flour, baking powder, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add all dry ingredients alternately with grated zucchini to first mixture. Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into 3 greased and floured bread pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sausage bread
directions: Bake sausage in oven so fat is drained out, about 30 minutes. Let the dough rise, then spread it out like a pizza pie.
Put on the tomato sauce, sliced sausage, peppers and cheese.
Fold the pizza dough over into a bread loaf; try not to let ingredients seep out.
Bake at 350° until done.
(Baste top of loaf with butter or oil for golden brown look.)
Slice with a bread knife or electric knife.
Serve warm.

title: granola for granolas
directions: Combine oats, coconut, nuts, sunflower seeds, sesame seed and wheat germ in a large bowl.
Heat together oil and honey in microwave or on stovetop until almost boiling.
Stir into dry mixture, mixing well.
Spread a third of mixture in shallow pan. Bake at 325° for 25 minutes, stirring occasionally. Repeat with remaining mixture.

title: sausage and cheese balls
directions: Mix the above ingredients together; form into small balls the size of marbles.
Bake at 400 degrees for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: marinated vidalia onions
directions: Slice onions thin and separate into rings.
Combine water, sugar and vinegar and stir until sugar is dissolved.
Pour over onion rings.
Cover and chill for at least 3 hours.
Drain.
Stir in mayonnaise and celery seed.
Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: rhubarb cobbler
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, sugar and salt.
Cut in Crisco.
Add egg and milk.
Pour over rhubarb mixture.

title: susan's crustless breakfast bake
directions: Rinse the spinach well and place it in a large saucepan with just the water that clings to the leaves.
Place the saucepan over low heat and stir to wilt the spinach, 3 to 4 minutes.
Drain well, squeezing out excess moisture.
Chop coarsely; set aside.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt the butter in a small skillet and saute shallots over medium low heat until translucent, 5 minutes; set aside.
Halve tomatoes and squeeze, releasing and discarding the seeds and juice.
Coarsely chop and set aside.
In medium-size bowl, whisk together milk, eggs, Monterey Jack cheese, dill, lemon zest, salt and pepper.
Stir in the reserved spinach, tomatoes and shallots.
Thoroughly butter an 8-inch square baking pan.
Add the filling and sprinkle with the breadcrumbs and Parmesan.
Bake until golden, 25 minutes.
Let the quiche stand for 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 8 servings.
Per serving:
172 calories, 10.5 g protein, 9 g carbohydrate, 3.5 g fiber, 12 g fat, 100 mg cholesterol, 445 mg sodium.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Melt
chocolate in boiling water.
Cool.
Mix flour and soda. Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each.
Blend in vanilla
and chocolate.
Alternately
add
flour
mixture and buttermilk, beating
after
each addition until smooth.
Beat egg
whites until
stiff peaks form;
fold into batter.
Pour into
three 9-inch
layer
pans,
lined on bottoms with waxed paper.
Bake
at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, or until a toothpick
inserted
in centers
comes out clean.
Immediately run spatula
around pans between cakes and sides.
Cool in pans 15 minutes.
Remove
from pans;
remove
waxed
paper and finish cooling
on racks.
Spread filling and frosting between layers and over top.
Frost with Coconut-Pecan Filling and Frosting.

title: peanut butter candy cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll them into walnut-size balls, flatten with a fork on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 13 minutes.

title: chocolate peanut butter balls
directions: Melt
butter and mix with peanut butter.
Stir in sugar until smooth; add vanilla.
Form into small balls and place on cookie sheet.
Chill in refrigerator for 2 hours or in freezer 1 hour. Melt chocolate chips and wax in double boiler and dip each ball in mixture.
Chill until firm.

title: old-fashioned egg salad
directions: In a bowl, combine mayonnaise, lemon juice, onion, salt and pepper. Stir in eggs and celery. Cover and chill. Use this recipe for the Potato Salad and/or Macaroni Salad recipes. Yields 4 servings.

title: munching onion
directions: Combine cream cheese and salad dressing, mix well. Add remaining ingredients, mix well. Chill, serve with assorted crackers or chips.

title: rabbit casserole
directions: Pressure cook rabbit with water and stick of butter for about 1 hour.
Remove meat from bones.
Place 1/2 of dressing in long casserole dish.
Using broth from which rabbit was cooked, lightly moisten dressing.
Layer rabbit on top of dressing.
Mix together 2 cans soup and 1 1/2 cups of rabbit broth; pour on top of rabbit. Spread remaining dressing on top; lightly moisten with more broth.
Lightly dot top of casserole with butter.
Bake at 375° for about 20 to 25 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: fruit and walnut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. In medium mixing bowl, sift flour, sugar and baking powder together. In a smaller bowl, combine egg, milk and oil. Add to flour mixture, stirring just to blended. Add nuts, raisins and apricots. Stir to blend and pour into loaf pan. Bake 1 hour or until done. Cool in pan 15 minutes. Remove from pan and cool 15 minutes more on a rack. Wrap in foil overnight before slicing. Makes 1 loaf.

title: sweet and zesty meatballs with peppers
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In a large bowl, combine all meatball ingredients; blend well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until browned and thoroughly baked; drain.

title: patriotic gelatin salad
directions: In four separate bowls, dissolve each package of jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Add 1/2 cup cold water to each and stir.
Pour one bowl of blue jello into an oiled 10-inch fluted tube pan. Chill until almost set, about 30 minutes.
Set the other three bowls of jello aside, at room temperature.

title: baco bagel snacks
directions: Spread each bagel half with 1 teaspoon dressing.
Sprinkle with bacon bits and onions.
Arrange bagel halves on broiler pan or cookie sheet and broil 2 minutes or until hot and bubbling. Serve immediately.

title: "no fat" vegetable soup
directions: Peel and cube potatoes.
Place in large soup kettle.
Cover with water and add onion flakes and bouillon granules.
Simmer until potatoes are beginning to be done.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer until potatoes are done.
Serve with fat free crackers or fat free corn chips.

title: date cake
directions: Pour water over dates.
Cool to room temperature.
Stir shortening to soften.
Add sugar and cream together until lighter. Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Sift flour, salt and soda; add to creamed mixture, alternately with the date mixture.
Stir in nuts. Bake in 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pumpkin crunch torte
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended.
Evenly distribute crunch topping in four 9-inch round cake pans.
Pat to cover bottom of pans.
Set aside.

title: nanny's lemon sponge pie
directions: Mix sugar and butter together.
Add milk and egg yolks, then add lemon and juice.
Last you beat white of the eggs and fold in the mixture.
Bake in unbaked pie crust until knife comes out clean.

title: grilled cinnamon apples
directions: Place cored apple in center of 24-inch length of aluminum foil, folded in half.
Fill hole with a tablespoon each of cinnamon candies and raisins.
Dot with butter.
Bring foil up loosely over apple and twist ends together to seal.
Cook over glowing coals for 30 minutes, or until done.
Serve with cream, if desired.

title: marinated slaw
directions: Place chopped cabbage, bell pepper and onion in layers in dish.
Boil vinegar, sugar, salt and celery seed for two minutes. Add oil. Bring to a boil.
Pour over chopped vegetables while hot. Cover tightly.
Refrigerate overnight.
Will keep in refrigerator for 4 to 6 days.

title: classy crabmeat casserole
directions: Combine rice, crabmeat, carrot, cheese, green onions, sour cream, salt and pepper.
Turn into a 1-quart baking dish or 2 individual baking dishes.
Dust with paprika.
Cover and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 2 servings.

title: peaches-n-cream pound cake
directions: Slice pound cake horizontally into 3 layers.
Drain peaches well.
Cut into small pieces.
Fold peaches into Cool Whip.

title: raisin cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Cook raisins with 2 cups of water for 15 minutes.
Do not drain.
Use it all.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan for 1 hour.
May be iced with your favorite vanilla frosting.

title: scandinavian cookies
directions: Roll in 1-inch balls.
Dip in egg white, then in chopped nuts. Place in greased pan.
Make depression in center.
Bake 5 minutes in a 350° oven and press centers.
Continue baking 15 minutes longer.
Fill center with jelly.

title: party punch
directions: Mix well and pour into two gallon milk jugs and freeze.
When ready to serve, take out 6 hours before to thaw.
Pour 2 liter ginger ale into punch mixture and serve.
Serves 50 people.

title: everett's alder jerky
directions: Pre-freeze London Broil.
This makes it easier for slicing. Slice in very thin strips.
Make brine of salt, sugar and water. (Dissolve completely.)
Add meat and brine.
Soak for 30 minutes. Rinse well in colander until meat turns from red to a dull pink. (This takes most of the salt out.)
After putting meat on the racks for your smoker, put on as much pepper as you like.
Put the meat in the smoker with Alder wood chips (almost sawdust) in the bottom.
Smoke for at least 12 hours, depending on the weather, it could be done sooner.
Be sure to test it.

title: left over ham dish
directions: Cook frozen vegetables per directions on package and drain. Add ham and warm. Add cream of mushroom soup and heat until hot.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Melt the margarine in a large saucepan. Stir in brown sugar, corn syrup and salt. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Boil without stirring 5 minutes.
Remove from heat. Stir in baking soda and vanilla. Gradually pour over popped corn in 2 large shallow baking pans.
Mix well. Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 30 minutes. Remove from oven. Cool completely. Break apart and store in tightly covered container.

title: microwave sticky buns
directions: Combine brown sugar, margarine and water in glass baking dish. Microwave on Medium-high for 2 minutes, or just until butter is melted.
Mix well; spread evenly.
Sprinkle pecans in prepared dish.
Arrange biscuits over pecans.
Microwave on Medium-high for 4 to 5 minutes, or until firm.
Let stand for 2 minutes.
Invert onto serving plate.
Serve immediately.
Yields 10 servings.

title: swedish apple pie(regular and low-fat)
directions: Grease or spray a 9-inch pie pan.
Fill it 2/3 full of sliced apples (peeling is optional).
Sprinkle 1 teaspoon cinnamon and 1 teaspoon sugar over apples.
If using margarine or butter, melt it.
Combine butter or margarine or applesauce* with flour, rest of sugar, 1 egg and pinch of salt.
Add raisins, nuts or both.
It will be thick.
Spread over top of apples (does not have to cover completely).
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: quick macaroni dish
directions: Brown onion, garlic and celery in hot fat.
Add meat; brown lightly.
Add all remaining ingredients (except macaroni).
Simmer 30 to 40 minutes.
Cook macaroni and drain.
Place on platter and pour sauce over macaroni.
Use Parmesan cheese, if desired, over all.

title: heavenly sole
directions: Rinse and pat fillets dry.
Place fillets in single layer on well-greased pan with tray under it.
Brush with lemon juice and let stand 10 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Spread on top.
Broil about 4-inches from heat for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: manicotti
directions: Brown meat in garlic (fresh or powder).
Drain fat.
Mix mayo, cottage cheese and Mozzarella cheese together.
Mix in cooled meat.

title: congealed salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water.
Add cream cheese and marshmallows. Place in refrigerator until it thickens, then whip Pet milk or cream and fold into mixture.
Place back in refrigerator.
Chill until firm.
Cut in squares or put in a mold.
Turn out on lettuce.
Makes a colorful and delicious salad.

title: refrigerator cole slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in refrigerator.
Can be kept in refrigerator up to 10 days.

title: country breakfast casserole
directions: In a large skillet, cook crumbled sausage over medium heat until brown, stirring occasionally.
Remove sausage and drain on paper towel.
Spread sausage over bottom of a lightly greased 11 x 8-inch baking dish.
Cut bread into 1-inch cubes.
Set aside.

title: fudge ribbon cake
directions: Cream 2 tablespoons butter with the cream cheese, 1/4 cup sugar and cornstarch.
Add 1 egg, 2 tablespoons milk and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.
Beat at high speed of mixer until smooth and creamy.
Grease and flour bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine flour with 2 cups sugar, salt, baking powder and soda in large mixing bowl.
Add 1/2 cup butter and 1 cup milk; blend well at lowest speed of mixer.
Beat 1 1/2 minutes at low speed or 225 strokes with a spoon.
Add 1/3 cup milk, 2 eggs, Choco Bake and 1 teaspoon vanilla; continue beating 1 1/2 minutes at low speed. Spread half of batter in pan.
Spoon cheese mixture over batter, spreading carefully to cover.
Top with remaining batter; spread to cover.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes, until cake springs back when touched lightly in center.
Cool and frost.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in boiling water according to package instructions until broccoli is almost done; drain well.
Blend all ingredients except cheese crackers.
Fold in broccoli.
Spoon into buttered casserole dish.
Sprinkle with crushed cheese crackers. Bake, covered, at 400° for about 20 minutes.

title: salmon broccoli bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine rice and apples in a lightly oiled 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Place broccoli spears in a single layer over top of rice.
Spoon salmon over broccoli. Prepare Hollandaise sauce according to package directions.
Pour over salmon.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes or until heated through. Makes 4 to 6 servings.
Contains less than 300 calories per serving.

title: meat balls and corn
directions: Mix hamburger meat, brown sugar, salt, pepper, cornmeal and egg into balls and brown in a large skillet until brown.
If you wish, add corn and whole tomatoes.
Cook slowly until all liquid is cooked away.

title: pork chops
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Arrange chops in a single layer in a baking dish.
In a small bowl, mix oil, ketchup, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce and soy sauce.
Spread 1/2 of mixture over chops.
Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes.
Turn chops and spread on remaining sauce.
Bake 30 minutes more.

title: sausage and fettuccine skillet
directions: Prepare fettuccine and drain.
Melt butter in skillet. Add onions and vegetables.
Cook until tender. Set aside. Brown sausage and drain. Combine sausage, vegetables and cream.
Add cheese and parsley; simmer.
Serve over fettuccine.
Yields 6 servings.

title: cheese toast
directions: Butter bread; top with cheese.
Broil until browned or cheese melts.

title: chili eggs
directions: Cube bread and put in large skillet with at least 1 stick oleo, more if needed.
Brown bread, take out and cook your sausage until done and drain it very well.
Beat your eggs well; add green chilies, salt and pepper; mix in cooked sausage and saute bread. Add milk.
Pour into 9 x 12-inch cake pan and put grated cheese on top and let set in refrigerator overnight.
Next morning, bake 45 minutes at 325°.

title: savory eggs
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease an 8 x 8-inch baking dish. Spread cheese in dish and dot with butter.
Combine cream, salt, pepper and mustard.
Pour 1/2 mixture over cheese.
Pour in eggs. Add remaining cream mixture.
Bake 25 minutes.
May add mushrooms, ham, broccoli, bacon, etc.
Serves 6.

title: apple slices
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients like pie crust.
Put the egg yolk into a measuring cup and add enough milk to make 2/3 cup liquid. Add to dry ingredients.
Roll out half of the dough to fit a large cookie sheet.
Spread the crushed wheat or corn flakes on bottom of crust.
Spread the apple slices thin over the flakes.
Mix the sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over the apples.
Roll out the other half of the dough for top crust.
Pinch edges together firmly. Beat egg white until stiff.
Spread on top crust.
Bake 1 hour in a 400° oven.
Remove from oven and pour on glaze while hot.

title: mom's harvard beets
directions: Mix together beet juice, vinegar, sugar, salt, pepper and cornstarch.
Pour over beets and cook for 2 1/2 minutes on High in microwave.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Sprinkle rice right from the box in 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Mix soups and milk; pour over rice. Place chicken on top of rice mixture. Cover pan tightly with aluminum foil.
Bake in 350° oven for 2 hours. Don't peek a minute before the 2 hours are up.

title: apple squares
directions: Crumble together yellow cake mix and margarine.
Reserve 2/3 cup.
Press remainder in 9 x 13-inch cake pan (ungreased).
Slice apples and evenly place over mix.
Mix egg and sour cream.
Spread over apples.
To reserved cake mix add 1/4 cup brown sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over sour cream.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: tortilla and refried bean appetizer
directions: Spread chips on cookie sheet.
Top each chip with 1 teaspoon refried beans.
Sprinkle with diced chilies and Cheddar cheese. Broil until cheese is melted.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies(dookie cookies)
directions: You will also need wax paper.
Measure oats and peanut butter. Set aside.	Cut butter and place in 4 1/2-quart pot over medium low heat.
Add sugar, cocoa, milk and salt.
Raise heat to medium high and stir until well combined.
Continue to stir frequently until mixture comes to a boil, about 4 minutes.
Reduce heat to medium and boil mixture for exactly 2 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove pot from heat and stir in peanut butter and vanilla until completely incorporated.
Stir in the oats until completely mixed. Place 2 sheets of wax paper about 18-inches long on the counter. With tablespoon drop cookies onto wax paper.
Let cookies stand at room temperature until firm or if you're like me and can't wait, eat them fresh and warm!

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and flour gradually.
Cream until fluffy.
(Important to cream ingredients thoroughly.)
Add both syrups.
Beat well.
Add salt.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each egg.
Add vanilla.
Spread pecans over bottom of pie shell.
Pour mixture over pecans.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Lower heat to 325° and bake for 50 minutes or until set.
(May need to adjust oven temperature so pie does not burn.)

title: chopped apple cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten egg.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to butter mixture.
Add fruit and nuts; mix well.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar, butter, cocoa and milk slowly, beating until smooth.
Boil until soft ball forms in cold water.
Remove from fire and add vanilla and peanut butter.
Pour in buttered pan and cut into squares.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and let stand 1 hour.
Mix remaining ingredients; boil 3 minutes.
Pour over cabbage mix while hot.
Let stand until cool.
Pack in bags or container and put in freezer.

title: very basic tuna salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl and chill.
Serve on sandwiches or stuffed tomatoes.

title: crab dip
directions: Melt cheese over low heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and blend in the rest of the ingredients.

title: easy cheesy potatoes
directions: Saute onions in oil until tender.
Stir in undiluted soup and cream cheese.
Stir until hot and creamy.
In 1-quart casserole, make layers of potatoes, soup mixture and Cheddar cheese, ending with Cheddar cheese.
Cover and bake at 400° for 45 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Discard all imperfect kernels and put popcorn in large pan. Cook sugar, syrup and water to the medium crack stage (280°).
Add flavoring and salt.
Pour over the corn, stirring with a spoon, so that all kernels will be evenly coated.

title: casserole italiana
directions: Put into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
After 20 minutes place cheese around edge of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or more.
If seems dry, add tomato juice.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt margarine; mix with dressing.
Put all but 1 cup of dressing in bottom of an 8 x 11-inch baking dish.
Mix the squash, carrots, soup, onion, pimento and sour cream; pour over dressing. Top casserole with reserved dressing.
Bake at 350° until casserole is hot and bubbly.
Will serve 10 to 12.

title: pink slush
directions: Soften sherbet; pour ingredients together in punch bowl.
Mix and serve.

title: roulade of beef
directions: Dice onion.
Salt and pepper the steaks.
Add rosemary and sprinkle half the diced onion on steaks along with half of dill pickle, cut in 4 long slices.
Roll steaks, using toothpicks to hold them together.
Heat 2 tablespoons shortening in skillet and brown steaks on both sides.
Remove steaks and place in casserole.

title: pineapple cole slaw
directions: Combine cabbage, marshmallows, apples, pineapple, celery and enough salad dressing to moisten.
Toss lightly.

title: holiday carrots
directions: Cook carrots until tender and drain.
Mix soup, oil, and sugar.
Slice peppers and onions and add to soup mixture.
Pour over carrots.
Cover and let marinate over night.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serves 8-10.

title: herbed tomatoes
directions: Cut tomatoes in half.
Brush cut sides generously with dressing.
Combine green onion, parsley and herbs.
Place tomato halves cut side up on grill rack.
Grill 6 to 8 minutes without turning.
Sprinkle with onion mixture halfway through cooking. Yield:
4 servings.

title: bean and bacon chowder
directions: Cook bacon and onion in a saucepan until bacon is lightly browned and onion is tender.
Blend in flour.
Add milk.
Cook and stir until bubbly.
Dice potatoes.
Add with thyme, 1 teaspoon of salt and 1/8 teaspoon of pepper.
Cover and simmer 12 to 15 minutes or until potatoes are done.
Stir in beans and heat completely. Top with your parsley.

title: pecan nut roll
directions: Mix two cups pecans with all other ingredients.
Roll and make into a log.
Roll log in the remaining 1 cup pecans.

title: raspberry almond coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread almonds in a single layer on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 5 to 7 minutes or until light golden brown.
Do not burn.
Allow almonds to cool; chop and set aside.

title: carrot ring
directions: Lightly oil 6-cup mold.
Mix ingredients and pour into mold. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Unmold on platter.

title: oyster crackers
directions: Mix spices, salad dressing and oil together.
Pour over crackers on baking sheet.
Bake at 275° for 15 to 20 minutes. Stir every few minutes.

title: marie's cordon bleu casserole
directions: In a large pan, melt butter over low heat (do not brown). Stir in mushroom soup/water mixture and mushrooms; heat until very warm.
Stir in gently the sour cream and heat (do not boil).
Stir in rice, ham and chicken.
Simmer gently.
(If mixture seems too thick, add water.)
Add cheese; combine all and heat until cheese melts.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Sprinkle with parsley for decoration.
Dot with butter and thin with water to reheat leftovers in microwave.

title: pig out soup
directions: Boil equal
amounts
of
all
vegetables
in V-8 juice. Boil in	V-8 juice until tender.
Choose thick, chunky soup or thin soup by
the amount of V-8 juice you use.
No calories to worry about so pig out!

title: fried chicken("low-fat")
directions: Roll chicken in bowl of crushed corn flakes, mixed with spices.
Place on foil lined pan and bake at 350° until tender. This really tastes like fried chicken!

title: roast marinade
directions: Mix and pour over chuck roast.
Marinate 3 to 4 hours or longer.
Turn every half hour.
Grill 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Can put tenderizer on meat before marinating, if desired.

title: fresh fruit salad
directions: Drain each can of fruit separately, reserving 2/3 cup pineapple juice, 1/2 cup orange juice and 1/3 cup peach juice. Mix juices and pudding into a heavy sauce.
Cook over a medium heat, stirring constantly.
Bring mixture to a boil and cook until it is clear.
Cool.
Mix canned fruit with sauce.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Just before serving, add bananas, grapes and strawberries.

title: best ever banana bread
directions: In a large bowl, stir together flour, sugar, baking soda and salt.
In another mixing bowl, combine eggs, bananas, oil, buttermilk and vanilla; add to flour mixture, stirring just until combined.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch baking pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until bread tests done.
Cool on wire rack.
Yield: 1 loaf.

title: chiffon bars
directions: Put everything together except nuts and chips; mix well.
Add half of the nuts and chips.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle remaining nuts and chips on top of cake. Bake 25 to 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: cranberry-apple casserole
directions: Mix together until well blended and put in casserole dish.

title: tomato sauce
directions: Cook together until vegetables are tender. Simmer.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add beaten egg yolks and a little milk to make a thin paste.
Then add rest of milk.
Cook until thickens.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and butter.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Grease well an 11 x 15 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle coconut and chopped nuts in bottom of pan.
Mix cake mix according to directions on package and pour over nuts and coconut.
Mix cream cheese and margarine; cream well and add powdered sugar and blend. Drop by teaspoon on top of batter in pan.
Do not spread.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: popcorn balls mix
directions: Melt margarine. Add marshmallows. Stir until melted. Add dry gelatin. Mix and pour over popcorn.

title: easy potato casserole
directions: Let potatoes thaw completely and drain.
Mix everything together in a casserole baking dish, heavily coated with butter. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: kahala hilton's pineapple macadamia nutbread
directions: In a large mixing bowl cream butter and sugar together until smooth.
Beat together eggs and milk and add to butter mixture. Blend well, then add flour and baking powder and mix lightly. Stir in corn syrup and vanilla.
Add pineapple, macaroons and macadamia nuts.
Blend well and pour into greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour and 40 minutes or until center tests done.

title: sausage balls
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Lightly grease cookie sheet.
Mix all ingredients and knead for 1 minute. Shape into 1 1/2-inch balls. Bake 25 to 30 minutes; drain.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: sad cake
directions: Mix
all ingredients together and pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: hot orange cider(130 calories per serving)
directions: Mix all ingredients in an eight-cup measure or a 2-cup casserole.
Cover tightly and microwave on High 6 to 9 minutes or until hot.
Stir.
Stir in 2 tablespoons brandy, if desired.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
In large bowl, sift flour with sugar, baking powder, salt and soda. Cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add eggs and bananas.
Use an electric mixer on low speed and beat for 2 minutes.
Add nuts, candied fruit and raisins.
Beat until well blended.
Turn into prepared pan.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes or until knife inserted in the middle comes out clean.
Let cool in pan on wire rack 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Let cool; store overnight before serving.

title: yellow pound cake
directions: Mix well.
Bake in a tube pan for 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: ham salad
directions: In a small bowl, add all ingredients. Stir to blend.

title: kay's roll recipe
directions: Melt margarine and mix yeast and water. Place melted margarine and sugar in a bowl. Mix, then add egg. Combine with yeast and water. Add flour and mix well. Put in container with tight lid. Refrigerate overnight. Put spoonful of dough in well-greased muffin tins. Bake at 450° for 20 minutes.

title: pineapple brownies
directions: Mix butter/margarine, sugar, eggs, vanilla, flour, baking powder and salt together.
Divide batter in half.
Add melted chocolate to half of batter.
Add pineapple chunks to the other half.
Put dark part on bottom and light on top in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken taquitos
directions: Heat oil and brown flour; add tomato sauce and mix well. Add chicken and stir until hot; reduce heat to low. Wrap 6 tortillas in paper towel and warm in microwave (about 60 seconds) until soft (be sure to pull each tortilla apart first then re-stack before warming). Spoon mixture onto tortillas (about 1 teaspoon) and roll into taquitos form. Fry tortillas over medium-high heat until golden brown. Serve with guacamole. Makes about 2 dozen.

title: orange juice cake
directions: Grease Bundt pan and evenly spread with chopped pecans.

title: fried onions
directions: Place butter and sliced onions in frying pan.
Stir and fry. When golden color, add 1/4 cup of water and cover.
Cook until tender.
May drain liquid before serving.

title: grated sweet potato pudding
directions: Grate raw sweet potatoes in milk to keep them from turning dark.
Add other ingredients in the order given.
Pour into well-greased 1 1/2-quart casserole. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serve warm.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: pretzel jello
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix pretzels, 3 tablespoons sugar and margarine.
Pat into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 7 to 8 minutes until toasty. Set aside to cool.

title: french chocolate pie
directions: Melt first 3 ingredients in top of double boiler.
Remove from heat and cool 2 minutes.
Add egg yolks and mix.
Whip egg whites until stiff.
Fold into chocolate mix (gently) leaving some white. Pour into pie shells.
Top with Cool Whip and chill until firm. (You won't taste the raw egg.)

title: dutch oven dinner
directions: Cut steak into 6 individual servings.
Rub with salt and pepper.
Dredge with flour.
Pound slightly as for Swiss steak. On each piece of meat, place a small carrot, cut into quarters, slice onion and celery.
Wrap steak around vegetables.
Fasten with toothpick.
Brown on all sides in bacon fat.
Add the halved potatoes and 3/4 cup water.
Cover and when boiling, turn to simmer for 1 hour.
Remove to heated platter.
Thicken the drippings with flour blended with 2 tablespoons water.
Serve over each portion.
Serves 6.

title: nora's homemade tomato soup
directions: Bring tomatoes, water, salt and pepper to a boil in a large pot.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 to 10 minutes; then remove from heat and add baking soda, stirring constantly.
(It will overflow if you are not careful.)
After bubbling stops, return to low heat and add the margarine.
Stir well.
When melted and smooth, it is ready to eat.
(Good with oyster crackers or saltines.)

title: rhubarb cream pie
directions: Place rhubarb in a pastry lined pan.
Blend sugar, flour and butter.
Add beaten eggs.
Beat until smooth.
Pour over rhubarb. Top with pastry, cut in fancy shapes.
Bake in a hot 450° oven for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° and bake until firm.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Mix together using enough Miracle Whip to hold together. Serve on bed of lettuce.

title: spanish cream
directions: Soak gelatin in cool milk for 5 minutes.
Place over hot water.
When
gelatin is dissolved, add the sugar.
Pour slowly over
beaten egg yolks and cook on low heat, stirring constantly, until
custard coats the spoon.
Remove from the heat; add flavoring.
Fold
in
the stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into mold and chill.

title: new ranch dip
directions: Mix ingredients; refrigerate.
Serve with vegetable dippers or crackers.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups.

title: christmas stollen
directions: Scald milk.
Add sugar, salt and butter; cool to lukewarm. Mix yeast with 1 tablespoon sugar; add to lukewarm milk.
Stir. Add eggs.
Add 3 cups of flour; beat well.
Add the cardamom, raisins and citron.
Add rest of flour until smooth and satiny. Place in warm place for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Divide dough into 1/3 for each Stollen.
Roll each part to an 8 x 10-inch oval.
Press center; fold over.
Let rise 45 minutes, until doubled.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: texas size chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and shortening; add sugars, eggs, corn syrup and vanilla.
Beat well.
Combine dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Stir in chips.
Line 2 pizza pans with foil. Spread batter in two pans.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 17 minutes or until light brown.
Remove pans from oven and let cookies cool in pan. When cool, turn out, peel off foil and place on plate and decorate.

title: strawberry squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together cake mix, eggs and oil until stiff.
Spread the dough evenly in a lightly greased 9x13-inch pan.
Bake 14 to 16 minutes.
Mix the milk and powdered sugar.
Drizzle the glaze over the squares.
Serve warm or at room temperature.

title: best oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat together the margarine and sugars until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Combine flour, baking soda, salt and spices.
Add to margarine mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in oats.
Drop by rounded tablespoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 9 minutes for a chewy cookie or 10 to 11 minutes for a crisp cookie.
Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet. Remove to wire rack.
Store in tightly covered container.
Makes 4 1/2 dozen.

title: mystery cake(fat mans delight)
directions: Crush graham crackers.
Add melted oleo and 1/4 cup of sugar. Bake at 350° for 7 minutes.
Let cool.

title: apple crisp
directions: Butter a baking dish and fill with apples, water and cinnamon mixed.
Work together remaining ingredients with fingertips until crumbly.
Spread over the apple mixture and bake uncovered in a 400° oven for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.
Serve with whipped cream, milk or ice cream.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut steak into thin strips; dust with flour and pepper.
In large skillet, brown meat in butter or margarine.
Add mushrooms, onion and garlic and brown lightly.
Stir in beef broth; cover and cook about 1 hour or until meat is tender.
Stir now and then. Gradually stir in sour cream; cook over low heat 5 minutes.
Serve over 3 cups cooked noodles.
Serves 4.

title: frozen cucumbers
directions: Mix cucumbers, onion and salt and let stand in refrigerator for 2 hours; drain but do not rinse.
Let stand in drainer 10 to 15 minutes.

title: hot sauce(salsa)
directions: If you like chunky salsa, chop up peppers, onion and cilantro, and combine all ingredients.
Let stand in refrigerator for 1 hour before serving.
If you like smooth salsa, place ingredients in a blender or food processor; process until pureed.
You control how hot the sauce is by the amount of peppers.
The sauce will keep in the refrigerator for approximately 2 weeks.

title: harvey wallbanger cake
directions: Mix and beat for 2 minutes.
Pour into greased Bundt pan. Bake 45 to 55 minutes at 350°.

title: pasta with gorgonzola sauce a la luana
directions: Melt butter in double boiler over low heat.
Add cheese and stir until melted and well blended.
Add nutmeg and pepper.
Pour over cooked pasta.
Serves 4 to 6 as a main course and 6 to 8 as a first course.

title: king ranch casseroles
directions: Mix together meat, tomatoes, soup and beans in a bowl.
Spread chips in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Add meat mixture to chips and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: lemon cheese frosting
directions: Add
sugar
and eggs together thoroughly.
Put in lemon juice and rind and cook over low heat until thickens.
Remove from heat and add butter.
Will frost 2 layers.

title: mama's macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain.
Cut cheese into 1-inch squares.
Beat eggs.
Mix all ingredients. Pour into a 12 x 12-inch bake dish.
Bake for 30 minutes at 400°.

title: russian pork chops
directions: Combine the dressing, onion and bell pepper.
Let marinate for 2 hours. Pour over pork chops.
Let bake for 45 minutes to an hour.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Beat together shortening, butter and sugar about 5 minutes. Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla and lemon juice.
Mix dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Stir in chips and nuts.
Drop large tablespoonfuls of dough 3 inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 16 to 18 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.

title: potluck casserole
directions: Defrost potatoes.
Combine in large mixing bowl all ingredients.
Pour into large greased casserole dish.
Cover with corn flake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Can be mixed night before, put in refrigerator and add corn flake mixture before baking.

title: cabbage meatballs
directions: Mix first four ingredients together.
Make meatballs. Put into skillet; add tomato soup and water.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours or until done.
Serves 4.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Flour and fry pork chops.
Debone and cut in half.
Grease pan and leave a little standing.
Cover bottom of pan with pork chops. Slice some onion and green pepper and spread over pork chops. Put rice over that.
Pour tomatoes over that.
Add salt for rice. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: taco pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pat rolls on bottom and sides of an 8-inch casserole; sprinkle with half of Fritos.
Cook together hamburger, onion and green pepper; drain.
Add taco seasoning mix and water; simmer until dry.
Pour mixture over Fritos.
Spread sour cream on top of meat mixture; sprinkle grated cheese, then remaining Fritos.
Bake for 20 minutes or until rolls are brown.

title: chicken stroganoff
directions: Boil chicken breasts until tender.
Simmer green peppers and sliced onion in oleo until soft.
Cook noodles and mix with cream of chicken soup and sour cream.

title: broccoli cauliflower soup
directions: In large saucepan, stirring occasionally, cook vegetables and garlic in margarine about 10 minutes or until tender.
Stir in flour, salt, nutmeg and pepper.
Stir in broth.
Cover and stirring occasionally, cook over low heat for about 15 minutes or until thickened.
Remove from heat.
Set aside 1 cup soup.
Puree remaining soup in blender.
Return to saucepan.
Stir in milk and lemon juice.
Cook on medium heat, stirring occasionally, 5 minutes.
Add reserved soup; cook until heated through.
Serves 4. Low-fat and low calorie.

title: texas brownies
directions: Make brownies according to package directions.
While brownies bake, prepare the frosting.

title: strawberry tea loaf
directions: Thaw strawberries.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
In a small bowl, combine dry ingredients and set aside.
In a large bowl, beat eggs and oil.
Add strawberries and continue beating until strawberries are in small pieces.
Add flour mixture and blend well.
Pour into loaf pan and bake one hour.

title: apple, walnut and coconut crisp
directions: Peel, core and cut apples into 1/3-inch slices.
In a large bowl, toss apples with lemon juice.
Layer drained apples in a well-greased 9-inch square baking pan.

title: no bake chocolate cookies
directions: Mix together in large saucepan the sugar, milk and margarine. Heat on high. Hard boil exactly 1 minute. Remove from heat and in the same saucepan, add peanut butter, oats, cocoa and vanilla. Do not let cool off. Spoon immediately onto wax paper and let cool. Eat and enjoy!!!!!

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix ingredients.
Shape into balls the size of a walnut and pat it lightly with a fork.
Bake in a moderate oven (350°) for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: earthquake cake(it looks awful but tastes so good i'm sure it's sinful.)
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Mix coconut and pecans and spread on bottom of pan.
Mix the German chocolate cake according to directions and pour over coconut-pecan mixture.
Mix together cream cheese, butter or oleo, powdered sugar and nuts and spread over top.
This will fill the pan awful full when it bakes, so put a cookie sheet or something under cake pan to catch spillage (if you are fussy about your oven).
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: islander barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Brush frequently over ribs or chicken while baking or grilling.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all but
the last two ingredients in large mixing bowl. Then put into buttered casserole dish.
Crumble Ritz crackers and put in bowl of melted margarine. Put on top of casserole. Bake 45 minutes in 325 degree oven or until brown.

title: fresh blueberry cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat until fluffy.
Add vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Reserve one cup flour mixture.
Add remaining flour to batter; beat well.
Dredge berries in reserved flour.
Fold gently into batter.
Spoon into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 1 1/4 hours.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Wash and pound, with a kitchen mallet, the chicken breasts until nice and flat.
Place on one chicken breast, 1 slice of ham and 1 slice of Swiss cheese.
Roll and hold together with a toothpick.
Dip in egg and roll in bread crumb mix.
Fry in skillet until done on medium heat.

title: beef rouladen
directions: Cut round steak into 4 x 6-inch rectangles.
Season with salt and pepper.
Spread with mustard.
Sprinkle with chopped onion. Add strip of pickle and roll up.
Fasten with toothpicks.
Brown in hot oil.
Add mushrooms, wine and broth.
Cover and cook slowly 1 1/4 hours.
Add water, if necessary, to prevent burning.
Remove toothpicks.
Transport to ovenproof serving dish.
Thicken broth with 2 tablespoons cornstarch and 2 tablespoons cold water.
Pour over meat.
Heat.
Can be served with Duchess potatoes.

title: marshmallow squares
directions: Melt margarine in large saucepan over low heat.
Add marshmallows and stir until completely melted.
Remove from heat. Add Rice Krispies; stir until well coated.
Using buttered spatula or waxed paper, press mixture evenly into a 13 x 9-inch pan or dish coated with cooking spray.
Cut into squares when cool. Yields 24 (2 x 2-inch) squares.

title: sweet potato surprise
directions: Whip cooked potatoes until creamy and combine all ingredients. Put into baking dish.

title: chocolate one bowl brownie recipe
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Microwave chocolate and margarine in large bowl at High for 2 minutes, or until margarine is melted.
Stir until chocolate is completely melted.
Stir sugar into chocolate. Mix in egg and vanilla until well blended.
Stir in flour and nuts.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan; bake for 30 to 35 minutes, or until toothpick inserted in middle comes out with fudgy crumbs.
Cool in pan; cut into squares.
Makes 24 fudgy brownies.

title: cinnamon ornaments
directions: No baking and simple for kids!
Combine the cinnamon and applesauce.
Roll out dough to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut with cookie cutters.
Make hole for ribbon.
Carefully place on wire rack to dry.
Let air dry several days, turning over occasionally. Makes 12 sweet smelling ornaments.

title: venison loin with a spanish twist
directions: You will need 1 (12-inch) cast-iron skillet.
This recipe is good with any type of meat (beef, pork, chicken, etc.).

title: chocolate snickerdoodles
directions: Sift first 5 ingredients. Cream oleo. Add sugar and vanilla. Add eggs, one at a time, mixing until light and fluffy. Add dry ingredients. Mix well. Roll dough into balls and roll in sugar. Put on an ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: banana ice cream
directions: Crumble vanilla wafers into ice cream freezer.
Add sugar, vanilla and condensed milk.
Mash bananas well; add to mixture. Finish filling freezer to fill line with milk.
Freeze.
(For large freezer.)

title: marinade for zesty grilled pork chops
directions: Combine first five ingredients.
Place chops in a glass baking dish and pour marinade over.
Cover and refrigerate.
To cook, remove from marinade and grill.
(Use no salt on your meat.)

title: cinnamon candy jelly
directions: Wash and sterilize canning jars and lids.
In a large, heavy saucepan, combine juice and sugar; stir well with a metal spoon. Add margarine and candies.
Bring to a rolling boil over high heat, stirring constantly.
Stir in liquid pectin.
Return to the rolling boil, stirring constantly, and boil for 1 minute.
Remove from the heat; skim off foam.
Fill the jars to within 1/4 inch of top.
Wipe the jar rims and seal jars.
Turn jars upside-down for 5 minutes, then turn right-side up.

title: buttermilk cinnamon bars
directions: Combine flour and sugars.
Cut in butter.
Combine 2 cups of crumb mixture with walnuts and coconut.
Press nut mixture in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine egg, baking soda, salt, cinnamon, buttermilk and vanilla in another bowl.
Beat until smooth, using an electric mixer.
Stir egg mixture into remaining crumb mixture, mixing just until moistened.
Spread over crumb-nut layer.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes or until golden.
Cool 10 minutes.
Frost with icing.
Cut into bars.
Makes 32 bars.

title: sock it to me cake
directions: Combine together 3 tablespoons white sugar and cinnamon.
Pour 1/3 batter into greased and floured tube pan and sprinkle with 1/2 sugar and cinnamon over it.
Pour another 1/3 of batter over this and sprinkle remainder of cinnamon and sugar mixture over it.
Top with final 1/3 of cake batter.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°. While cake is still warm, ice with the following:

title: luscious peach pie
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; beat until smooth.
Fold in whipped cream and gently stir in peaches.
Pour into pie crust. Chill well until it sets.

title: easy taco salad
directions: Mix ingredients and enjoy!

title: cheese ball with chipped beef
directions: Mix all together; put in dish to use as a spread.

title: apple crisp
directions: Butter baking dish.
Measure sugar, salt and flour into bowl; stir well.
Add butter to dry mixture until you have crumbs. Slice the apples and put in baking dish.
Sprinkle the lemon juice, then cinnamon over apples.
Spread the flour mixture over apples.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: deep south cookies
directions: Stir all ingredients in bowl until blended.
Drop on greased cookie sheet and bake in moderate oven for 15 minutes.
Makes 18 cookies.

title: italian spaghetti
directions: Cook and stir meat, onion and pepper until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except spaghetti. Cover; simmer for 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Serves 8.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients in order listed.
Pour into ungreased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Sprinkle cake mix over filling; pour melted butter over top.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until knife comes out clean when inserted halfway from center.
Serve warm or cold, plain or with whipped topping.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook chicken breasts (boil). Cook broccoli. Mix soup, sour cream, mayonnaise, grated cheese and seasonings. Drain broccoli and arrange in bottom of a flat, greased 3-quart casserole. Sprinkle generously with Parmesan cheese.

title: tropical fruit pie
directions: Mix all ingredients except pineapple and bananas.
Bring to a full boil.
Cool.
Add pineapple.
Slice 2 bananas into each crust.
Pour mixture over and refrigerate.
Serve with or without Cool Whip.

title: kula pig
directions: Bake pork roast at 350° until done.
Add small amount of water.
Shred pork.
Pour rock salt all over pork.
Cover and put back in oven until done.
Serve with rice or potatoes.

title: caramel pie
directions: Boil two cans of milk in a large pan of water; keep the milk covered with water at all times.
Boil for 2 hours on low heat. Remove cans from water.
Do not open cans until they are cool. Pour into pie crust.
Cover with Cool Whip.

title: dutch scalloped potatoes
directions: Heat milk in large saucepan; add potatoes and seasonings. Cook about 20 minutes, stirring often.
Layer in greased baking dish with shredded cheese.
Pour cream over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: party chicken
directions: Wrap each piece of chicken in strip of bacon.
Place beef in baking dish.
Place chicken on top.
Mix soup and sour cream and pour over top of chicken.
Cover and refrigerate for 3 hours. Bake, uncovered, at 275° for 3 hours.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix and place on top of cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: taco hot dish
directions: Press crescent rolls onto bottom of pan.
Crush 2/3 of chips and sprinkle over top.
Brown hamburger and drain.
Add seasoning and sauce.
Pour meat mixture over crust.
Spread sour cream over meat mixture and top with cheese.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 375°.
Serve with topping of shredded lettuce, chopped tomato, black olives, salsa, etc.
(Good with corn meal bread stixs.)

title: sweet potato casserole with sausage
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish and set aside.
Peel and cut up sweet potatoes; cook in boiling water until soft.
Strips casings off of sausage and discard.
Crumble sausage into a frying pan and saute until done.
Drain, reserving some drippings.
Saute mushrooms and onion in 2 tablespoons of drippings.
Cut apples into thin slices about the size of potato chips; set aside.
When sweet potatoes are cooked, mash them and add butter, salt and pepper.

title: spanish delight
directions: Chop green pepper and onion.
Brown hamburger, pepper and onion.
Drain grease.
Mix with tomato sauce, drained corn and chili seasoning.
Cook egg noodles until tender.
Pour hamburger sauce and noodles into 9 x 12-inch oblong pan and mix well.
Add cream of mushroom soup and mix.
Layer American cheese over top and heat in oven until melted.

title: salsa dip
directions: Chop and mix together.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: apple pancakes
directions: Mix together eggs, sugar, cinnamon, sour cream and salt.
Add flour and baking powder.
Slowly add water and chopped apples. Fry in oil on low heat.

title: b.l.t. soup
directions: Mix the water and ham base in gallon pitcher. Cook the bacon until crisp. Remove and drain on paper towel. Pour all drippings into pot. Saute the celery, onions and bell peppers in bacon drippings. Cook about 5 minutes. Add the garlic and cook 3 minutes. Add the cumin. Add the tomatoes and parsley and simmer until mixture is dry. Mix in the sugar, salt and cayenne pepper. Add reserved ham base liquid and bring to a boil. Add the oregano, black pepper and lettuce. Cook 5 minutes. Garnish with crumbled bacon.

title: enchilada verde(low-fat)
directions: Dip tortillas in green enchilada sauce.
(Sometimes warming the sauce and allowing the corn tortillas to be at room temperature helps keep them from breaking when rolled.)
Mix diced onion, picante sauce and beans (the kind without lard).
Place 1 tablespoon mixture in tortilla and 1 tablespoon shredded cheese. This is easier the second time you do it and remember Jesus loves you.
Cover tightly with aluminum foil and bake in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
Remove cover; add any sauce and shredded cheese. Garnish with optional ingredients.

title: banana cheese cream pie
directions: Line pie shell with 2 sliced bananas.
Whip softened cream cheese.
Beat in Eagle Brand milk.
Add lemon juice and vanilla. Blend well.
Pour into crust.
Chill for at least 2 hours or overnight.
Slice 3rd banana over pie.
Cover with Cool Whip. Must keep refrigerated.

title: monkey bread
directions: Prepare roll mix as directed.
Cut dough into pieces and dip in butter.
Place in Bundt pan and bake as directed.

title: chicken with broccoli
directions: Cook rice.
Cut up chicken into bite size pieces.
Stir-fry the chicken and onion in the olive oil.
Lower the heat.
Add broccoli and cover, stirring occasionally.
After the broccoli is cooked, add the soy sauce (approximately 1 tablespoon).
Mix rice with the chicken and broccoli mixture.
Ready to serve.

title: black forest cake
directions: Prepare and bake cake mix according to package directions. Bake in 2 9 inch cake pans.
Cool on wire rack.
Spread first layer with half of the pie filling and 1/4 of the whipped topping. Spread remainder of pie filling on top layer.
Frost the cake completely with remainder of whipped topping.
Garnish with chocolate curls.

title: dieter's cake
directions: Mix and bake cake in 9 x 13-inch pan as directed on box. Combine sugar and pineapple; bring to boil. Boil 5 minutes. Pour while hot over hot cake. Chill cake. Slice bananas and layer over cake. Make pudding as directed on box, using 2 1/2 cups milk. Spread over bananas. Chill. Sprinkle pecans over pudding. Cover with coconut. Chill.

title: kaye's mom's chili
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add beans and cut up onions.
Add tomatoes and bell pepper.
Add all the spices and stir.
Cook in crock-pot on low all day!

title: dach(german pancakes)
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Spread batter thinly on a griddle and cook; turn when edges curl.
Serve with fried potatoes and onions.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 (9 x 5-inch) pans.
In medium bowl, mix berries, eggs and oil.
In large bowl, combine flour, sugar, cinnamon, baking soda, salt and nuts.
Then add dry ingredients to strawberry mixture. Stir and blend.
Pour into pan and bake 60 minutes or until smooth and pick comes out clean.

title: shrimp chowder
directions: Lightly cook onions in butter.
Add potatoes and boiling water.
Simmer until potatoes are tender and season to taste. Melt cheese in milk and add to potatoes and onions.
Add shrimp and simmer gently for 20 minutes or more.
Do not boil!
Top with fresh snipped parsley.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add oregano, garlic and salt; simmer 3 to 5 minutes.
Stir in spaghetti sauce and tomato paste.
Cook, stirring occasionally, for 10 to 15 minutes.
Combine eggs, cottage cheese, Parmesan cheese and parsley; blend well.
Boil lasagna in large amount of water for about 10 minutes, stirring with wooden spoon.
Drain well.

title: chicken and broccoli alfredo
directions: Prepare fettucine or spaghetti according to package directions.
Add broccoli for last 4 minutes of cooking time.
In skillet over medium-high heat, heat butter.
Add chicken and cook until browned.
Add soup, milk, cheese, pepper and fettucine mixture and cook through, stirring often.
Serves 4.

title: mom's rhubarb custard pie
directions: Line a deep pie pan with pastry.
Place rhubarb in unbaked crust.
Mix rest of ingredients to make a custard and pour over rhubarb.
Butter may be dotted on top of pie rather than put into the custard.
Bake at 400° until crust is set and reduce heat to 350° and bake until thick and rhubarb is tender.

title: no bake quick stack cake
directions: Put layer of graham crackers in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch sheet pan.
Spread a thin layer of applesauce over crackers.
Repeat layers until you run out of ingredients.
End with crackers on top.
Let set overnight.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together. Cream shortening and sugar 10 minutes. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition. Add flour mixture alternating with milk, beating after each addition. Add coconut and flavoring. Mix at low speed of mixer. Put in a large greased and floured tube pan. Put in cold oven. Bake 1 hour and 25 minutes at 350° or until done.

title: "country apple tart"
directions: Preheat the oven to 450°.
Grate 1 teaspoon of lemon peel and squeeze 2 teaspoons of juice from the lemon.
Set aside.
Toss the apples with the sugar, flour, cinnamon, lemon peel and juice. Place the pie crust on a rimless baking sheet lightly dusted with flour.
Dust a rolling pin with flour and roll the pastry to a rough 13-inch circle.
Heap the apples on the pastry, leaving a 2-inch border all around.
Scatter the butter on the fruit.
Fold the pastry border back over the apples to make an uneven rustic edge of about 1 1/2 inches, leaving the slices in the center exposed.
Sprinkle the reserved sugar over the pastry border.
Bake 12 minutes then reduce the temperature to 425° and bake until the apples are softened and bubbly and the pastry is golden brown (12 to 15 minutes).
Serve warm.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: french apple pie
directions: Prepare pie crust, according to directions on package for 1 crust pie.

title: snappy golden cream of potato soup
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in large pot. Bring to boil. Reduce heat and simmer, covered, 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Use potato masher to mash potatoes to small lumps. Add potatoes, both soups and milk. Blend well. Cook over medium heat 10 minutes. Add more milk if too thick.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli with margarine and onion until the broccoli is thawed and hot.
Combine cooked broccoli with rice;
add Cheez Whiz and then mushroom soup.
Mix together well.
Pour into a greased pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, uncovered. Enjoy!

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Stir all together and place in a buttered casserole.
Top with slivered almonds.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: diabetic individual pizzas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown meat, add salt.
Split English muffins and spread with margarine.
Place on baking sheet.
Spread pizza sauce on muffins, then add meat.
Put onion, pepper and mushrooms on top of this.
Cover with cheese.
Heat about 15 minutes, until cheese melts and muffins begin to brown.

title: baked beans
directions: In large baking casserole, place beans, onion, sugar, ketchup and green pepper.
Mix well.
Break up raw hamburger and mix in with beans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lo-cal sour cream
directions: Place all ingredients in blender; cover.
Blend for 10 seconds or until smooth.
Makes 1 cup.
Use any way you would sour cream. Soft curd cottage cheese seems to work best; it gets smoother.

title: strawberry jam cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter and egg yolks together. Add milk, jam, raisins and floured nuts (use 1 cup flour).
Then sift remaining 3 cups flour and the rest of the dry ingredients.
Add to the egg yolk mixture.
Bake in 4 well-greased 9-inch cake pans. Bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes. Spread with strawberry jam cake filling.

title: apple torte
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to butter, eggs and sugar.
Add raw apples and mix well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve plain or top with ice cream.

title: strawberry-pecan cake
directions: Mix jello and cake mix together dry.
Mix cake as any other cake.
Bake at 350°.
Bake in 3 layers for 25 to 35 minutes.
Cool before adding filling.

title: apricot bread
directions: Cream together brown sugar, sugar, and softened margarine. Then add to mixture, eggs, vanilla, apricot preserves. Sift together flour, baking soda, salt, baking powder, and cinnamon. Then blend dry ingredient mixture with creamed mixture. Finally stir in chopped nuts.
Bake in 325° oven for 45 minutes. Makes 2 loaves.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Mix and store in a glass jar.
Use on your favorite salad.

title: cocktail franks
directions: Melt jelly with mustard and horseradish.
Add hot dogs and heat until warm in an electric skillet.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Saute onion in margarine.
Mix all ingredients together.
Place in baking dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add next 4 ingredients.
Bring to a boil. Cook 10 minutes.
Cook noodles.
Place half in baking dish.
Cover with 1/2 sauce; add 1/2 Mozzarella and 1/2 Ricotta.
Repeat layers, ending with noodles.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken rub
directions: Mix. Store airtight. Makes 1/3 cup of mix. Use 1 tablespoon of rub per pound of chicken. Great on grill or in the oven.

title: clam and crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients, then set aside for several hours or overnight.
Serve as dip or spread on cocktail round.
Broil until bubbly and serve hot.
Make a lot, they go fast.

title: neva's old fashioned teacakes
directions: Cream butter. Gradually add sugar, beating well with mixer. Add egg and vanilla. Beat well. Combine flour, soda and pinch of salt. Add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk. Mix well. Add remaining 1/4 cup flour

if dough seems sticky. Cover and chill 8 hours (or less). Roll dough to 1/4-inch thickness on lightly floured surface. Cut with 3-inch round cutter. Place on lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes. Makes about 2 dozen.

title: fettucine alfredo with shrimp
directions: Cook fettucine according to package directions, omitting salt. Drain well.
Place in a large bowl.
Combine butter and whipping cream in a small saucepan.
Cook over low heat until butter melts. Stir in cheese, pepper and parsley.
Stir in boiled shrimp.
Pour mixture over hot fettucine; toss until fettucine is coated.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Place in saucepan on low heat.
Bring to slight boil and baste meat.

title: swiss steak
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Coat the steak and fry until brown.
Mix sauce, brown sugar, molasses, Worcestershire sauce and salt.
Pour over meat, arranging mushrooms and onion over meat.
Roast until done, about 1 1/2 hours.

title: brownies
directions: Stir eggs and sugar together.
Stir chocolate and oil together.
Add vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients and nuts into mixture.
Spread into greased 8-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until done.
