title: eye of round roast
directions: This is probably not the way to make them at the West Indian Bakery in Hartford, Connecticut, but it's pretty good, anyway.

title: tossed salad
directions: Top with 8 slices bacon, crumbled.

title: bread pudding
directions: Tear rolls into small pieces and soak in milk for approximately 30 minutes.
Beat eggs and fold into rolls and milk. Melt butter in a 9 x 12-inch glass baking dish.
Pour in bread mixture.
Add sugar, nutmeg and vanilla.
Mix in pineapple or raisins.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes or until firm.
Serve warm or cold.
Serves 12.

title: coffee cake
directions: Take 1/3 of the cake mix and blend with brown sugar, butter and nuts (set streusel aside).
Beat eggs slightly, then add sour cream and remaining cake mix (this will be slightly lumpy).
Grease and flour two 8-inch round cake pans.
Put about 1/4 of cake mixture (egg-sour cream mixture) in each pan.
Sprinkle 1/4 Streusel over the mix in the pans.
Put another layer of egg-sour cream mixture in each pan, then top with remaining Streusel.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until done (use toothpick to see when cake is done).
Let cake cool, then cut into pieces and serve.

title: red beet chocolate cake
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until light.
Add oil, beets, melted chocolate and vanilla.
Beat on low speed.
Sift flour, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.

title: shrimp dip sauce
directions: Mix well.
Can be used for shrimp, crab
or
as a salad dressing.

title: island of strawberry cake
directions: For cake, preparation time is 15 minutes. It is ready in 1:40 hours. Heat oven to 350°. Grease and flour 13 x 9-inch pan. Prepare cake mix as directed on package using water, oil and egg whites. Spread batter in greased and floured pan. Drop pie filling by heaping teaspoonfuls evenly onto batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until edges pull away from pan and top is golden brown.
Cool cake until completely cooled. In medium bowl, combine frosting and whipped topping.
Blend well and spread over cooled cake.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes and onion in water until tender; drain well. Mash coarsely with fork.
Add celery soup, milk, butter to taste and salt and pepper to taste.
Return to stove on medium heat until soup is heated through.

title: canned peaches
directions: To keep peaches/fruit from turning dark after peeling, place them in the salt and vinegar water as you slice them up.

title: broiled backfin crabmeat
directions: Spread crabmeat in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch Pyrex dish.
Cut margarine in pats and place over top of crabmeat.
Sprinkle with garlic salt and black pepper.
Place in oven on broil until butter is melted and the tips of crabmeat are lightly golden.
Serve as appetizer or main dish.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Grate rind of orange into chopped cranberries. Cut up orange and add to cranberries along with pineapple, sugar and nuts. Refrigerate overnight.

title: amazing coconut pie
directions: Combine all of the ingredients except the coconut in the blender.
Blend for 3 minutes.
Then pour the mixture into a greased 9 x 10-inch pan.
Let stand for 5 minutes; sprinkle coconut on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.

title: bavarian date slices
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; chill.
When slightly thickened, beat with eggbeater until of consistency of whipped cream.
Fold in almonds, dates and marshmallows, then the whipped cream to which almond flavoring and salt have been added.
Pour into loaf pan; chill until firm.
Serve in slices.
Serves 8 people.

title: egg pie
directions: Blend sugar and flour together; gradually add the well beaten eggs.
Mix in margarine; add buttermilk.
Pour mixture into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° until pie is golden brown.

title: cheese bread
directions: Beat egg at low speed of electric mixer.
Add biscuit mix, milk and cheese; beat 1 1/2 minutes at medium speed until well mixed.
Spoon batter into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Yields 1 loaf.

title: spiced tea mix
directions: Mix.
Put 3 teaspoons in cup.
Add boiling water.
Good on a cold day.

title: deep south red beans and rice
directions: Cut bacon into bite size pieces.
Place in a saucepan and cook until partially browned.
Pour off the fat which has cooked out of the bacon.
Add the onion.
Cook until slightly browned.
Pour off any fat.
Add the beans and bay leaf.
Cover.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Add water only if mixture begins to stick.
Stir occasionally.
Stir in rice.
Cover and cook until rice is hot.

title: western pot roast
directions: In heavy pot, brown meat on sides and top in small amount of oil.
Add chopped onion; cook until golden.
Combine catsup, Worcestershire sauce, brown sugar, vinegar and salt; pour over roast.
Simmer, covered, about 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Slice and serve with sauce along with onions, carrots and potato chunks if desired.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: applesauce oatmeal muffins
directions: Combine oatmeal, flour, cinnamon, baking powder and baking soda.
Add applesauce, milk, brown sugar, oil and egg white.
Mix just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Put in greased muffin pan.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: If chicken is not boneless, remove bones and skin.
Then cut chicken breasts into halves.
Place chicken between 2 pieces of waxed paper.
Pound with meat mallet or hammer until 1/4-inch thick.
Place one slice of ham and cheese on each piece of chicken. Roll up carefully, beginning at narrow end.
Secure with wooden toothpick.

title: chicken wings
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour over chicken.
Let marinate for 1 hour (or longer if possible).
Line 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with foil. Bake for 1 hour at 400° until chicken is very tender.

title: bread pudding(lo-cal)
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix just until bread is moistened. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with Pam or the like.
Place in a nonpreheated oven.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Serve alone or with fat-free ice cream or frozen yogurt.
Serves about 10 to 12.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Heat milk, butter and chocolate in double boiler until mixture almost boils and chocolate is melted.
Stir until smooth.
Remove from heat and cool until lukewarm.
Place mixture in large mixing bowl.
Add eggs, sugar and vanilla; mix well.
Sift flour, baking soda and salt together, adding a little at a time until flour is added and mix well.
Pour into 8 x 12-inch baking pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: good corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Grease 2 pans.
Pour into pans and bake at 450° for 20 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Saute the onion in the butter until translucent.
Add the potatoes and combine.
Add the lemon juice, thyme and salt.
Mix. Spray a casserole dish with nonstick vegetable cooking spray.
Put half the potato mixture in the casserole and sprinkle with the flour.
Add the rest of the potatoes.
Pour in the skim milk and sprinkle with the bread crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until potatoes are tender and slightly browned on top.
Yields 4 servings.

title: pecan drops
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift flour with salt; set aside.
In large bowl, beat margarine, shortening, sugar, cream and vanilla until smooth and fluffy.
Stir in flour mixture until well combined.
Stir in nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls, 2-inches apart, onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or just until light golden brown.
Remove to wire rack; cool.

title: sausage stew
directions: Cut sausage in small pieces. Add rest of ingredients. Cook in chicken broth or water until vegetables and bows are done.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add fruit and juice with beaten egg. Pour into oblong cake pan and sprinkle with 1 cup brown sugar. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream sugar and butter until fluffy. Add banana, eggs and vanilla.
Blend well.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to mixture and mix thoroughly.
(Add 1/4 cup chopped, toasted walnuts, if desired.)
Turn into greased, sprayed 8 x 4-inch loaf pan and bake until tester inserted in center comes out clean (about 55 minutes).
Remove from pan and cool completely before slicing.

title: quesadilla casserole
directions: Oil a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Layer tortillas on bottom of pan.
Put cheese on top of tortillas, then layer of hamburger.
Place another layer of tortillas.
Top with cheese and hamburger.
Blend remaining ingredients and pour over top of last layer.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pecan or walnut pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, syrup, vanilla and margarine or butter. Mix well.
Add nuts and stir.
Pour into uncooked pie shell. Bake in slow oven until almost set, about 45 minutes to 1 hour, at 350°.

title: fruit bars
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine first four ingredients in bowl; set aside, stirring occasionally.
in large bowl, beat together sugar and margarine until creamy.
Add flour, oats and cinnamon. Beat until crumbly.
Use 3/4 cup oats for topping.
Press remaining oat mixture into bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 15 minutes.
Spread fruit evenly over crust.
Combine nuts and reserved oat mixture.
Sprinkle over fruit.
Bake 16 to 20 minutes.

title: coconut frosting
directions: Combine sugar, syrup, water, egg whites, cream of tartar and salt in top of double boiler.
Cook over boiling water, beating with electric mixer until mixture stands in peaks.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Continue beating until frosting holds deep swirls.
Frost cake.
Sprinkle immediately with coconut, pressing into sides for pretty cake.

title: tofu pie
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water and add lemon juice. Set aside to cool a little.
Blend tofu with mixer, then add 1 carton of Cool Whip; mix, then add jello until smooth.
Pour into the 3 chocolate pie crusts and refrigerate until firm, but do not cover.
After firm, top with Cool Whip.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Prepare pastry.
Sprinkle bacon, cheese and onion in pastry lined pie pan.
Beat eggs slightly; beat in remaining ingredients.
Pour cream mixture into pie pan.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 300°; bake 30 minutes longer, or until knife inserted 1 inch from edge comes out clean. Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.
Serve in wedges.
Makes 6 main dish servings (8 appetizer servings).

title: ginger creams
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar, egg and molasses.
Sift flour, salt and spices together and stir into molasses mixture, alternately with hot water and baking soda mixture.
Chill dough thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoon about 2 inches apart on slightly greased baking sheet.
Bake about 8 minutes at 400°.
Cover the tops with frosting while still warm.

title: quick and tasty dessert
directions: You will need one deep dish Pyrex pie plate.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes.
Fry bacon crisp.
Drain bacon on paper towels and save grease.
Crumble bacon on sliced hot potatoes.

title: venison roast
directions: Take roast and put strips of bacon across top of it to keep moisture in.
Cook slowly at 300° to 325° until tender.
If more gravy is desired, use 2 cans of mushroom soup.

title: catfish fillets with crabmeat topping
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in small bowl; brush mixture on both sides of fillets.
Combine garlic powder, Creole seasoning and ground red pepper.
Sprinkle evenly over both sides of fillets.
Place fillets in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 minutes.
Coat a large nonstick skillet with cooking spray; place over medium-high heat until hot.
Add chopped onion, green onions, green pepper and sweet red pepper. Saute 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Add crabmeat and cook 30 seconds or until thoroughly heated, stirring constantly. Spoon crabmeat mixture evenly over baked fillets.
Bake an additional 5 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with fork.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sausage balls
directions: Allow sausage to reach room temperature. Add cheese and baking mix.
Squeeze together until firm.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: three minute pie
directions: Blend lemonade and milk, then fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into pie crust.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.

title: alabama chocolate pecan jumbo christmas fudge pie
directions: Combine chocolate crumbs and 1/3 cup melted butter.
Firmly press mixture on bottom and sides of pie plate and bake at 350° until done or 6 to 8 minutes.
Cream 1/2 cup butter.
Gradually add brown sugar, beating at medium speed and add eggs, one at a time.
Stir in melted chocolate and next 4 ingredients.
Pour mixture into prepared crust.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes and let cool.
Top with Cool Whip, chocolate syrup, maraschino cherries, etc.

title: chicken divine
directions: Mix mushroom soup and sour cream. Pour over chicken and beef in bottom of greased casserole dish. Sprinkle
top with bacon bits and paprika. Bake for 3 hours at 250 degrees. Serves 4.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender, then drain and add cracker crumbs, milk, ham, onion, eggs and cheese.
Mix ingredients and bake for 30 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Blend together the oil and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well. Stir in flour and mix well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour in greased tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: holy cake
directions: A house should have a cookie jar, for when it's half past three

title: neiman-marcus bars
directions: Cream together cream cheese, 2 eggs, confectioners sugar and vanilla.
Mix first 4 ingredients together and press into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread creamed mixture over first layer. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top will bubble and brown.

title: cheese cake
directions: Beat sugar and cream cheese.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 350°
for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven for 7 minutes.
Mix sour cream and sugar.
Add to top of cake.
Return to oven for 8 minutes.

title: orange cake deluxe
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pineapple millionaire pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Cream powdered sugar and oleo.
Add egg, salt and vanilla. Mix until light and fluffy.
Spoon mixture evenly into crusts. Chill and whip cream until stiff.
Stir in pineapple and nuts. Spoon on top of pies and chill thoroughly.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter on High 1 minute in a glass casserole.
Stir in milk, flour and sugar.
Pour peaches over batter.
Do not stir. Microwave on High, 10 to 15 minutes.

title: todd's keuka cottage oatmeal pancakes
directions: Combine the milk and rolled oats in a bowl and let them stand at least 5 minutes.
Add the oil and beaten eggs, mixing well. Stir in the flour, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Stir just until the dry ingredients are moistened.
Bake on a hot lightly oiled griddle, using 1/4 cup batter for each pancake.
Turn them when the top is bubbly and the edges slightly dry.
Our favorite cottage breakfast!
Makes 8 to 10 pancakes.

title: welsh rarebit
directions: Melt butter.
Add cornstarch & milk.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Add cheese and seasonings.
Serve on crackers or toast.

title: christmas pies(no bake)
directions: Make 2 vanilla wafer or graham cracker crusts.
Slice bananas into prepared crusts.
Mix cream cheese, sugar, Cool Whip, milk, vanilla and pecans.
Add mixture to bananas and top with pie filling.
Chill before eating.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Place all ingredients except nuts in a large bowl.
Microwave at Medium (50%) until chocolate chips are melted; takes 3 to 5 minutes, stirring once or twice.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into a well-greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Refrigerate until set.
Cuts best when cold.

title: trout with clam stuffing
directions: Cook celery, onion and mushrooms in 2 tablespoons butter or margarine.
Stir in clams, bread, parsley, salt and pepper. Moisten with a little reserved clam juice.
Stuff trout cavity with clam mixture and place on greased baking pan.
Dot with remaining butter.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 15 to 25 minutes, until fish flakes easily with fork.
Garnish with lemon and parsley.

title: strawberry fizz
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender until smooth. Serve immediately.

title: caramel pie
directions: Place 3 unopened cans of Eagle Brand milk in a Dutch oven or large cooking pot.
Cover with water to a depth of 1-inch.
Bring to a boil.
Boil for 4 hours, being careful to add more boiling water to keep cans well covered.
Carefully remove cans from water and open them immediately, being careful to cover each can with a towel to prevent being burned.
Spread in pie crust.
Chill well. Top with whipped cream or Cool Whip as desired.

title: brownie cake
directions: Prepare brownies according to package directions, using a 11x7 inch baking pan.
Cool.
Whisk fruit spread in a small bowl until smooth.
Cut brownie crosswise in half.
Place half of brownie, flat-side down on serving dish.
Spread with fruit spread and 1 cup whipped topping.
Place second half of brownie, flat-side down, over bottom layer.
Spread with remaining whipped topping.
Arrange strawberry halves on whipped topping.
Drizzle chocolate sauce onto cake before serving.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook mixed vegetables as directed on package.
Mix celery, onion, mayonnaise and cheese together and spread over mixed vegetables in a 9 x 9-inch glass pan.
Mash package of Ritz crackers and add to 1 stick of butter; sprinkle over top.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes or until casserole is bubbling on sides.

title: chili soup
directions: Add all ingredients in saucepan.
Heat. Simmer for a few minutes.
Add grated Cheddar cheese to top.

title: spoon salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill for at least 2 hours.

title: corn casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix cream of celery soup and sour cream.
In casserole dish layer corn, soup mixture and grated cheese.
Mix crushed Ritz crackers with melted butter.
Top the layers with cracker mixture.
Bake 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: cucumber pickles
directions: Cut lengthwise, like French fries, large cucumbers and remove seeds.
If pickles are smaller, slice or do in strips.
Note: Larger cucumbers are the best.
In plastic bowl, cover cucumbers with water.
Add 2 cups pickling lime.
Cover with towel.
Soak for 24 hours.
Rinse several times.
Cover with cold water.
Soak for 3 more hours.
Drain water and pour ingredients into pot (cloves, celery seed, pickle spice are best put in cheesecloth and added to pot).
Cook for 35 minutes (medium heat; just to boiling).
Pour into jars, add lids, turn upside down for best sealing results.

title: my papa's italian spaghetti sauce
directions: Heat olive oil.
Add ground beef and stir.
Add onion, garlic, pepper, mushrooms, tomato paste, tomatoes and water.
Cover and simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve over cooked spaghetti.

title: 5 flavor pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, Crisco and butter together; then add the eggs, one at a time.
Then add the milk, plain flour and salt.
Mix well; then add the teaspoons of flavoring as listed.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours in a greased and floured tube pan.

title: easy sweet rolls
directions: Take frozen dough balls and place in baking pan.
Mix together pudding and brown sugar.
Pour melted butter over rolls and sprinkle pudding mix and pecans over rolls.
Cover with wax paper sprayed with Pam.
Let stand overnight.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: delicious sauce for brisket or roast
directions: Marinate brisket or roast in sauce overnight and bake at 250° for 5 to 6 hours.
Leftover sauce may be used a second time or makes a delicious gravy.

title: seven layer salad
directions: This works best in a deep, narrow bowl, preferably glass so layers show.
Layer ingredients, starting with lettuce.
Combine mayonnaise and sugar together for layer seven.
Top with cheese and bacon bits.
Refrigerate overnight to allow flavors to blend. When serving, slice down through all layers.

title: cold cucumber soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender and process until smooth. Chill.
Yields 2 1/2 to 3 cups.

title: coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake according to package directions.
Bake in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
While cake is still hot, punch holes in cake all over with fork.
Mix condensed milk and creme of coconut in small bowl; pour over cake.
Cool completely.
Spread top of cake with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle coconut over Cool Whip.
Keep refrigerated. Even better after refrigerated overnight.

title: beth's pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except eggs.
Add eggs, one at a time. Beat well and pour into a greased Bundt pan. Bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: zesty italian chicken
directions: Place chicken breasts in greased casserole.
Pour spaghetti sauce over chicken. Bake for 1 hour in a 350° oven.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Reduce heat to 325°. Heat until cheese is melted and lightly golden brown.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion slightly.
Alternate layers of meat mixture and potatoes in casserole dish until all are used.
Add soup, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Good for covered dish meals.

title: drop sugar cookies
directions: Drop by teaspoon; sprinkle sugar on top.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Bake cookie dough for one big cookie on pizza pie pan.
Put fruit on top of cookie (mixed all together with apple pie filling).
Put Cool Whip on top of fruit.
Put cherries on top.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Mix ingredients, adding cereal last.
Store in refrigerator for 48 hours before baking.
Bake at 400° until done.
(Very moist and keeps well.)

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, soda, salt and sugar.
Cut in 2/3 cup margarine until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Add buttermilk, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Turn dough onto lightly floured surface; knead lightly 4 or 5 times. Roll dough to 3/4-inch thickness; cut with biscuit cutter.
Place on lightly greased baking sheet; brush with melted margarine. Bake at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes.
May brush with additional margarine when done, if desired.

title: pat m.'s fettucine alfredo
directions: Melt butter on high until lightly browned.
Add 1/2 cup of cream and boil rapidly until slightly thickened.
Reduce heat to medium.
Add cooked, drained pasta and mix gently.
Add 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 cup cream.
Mix gently.
Repeat with remaining cheese and cream.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
(Option: Top with nutmeg.)

title: popcorn balls
directions: Bring the first 3 ingredients to a boil over medium heat 5 minutes. Add the soda. Stir well and mix with popcorn.
Bake in oven at 200° for 25 to 30 minutes. Store in tight container.
(Add 1 cup of nuts, if desired.)

title: date cake
directions: First put dates in bowl, sprinkle soda over them.
Pour hot water over dates and soda.
Let stand awhile.
Cream eggs, sugar and oleo together.
Roll nuts in 3 tablespoons flour.
Add dates to sugar mixture.
Add flour and cream well.
Last, add nuts and vanilla.
Makes a 4 layer cake.
Bake at 350° until done.
Top with a caramel filling to which nuts have been added.
Will be delicious.

title: pork tenderloin
directions: Marinate pork tenderloin in remaining ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Bake in greased 13 x 9-inch pan in 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: brown sugar
directions: Add molasses to sugar and stir with a fork. Store brown sugar in an airtight container to keep it soft.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown meat, peppers and onion; drain fat.
Pour in pizza sauce and cooked pasta.
Stir well, then put in 9 x 13 glass pan. Cover with pepperoni and Mozzarella cheese.
Bake 45 minutes, covered with foil, in 325° oven.

title: cookie sheet apple pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt and cut in shortening.
Put egg yolk in measuring cup and add enough milk to make 2/3 cup.
Add to shortening mixture and mix until you can make a ball.

title: dirt pie
directions: Mix vanilla pudding as directed on box.
Add cream cheese, sugar and cool whip.
Crumble oreos and layer in dip dish with mixture.
May add gummy worms for decorations.

title: pizza loaf
directions: Brown ground beef until crumbly; drain.
Add tomato paste, oregano, basil, garlic and cheese stirring until cheese melts.

title: deep-dish taco squares
directions: In a nonstick skillet, cook beef until no longer pink; drain. Remove from heat. Stir in cheese, mayonnaise, sour cream and onion. In a bowl, combine biscuit mix and water. Spread into an 8-inch square baking dish coated with nonstick cooking spray. Top with beef mixture and tomato. Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 20 minutes or until bottom crust is golden brown.

title: whipped cream pound cake
directions: Do not preheat oven.
The cake must be put in a cold oven to keep the cream from souring.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients. Pour into an 8 x 11 casserole dish that has been sprayed with Pam.

title: microwave chicken and dressing
directions: In a 2-quart oblong glass baking dish, toss together stuffing mix, celery, onion, pimento, egg and broth.
Brush chicken pieces with melted butter.
Place on top of dressing with meaty pieces to the outside edges of dish.
Sprinkle with salt and paprika.
Cover with wax paper.
Microwave at High (10) for 19 to 22 minutes.
Let stand about 5 minutes before serving.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk and butter; bring to boil.
Boil 2 minutes.
Beat and let cool.
Add oatmeal, vanilla and salt.
Add pecans or coconut.
Drop by teaspoonful onto waxed paper.
Let set until completely cool.
You may want to use 1/2 cup peanut brittle instead of pecans or coconut.

title: dirt cake
directions: Cream butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
In another big bowl, mix milk, pudding and Cool Whip.
Combine mixtures.
In 8 x 10-inch pan, pail or pot (plug hole), pat 1/3 of cookies on bottom; layer 1/2 filling and top with 1/3 cookies, then filling layer. Top with remaining cookies.
Refrigerate overnight.
Before serving, add decorations - worms, fake plants, shovel, etc.

title: polish noodles and cabbage
directions: Melt butter in large skillet. Add onion. Saute until soft. Add cabbage and saute until crisp-tender. Stir in caraway seeds, salt and pepper. Cook noodles in salted boiling water as directed on package. Drain well. Stir noodles into cabbage. Add sour cream.

title: marshmallows
directions: In medium saucepan combine granulated sugar, gelatin and salt. Stir in water; heat until sugar is dissolved, then bring just to boiling.
Remove from heat; cool slightly, about 5 minutes.
Stir in vanilla.
Transfer to large mixer bowl.
Beat at high speed of electric mixer about 10 minutes or until mixture resembles thick marshmallow cream.
Pour into buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Cool.
With kitchen shears dipped in hot water, cut in 1 1/4-inch squares.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Makes about 6 dozen pieces.

title: italian zucchini crescent pie
directions: Cook and stir zucchini and onion in margarine for 10 minutes. Add parsley and other seasonings.
Combine eggs and cheese.
Stir in zucchini mixture.
Separate crescent rolls into 8 triangles. Place in ungreased 10-inch pie pan.
Press over bottom and up sides to form crust.
Spread crust mixture with mustard.
Pour vegetable mixture into crust.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes or until center is set.
Cover crust with foil last 10 minutes of baking; let set 10 minutes before serving.
Yields 6 servings.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Rinse chicken and pat dry.
Dip into beaten eggs; coat with bread crumbs.
Brown on both sides in oil in skillet; remove to 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese and half the Parmesan cheese.
Spread spaghetti sauce over top; sprinkle with remaining Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Yield:
8 servings.

title: seven hour stew
directions: Place in oven (covered) and bake 7 hours at 250°.

title: leeza's low-fat ziti
directions: Cook ziti al dente.
Combine Ricotta, egg and parsley in a bowl; mix.
Drain ziti.
Coat bottom of baking dish with 2 cups marinara sauce.
On the sauce, layer half the ziti, half the Ricotta, half the Mozzarella and half the Parmesan or Romano. Cover with 2 more cups of marinara.
Layer the remaining ziti, Ricotta and Mozzarella.
Cover with the remaining sauce.
Sprinkle with the remaining Romano or Parmesan.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour, until bubbling.

title: chicken wings
directions: Mix sauce mixture and marinate wings at least 2 hours.
Spread wings flat in baking dish and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: party meat balls
directions: Mix first ingredients together and make small balls (bite size).
Brown meat balls and remove from pan.
Drain on paper towels.
Place chili sauce and jelly in pan and melt together. Add meat balls and simmer approximately 30 minutes.
Insert toothpick in meat balls and serve.

title: best ever cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in order and pour into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: oklahoma dip
directions: Combine sausage, hamburger and finely chopped onion until browned.
Drain fat.

title: ray's chili
directions: Brown ground
beef; drain.
Add chili mix, tomatoes and beans. Stir
in
celery,	garlic and parsley; bring to a boil for 2 minutes.
Turn
down
heat	and simmer for 25 to 30 minutes. Serve with cheese on top.

title: mom's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well. Add dry ingredients and chocolate chips.
Mix well.
Add 1/2 cup nuts and oatmeal.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes on ungreased cookie sheets.

title: rice krispies cookies
directions: Mix all the ingredients in the order given.
Drop by teaspoonful on slightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 6 to 10 minutes.

title: santa's tasty tidbits
directions: Cook onions in butter in small skillet until tender, but not browned; about 3 minutes.
Set aside.

title: mushroom roll-ups
directions: Mix cheese and mushrooms together.
Use garlic salt to taste. Cut crescent rolls in half.
Put small amount of mixture in middle and brown.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix cocoa and sugar together.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour in the unbaked pie shell.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Put cottage cheese in a bowl.
Add jello to cottage cheese. Drain pineapple and add to cottage cheese.
Fold in Cool Whip and oranges.
Refrigerate.

title: teriyaki burgers
directions: Mix the turkey, beef, ginger, salt, pepper and 2 tablespoons light soy sauce. Form into burgers. Either grill or pan-fry until done. Brush with a mixture of the 1/4 cup soy sauce, honey and hot pepper sauce. Cook both sides for another minute.
Put meat on buns. Serve with a salad.

title: double fudge brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
In small saucepan, combine sugar, butter and water.
Bring to a boil and remove from heat.
Add chocolate chips and vanilla and stir until melted.
Transfer this mixture to a large bowl and beat in eggs one at a time.
In a separate bowl, combine unsifted flour, soda and salt.
Gradually add this to the chocolate mixture.
Once its all mixed, spread it into the greased pan.
Bake at 325° for about 50 minutes.

title: pizza pork chops
directions: Remove excess fat from pork. Sprinkle pork with salt and pepper. Heat in 12-inch skillet over medium-high heat. Cook pork in oil about 5 minutes, turning once, until brown. Place pork in 3 1/2 to 6-quart slow cooker. Sprinkle onion over pork. Add spaghetti sauce. Cover and cook on low heat setting 4 to 6 hours or until pork is very tender. Place rosamarina on platter. Top with pork and sauce. Sprinkle with cheese. Makes 6 servings.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Drain and rinse in colander all canned vegetables, then add all fresh vegetables and drained vegetables in large bowl.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix cream cheese and confectioners sugar well.
Spread over cooled graham crust.
Slice bananas over cream cheese mixture. Drain pineapple and spread over bananas.
Spread Cool Whip over bananas.
Top with cherries and pecans.
Refrigerate.
Very good.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl.
Chill until firm.
Roll into ball.
Roll ball in 1 cup of pecans.

title: pork barbecue philippine style
directions: In a bowl, mix soy sauce, garlic, vinegar, brown sugar, and ketchup.
Add pork cubes and marinate at least overnight.
Heat grill until hot.
With bamboo skewers, thread pork cubes and place on grill, turning each side until browned and well done.
Serves: 6.

title: monkey bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Coat inside of Bundt pan with cooking spray. Melt margarine.

title: heavenly rice
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except the cream.
Let stand for several hours, stirring occasionally.
Add cream, stir and chill good in refrigerator.
After mixture gets set, sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Mix butter and sugar in large bowl.
Add coconut, nuts and vanilla.
Roll into small balls and chill for hour.
Mix wax and chocolate chips and melt in double boiler over simmering water. Drop each ball in chocolate mixture with toothpick.
Place on waxed paper until cool.
Store covered.

title: american cheese and roast beef
directions: From leftover turkey,
slice
the breast of turkey thin and on lettuce leaves, add the turkey.
Slice tomatoes thin, 3 to 4 slices, and put on top of turkey and lettuce.
Spread the bread with mustard, salad dressing or mayonnaise.
Serve.

title: chocolate chip pecan pie
directions: Beat together eggs and sugar. Gradually add melted butter and corn syrup. Stir in chocolate, nuts and bourbon. Pour into pie crust and bake in 350° oven for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: seafoam candy
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients until mixture will string from a spoon.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks.
Pour the cooked syrup over the beaten egg whites; beat until thick.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper to cool.
This mixture is very hot.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni.
Mix together cooked macaroni, onions, pimento, grated cheese (reserving 1/4 cup of cheese for topping), milk and mushroom soup.
Season with salt and pepper.
Pour into greased casserole.
Sprinkle with reserved cheese and cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mauve punch
directions: Combine cranberry juice and 7-Up.
Will be real foamy.
Drop balls of sherbet on top.

title: cream beef or sos
directions: In a skillet, brown off hamburger, drain meat of fat retaining 2 tbls. of hamburger fat.
Heat fat, add flour and brown.
Add milk to make gravy, salt and pepper to taste.
Add meat to gravy.
Serve hot on toast.

title: tammy wilson's barbecue sauce
directions: Coat about 9 pieces of chicken with flour and brown in skillet. Saute onion, green pepper and mushrooms in butter until tender. Add 2/3 cup water and remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil. Place browned chicken in a casserole.
Pour sauce over and between layers.
Bake at 350° at least 45 minutes.

title: fried sweet potatoes
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Peel potatoes and slice 1/2 inch thick.
Put potato slices in skillet, turning once immediately to get butter on both sides.
Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon on potatoes.
Cover and cook on low for about 20 minutes; turn occasionally.

title: louise's jam cake
directions: Sift flour and spices together; set aside.
Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg yolks and beat thoroughly. Alternately add buttermilk/soda mixture and dry ingredients.
Mix jams, raisins, preserves and nuts together and add to batter. Fold in the beaten egg whites.

title: brownies
directions: Mix ingredients and bake at 350°.

title: ma's speckrouches(meat and onion filled rolls)
directions: Saute onion and ham in margarine.
Take a small amount of dough (golf ball size or slightly smaller) and pull very thin with your fingers into a 3-inch circle.
Put 1 teaspoon filling on one half of the dough and fold in half.
(Should look like a turn over.) Pinch edge together and seal.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Place on a cookie sheet and bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes, until golden brown.

title: calico salad(3-bean)
directions: Drain beans, mix well and refrigerate.

title: salt cod with leeks
directions: Soak the cod (which should be as light colored as possible) for at least 48 hours.
Cut it into 2-inch pieces and put into 3 1/2 pints of water with the onions and garlic, sliced, and the bouquet garni. Bring to a boil and simmer for 15 minutes.
Dab the pieces of cod dry. Flour lightly and fry in very hot olive oil until golden brown. Transfer to the bottom of a gratin dish with fish slice.
Slice the leeks (the white part only) and brown slightly in the same pan.
Put them on top of the cod. Add the stock and plenty of pepper.
Put in a hot oven for about 20 minutes. Serve with mashed or boiled potatoes.

title: hot (spiced) fruit
directions: Drain fruit.
Layer in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Cut oleo in chunks over fruit.
Sprinkle sugar over this.
Sprinkle cinnamon and cloves on this.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Prepare macaroni and cheese.
Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Pour in cake pan.
Place cheese slices over top.
Bake until cheese melts.

title: pan eclair
directions: Melt margarine in water.
Add flour while on heat.
Take off heat and add eggs, one at a time, beating after each egg.
Spread in slightly greased baking dish (11 x 14-inch).
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
It will be bubbly.
Poke down with a fork.
Let cool.
Mix cream cheese, pudding and milk.
Spread over crust. Refrigerate until firm.
Top with Cool Whip.
Drizzle with chocolate syrup or nuts.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef with onion, salt and pepper. Drain well.

title: fried okra
directions: Beat eggs with water.
Dip sliced okra in flour, then eggs and then cornmeal.
Fry in skillet until golden.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix sugar and margarine; add eggs, banana and water.
Add all other ingredients and bake at 350°.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix in all ingredients, then grease a pan.
Set the oven at 375° and let bake for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until brown.
Cut and serve.

title: low-fat beef stroganoff
directions: Place beef cubes, 1/2 cup of wine, salt and pepper in a large Ziploc bag; marinate several hours or overnight.
Heat a large skillet or Dutch oven; spray pan 3 times with cooking spray.
Add beef cubes and stir until browned.
Add garlic; saute lightly. Add onion and mushrooms; saute until onion is transparent.
Add 1 cup of wine; cover and simmer until beef is tender, about 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove cover.
Cook until liquid is reduced by half. Add buttermilk.
Stir 5 to 6 tablespoons of water into cornstarch and stir until smooth.
When buttermilk starts to bubble, add cornstarch thickening a little at a time, cooking until sauce thickens.
Serve over hot noodles.
Serves 6.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Remove center of cabbage, save insides. Cook in salt water until tender. 1 c. minced onion, 2 Tbsp melted butter, add cabbage insides, 2 cloves garlic, 2/3 c. tomatoes paste. Cook 6 to 8 minutes. Combine sauce mixture, pork, bread crumbs, parsley, thyme, sage and pepper in large bowl. Stuff cabbage and cover opening with foil. Tie together.
Melt 2 Tbsp butter, carrots, onion, parsley and cook 5 minutes. Place cabbage open end down. Add remaining ingredients. Simmer 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Measure flour and sift 3 times.
Then sift it together with salt and baking powder.
Cream butter with sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Cream well.
Add flour alternately with cream cheese or sour cream to mixture.
Add vanilla or use any desired flavoring.
Bake in tube cake pan 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: joan's dressing
directions: Mix dry ingredients and then add wet ingredients.
Mix together, only until lumps disappear.
Bake in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased pan at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients with shrimp added last.
Refrigerate overnight to blend flavors.
Serve with crackers.

title: breakfast pie
directions: Beat eggs
and add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into pie shell.
Line the edge of pie shell with foil so it won't burn.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: grandma's apple butter
directions: Mix all ingredients and simmer gently (partly covered) for about 1 hour, stirring frequently.
When thick, pour into hot sterilized jars and seal at once.
This makes 5 pints of apple butter.

title: mounds
directions: Mix first five ingredients together and put in a 13 x 17 pan. Chill in freezer several hours.
Cut into 1 inch or smaller squares.
Melt candy bars, chips and wax together.
Dip coconut squares in mixture and place on waxed paper to dry.
Almonds can be pressed into coconut squares before dipping.

title: bologna i
directions: Mix and sprinkle over meat like you would sausage.
Grind twice. Stuff in cloth bags
5 to 7, 3-inches in diameter.
Let hang 6 days and smoke.
(Old recipe
says:
Let
hang 48 hours. Brush bags with liquid smoke and let hang several days.
Place in big iron kettle.
Cover with cold water and
boil
until
bologna floats.)

title: brownie cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour round pan (8 x 1 1/2-inch).
Mix all ingredients, except whipped cream and chocolate.
Spread in pan.
Bake about 35 minutes or until top appears dry.
Cool 10 minutes and remove from pan.
Cool cake completely.
Top with sweetened whipped cream and shaved chocolate. Refrigerate.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Combine cocoa and sugar in saucepan.
Blend in water.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir for 2 minutes.
Add milk.
Stir and heat to desired temperature. Add vanilla.
Makes about 1 quart.

title: favorite pound cake
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each one.
Add flour alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour.
Mix just until blended after each addition.
Stir in flavorings.

title: fat-free almond cream and berries
directions: Mix sour cream and sugar.
Add a few drops almond extract. Chill.
Put assorted berries in four serving bowls.
Divide cream evenly over the bowls and serve.

title: ice cream supreme
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, place 1/2 Cool Whip to form bottom layer.
Arrange ice cream sandwiches on top of Cool Whip, cutting a few to fill small spaces.
Cover with remaining Cool Whip. Sprinkle with candy pieces.
Freeze for several hours.
Drizzle with chocolate syrup when serving if desired.

title: chicken dijon
directions: In large skillet over medium-high heat, cook chicken on all sides in butter until brown and tender, about 15 to 20 minutes. Remove chicken to heated platter; keep warm.
To drippings in skillet, add garlic, onion, mushrooms, salt and pepper.
Cook until onion is soft, about 5 minutes.
Stir in milk, parsley and mustard.
Simmer, stirring occasionally, until sauce is slightly thickened.
Return chicken to pan; heat through, about 3 to 5 minutes.
Serve immediately.
(Rice is a nice side dish with this.)

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes until tender; do not overcook.
Drain all but 1 cup of water from potatoes.
Add evaporated milk, salt and pepper to suit taste.
Saute pepper, celery and onion in margarine until tender.
Combine sauteed vegetables and parsley to potatoes. Simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve with grated cheese, bacon bits and sour cream as desired.
Always better the second day.
Serves 8.

title: grandma's cherries in the snow
directions: Mix together cream cheese and sugar until creamy. Fold in Cool Whip. Tear angel food cake into bite-size pieces and stir into sugar, cream cheese and Cool Whip mixture. Pour into serving dish and top with 1 can cherry pie filling.

title: glazed pineapple chicken
directions: Preheat grill or broiler.
In a large sealable plastic bag, thoroughly combine marinade.
Mix with pineapple juice, soy sauce and brown sugar.
Add chicken parts and coat thoroughly with marinade.
Seal bag.
Marinate 15 minutes.
Grill or broil chicken 5 to 6 inches from heat for 15 to 18 minutes per side or until chicken is thoroughly cooked.
Baste occasionally with remaining marinade.
Serve chicken garnished with sliced pineapple.

title: is it cheese cake
directions: Melt butter in medium saucepan.
Stir in cake mix.
Remove from heat and place in baking pan (9 x 12-inch).
Sprinkle with coconut.
Pour pie filling over.
Spread to edges.
Mix sour cream with egg yolks and vanilla.
Spread on top of filling.
Sprinkle with sugar, cinnamon and 1/4 cup coconut combined.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: tuna fish salad
directions: Put tuna in a large bowl and take a fork and break tuna apart. Add pickles, sugar and mayonnaise.
Stir, then take hard-boiled eggs and cut up, then mash them up very good with a fork.
Add this to tuna mixture and stir.
This is good for sandwiches or with crackers.

title: church windows
directions: Melt margarine and chocolate chips.
Cool slightly and add chopped nuts and marshmallows.
Mix and form into 2 logs.
Roll in coconut or confectioners sugar on wax paper.
Wrap logs in wax paper or foil and place in fridge until firm.

title: lemon and herb turkey breast
directions: Combine juice, oil, garlic, mustard, herbs, salt and pepper in gallon size plastic food bag.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Fold piece of heavy aluminum foil in half (dull side out) to form an 18-inch square.
Place turkey in middle of square and drizzle with marinade.
Fold foil over to seal tightly.
Prepare medium hot coals.
Grill packet 5 to 6-inches over coals for 25 minutes. Remove from grill.
Remove turkey from packet, reserving juices. Grill, basting with reserved juices and turning over, for 20 to 30 minutes longer or until cooked through.
Makes 8 servings.

title: applesauce muffins
directions: *If substituting butter or margarine for the butter flavor Crisco, reduce milk to only 3/4 cup and reduce amount of salt to 1/4 to 1/2 teaspoon.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine the eggs, oil, sugar, molasses and vanilla.
In a separate bowl, combine the flour, baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon, raisins and nuts.
Add to the egg mixture.
Stir in the zucchini, mix just until blended.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 1 hour. Cool on a wire rack for 10 minutes, remove from the pans.
Cool completely before slicing.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: crisco single pie crust
directions: Spoon
flour
into
measuring cup and level.
Mix flour and salt
in
medium
bowl.
Cut in Crisco with pastry blender until it forms pea-sized chunks.	Sprinkle with cold water one tablespoon at
a
time.
Some
brands of flour need more water than others.
Toss	lightly
with fork until dough will form a ball.
Press
between
hands
to
form five to 6-inch pancake. Flour rolling surface and pin lightly.
Roll dough into circle an inch
larger
than	pie plate.
Lift gently and flute under edge.

title: hot water corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In large bowl, sift corn meal, flour, baking powder and salt.
Add oil and stir.
Add enough boiling water to mixture to make a firm dough.
Place dough in skillet and turn once to cover with oil.
Bake at 425° for 1 hour.
Bread will be crusty.
Serve hot.

title: satiny beige icing
directions: Combine all ingredients in top of double boiler.
Beat with electric mixer over boiling water until peeks form, about 5 to 7 minutes.
Add vanilla.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Heat soups, milk and butter together.
Add extra mushrooms, if desired.
Add 1 1/4 cups raw rice and heat.
Put this mixture in a greased casserole.
Cut up chicken and drop in melted butter.
Lay on top of rice.
Don't move chicken and do not cover.
Do not add salt.
Bake 2 1/2 hours at 275°.

title: egg custard
directions: Beat egg whites stiff.
Set aside.
Mix sugar and egg yolks. Add egg whites, vanilla and melted margarine.
Scald milk and add to other mixture.
Put in unbaked pie shell.
Put in cold oven and bake at 225° until firm.

title: cream of winter vegetable soup
directions: In large saucepan, combine potatoes, squash, celery, onion, garlic, parsley, dry mustard and lemon peel.
Stir in chicken broth; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Transfer about 2 cups of vegetable-broth mixture to blender container or food processor bowl.
Cover and process until smooth.
Return pureed mixture to saucepan.
Stir in milk or cream.
Heat through.
Season to taste. Sprinkle nuts atop each serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: swedish meat balls for 48
directions: Return meat balls to gravy.
Cook 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 36 to 48 people.
The meat balls may be made, cooked and refrigerated the day before serving.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix first five ingredients (cake mix, sugar, sour cream, oil and poppy seed).
Add eggs, one at a time.
Grease Bundt cake pan.
Use sugar instead of flour.
Bake 45 to 55 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, vanilla and mayonnaise, then add soda in boiling water, dates and nuts.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: potato cheese soup
directions: In a large saucepan, melt margarine over medium heat.
Saute celery and onion until tender.
Add potatoes and broth.
Cover and simmer until potatoes are tender (about 12 minutes).
Puree potato mixture in a blender.
Return to saucepan, stir in milk and seasoning.
Add cheese and heat only until melted.
Makes 8 servings.

title: oven style caramel corn
directions: Place brown sugar, margarine, corn syrup and salt in a 2-quart saucepan.
Bring to a boil and boil 5 minutes.
Add vanilla and soda, stirring after each addition.
Pour syrup over popped corn and stir to cover all kernels.
Place on 2 cookie sheets and bake in 250° oven for 45 minutes, stirring often.
This may be stored in coffee cans or frozen in bags.

title: pizza meat loaf
directions: Mix ground beef with the next 8 ingredients.
Bake.
When done top with pizza sauce and bake for additional 10 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese on top and bake until cheese is melted.

title: dump cake
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan, add ingredients as they are listed.
Spread evenly in layers.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Cool and serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: second day mashed potatoes
directions: Mix all, except butter, beating well.
Put in buttered casserole; spread butter over top.
Bake 25 minutes in 400° oven until brown on top.

title: tortilla wheels
directions: Cream softened cream cheese and sour cream together.
Add remaining ingredients.
Spread on flour tortillas and roll. Refrigerate until firm.
Slice crosswise approximately 1/3-inch slices and serve.

title: grandma's potato soup
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to a boil; cover.
Reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Drain, setting vegetables aside and reserving 1 1/2 cups cooking liquid in Dutch oven.
Mash vegetable mixture with a potato masher or electric mixer.
Add to reserved cooking liquid, along with the next five ingredients.
Cook, stirring constantly, until soup is thoroughly heated.
Garnish with chopped chives, if desired.
Yield:
6 cups, about 116 calories per cup.

title: candied yams
directions: Cook sweet potatoes in water at least 30 minutes.
When cold, peel and slice into baking dish.
Sprinkle on sugar and seasoning. Add butter and cover with water.
Bake in 350° oven until thick syrup has formed.

title: tater tot dish
directions: Crumble hamburger in bottom of casserole.
Add layer of onion. Next add mixed vegetables mixed with celery soup.
Put in casserole, cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Add Tater Tots last half hour.

title: christmas butter cookies with icing
directions: Sift together flour, cream of tartar, salt and soda.
Cut in shortening until fine particles form.
Beat the eggs well and add sugar and vanilla.

Stir into first mixture and chill 1/2 hour. Pinch off dough and roll in balls about the size of walnuts. Place on greased cookie sheet and flatten with bottom of a glass which has been dipped in sugar.
Or:
Roll dough out to about 1/4-inch thickness on lightly floured board.
Cut out with cookie cutters and bake.
Bake in 375° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
For variation sift nutmeg and cinnamon with light brown sugar and sprinkle over top of cookies before baking.

title: egg drop soup
directions: Boil chicken with water at high heat, add the chicken bouillon cubes and white pepper.
Remove chicken when done.
In boiling water drop eggs in, lightly scrambling as you drop them in.
Then add the cornstarch mixture and food coloring, stirring constantly for 30 seconds.
Remove from heat.
When serving, toss in green onion.

title: ma's "goose grease"
directions: Grind all ingredients except mayonnaise and mustard to coarse small pieces.
Stir in prepared mustard and enough mayonnaise to spread easily.
Spread over English muffins and broil until bubbly and brown.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add seasoning mix; follow pack directions.
Add a jar of salsa.
Layer half of the ground beef in a 9 x 11-inch baking dish.
Top with crushed tortilla chips.
Add a layer of Cheddar cheese.
Layer remainder of ground beef and chips.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Top with sour cream. Sprinkle with additional cheese.

title: stuffed chicken breast savannah
directions: Flatten chicken breasts with meat mallet. Place a slice of ham and cheese on each breast. Roll up and secure with toothpicks. Dredge each roll in 1/4 cup flour, dip in egg and coat with bread crumbs. Lightly brown in 1/4 cup butter; add wine. Simmer, covered, 20 minutes. Place rolls in shallow baking dish, reserve drippings. Saute onion in 6 tablespoons butter until tender; blend in 1/4 cup flour, salt and pepper. Gradually add milk and half and half, stirring constantly until smooth. Add reserved drippings; simmer until thickened. Pour sauce over rolls. Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 20 minutes. Garnish with parsley.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: hot dog relish
directions: Sprinkle the coarsely ground vegetables with 1/2 cup salt; let stand overnight.
Combine and bring to a boil the remaining ingredients.

title: mock guacamole
directions: Position knife blade in food processor bowl.
Add asparagus. Process until smooth.
Transfer to a mixing bowl.
Stir in tomato and remaining.
Place mixture in a paper towel-lined wire-mesh strainer or colander and let drain 1 hour.
Cover and chill at least 3 hours.
Yields 2 cups.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all together (will be hard to manage; do the best you can).
Place mixture in a greased 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Top with 2 cups crushed corn flakes and 1/4 cup melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: buttermilk pan rolls
directions: In large mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water. Add buttermilk, oil and sugar. Combine flour, soda and salt. Add to yeast mixture and beat until smooth. Do not knead. Let stand for 10 minutes. Turn dough on a lightly floured surface. Punch down. Shape into 24 balls and place in 2 greased 9-inch square baking pans. Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled, about 30 minutes. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until golden brown. Yields 2 dozen.

title: "irish brain food"(snackin' spuds)
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Line a jelly roll pan with foil.
In mixing bowl, toss potatoes with olive oil, garlic and seasonings until well coated.
Transfer to jelly roll pan and arrange in a single layer.
Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes.
Turn them over and continue baking until well browned, about 15 to 20 minutes longer. Serve immediately with a big bowl of sour cream for dipping and lots of toothpicks!

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, melted butter and 3 teaspoons sugar.
Mix and place in square dish.
Pat it down and bake at 350° for 8 minutes. Let cool.

title: no butter biscuits
directions: Mix well and put into small ungreased muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: virginia spoon bread
directions: Mix
meal,
salt and margarine;
scald with the boiling water. Add well-beaten eggs, milk and baking powder.
Bake in moderate oven
in
greased
dish
for
approximately 40 minutes. Serve hot, and it loves butter.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream the sugar, cream cheese and butter.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add the vanilla.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: ozarkain taffy apples
directions: Melt 1/2 cup of sugar over direct flame, add boiling water and cook to a smooth syrup.
In a separate pan, cook the cream with remaining sugar and butter to soft ball stage.
Combine the 2 syrups until drops of syrup will form hard ball when dropped into cold water.
Cool to lukewarm.
Place apples on skewers.
Dip into caramel syrup.
Dip into ice water immediately to harden the caramel.

title: banana slush punch(for 75 small servings)
directions: Heat sugar and water until sugar melts.
Mix together all ingredients.
Freezes 8 hours.
Thaw 2 hours before serving.
Add 2 quarts of ginger ale.
(I have kept frozen longer.)

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken and debone.
Cut into cubes.
Saute chopped bell pepper and onion in butter.
Melt cheese in microwave and mix with cream of mushroom soup.
Add deboned chicken and sauteed bell pepper and onion.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: In skillet:
Cook onions and broccoli about 10 minutes in oleo. In large bowl put broccoli mixture, Minute rice (made as directed on box), cream of mushroom soup and Cheez Whiz; mix together.
Put in 2-quart casserole dish and top with buttered bread crumbs.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine green beans and soup in small casserole dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and top with the onions.
Bake for an additional 10 minutes and serve.

title: hickory smoked pulled pork
directions: Prepare gas grill, turn half of grill on high, leaving the other half off.
Add water soaked hickory chips to side that is turned on.
Place roast on side that is off.
Grill, covered, until fork slips easily into meat.
Cook slowly so meat does not burn on outside.
When meat is cool enough to handle, shred meat and place in bowl.
Meanwhile, stir together vinegar, water, hot sauce, mustard and salt in small bowl.
Add sauce to meat when ready to eat on buns.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Pour into two greased and floured 9x13 inch pans and bake at 350 degrees for 20-25 minutes. Makes 4 to 5 dozen bars.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Combine 1/2 cup confectioners sugar, condensed milk and peanut butter in a bowl.
Mix well. Shape into small balls.
Roll in 1/2 cup confectioners sugar, coating well. Store in airtight container.
Yields 32 servings.

title: bacon sausage roll-ups
directions: Cut bacon into thirds.
If you don't have small sausages, cut large sausages into 2 inch pieces.
Wrap bacon around each sausage;
secure with a toothpick.
Fill 13x9x2 inch pan with roll-ups.
Sprinkle brown sugar over links.
Cover & refrigerate 8 hours.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: wild blackberry pie
directions: In a large bowl, combine the first four ingredients, mixing well.
Turn into prepared 9-inch pie pan.
Dot with butter. Adjust top crust and flute edges.
Make slit in the middle to let steam escape.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes, or until nicely browned.

title: crockpot chicken casserole
directions: Lightly grease crockpot or spray with cooking spray.
Place chicken breasts in pot.
Top with cheese.
Combine soup and milk (make sure stirring well).
Spoon over cheese; sprinkle with stuffing mix.
Drizzle melted butter over stuffing mix.
Cook on low 8-10 hours or on high 4-6 hours.
Serves 6.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Salt and pepper chops.
Coat them with mustard and flour. Place in a small casserole dish.
Mix chicken soup, 1 bag of precooked instant rice and water.
Pour this mixture over the chops.
Cover and cook for 1 hour at 350°.

title: steamed pudding
directions: Beat egg and sugar.
Dissolve soda in sour cream.
Add to sugar and egg.
Add salt, fruit and flour.
Put in double boiler or over a pan of water and steam 1 hour.
Serve with sugar and milk.
(Old recipe.)

title: apple cake
directions: Beat oil, sugar and 1 egg at a time.
Add flour and orange juice.
Beat well.
Mix and let stand. Put batter and apples in layers ending with batter.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream the margarine.
Add sugar and cream well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat 1 minute.
Add vanilla wafers, crushed with rolling pin and add milk.
Add coconut and nuts.
Bake in a 300° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Use a greased and floured tube pan.

title: easy potato soup
directions: Saut onion in butter until tender. Add potatoes and cook over low heat until tender. Add milk and cream of celery soup; simmer until heated through. Add 1 cup of cheese. Bring to boil and cook until cheese is melted. Season with salt and pepper. Serve with a sprinkling of Cheddar cheese and bacon bits on top. Serves 8.

title: cranberry jello mold
directions: Add jello to 1 cup boiling water.
Boil about 15 seconds. Remove from heat and add cranberries, nuts and celery.
Mix well. Fold in sour cream.
Pour into jello mold pan that has been greased well with Miracle Whip salad dressing.
Chill 12 hours or overnight before unmolding.

title: beet salad
directions: Drain beets, reserving liquid. Add water to reserved liquid to equal 2 cups. Place in a saucepan and bring to boil. Remove from heat. Stir in gelatin until dissolved. Add cold water, onion, horseradish, vinegar and salt. Chill until partially set. Stir in beets, celery and olives. Pour into an 8-inch square dish. Chill until firm, about 3 hours. Cut salad into squares. Can serve on lettuce-lined plate and top with dollop of mayo and an olive. Makes 9 to 12 servings.

title: candy coated nuts
directions: Butter sides of 1 qt. saucepan. In it mix brown sugar, sugar and sour cream. Stir until sugars melt. Cook till softball stage (236°).

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake mix as directed (2 layers). Crumble 1 layer in bottom of punch bowl. Mix 1 package instant pudding with 2 1/2 cups milk. Let chill for a few minutes, then spread over crumbled cake. Spread 1/2 can crushed pineapple on top of pudding. Spread 1 can of pie filling on top of pineapple. Spread 1 container of Cool Whip on top of pie filling. Sprinkle with nuts. Then crumble second layer of cake on top and repeat steps again.

title: red satin punch
directions: Refrigerate fruit juice and 7-Up.
At serving time, combine cranberry juice and apple juice in punch bowl.
Slowly pour in 7-Up.
Add ice cubes.
Makes 35 punch cup servings. Contains 88 calories per serving.

title: juicy rib steaks
directions: Rinse steaks; pat dry.
Rub 1 teaspoon cornstarch on each steak.
Rinse and slice leek.
In skillet, heat butter.
Add leek. Reduce heat, saute leek until soft.
Remove from pan and set aside. Add steaks to hot pan.
Cook steaks until steaks are done to your liking.
Remove from pan.
Add beef broth and vinegar to skillet. Stir to scrape up brownings.
Add thyme or rosemary.
Cook until juices are smooth and shiny.
Add steaks and leeks back to juices. Heat quickly and serve.
Good served with broiled tomato halves and corn on cob.

title: pizza fries
directions: Bake French fries as directed on bag.
Heat sauce on stove top.
Pour sauce over fries.
Add toppings of your choice and enjoy.

title: rice pudding
directions: In the top half of a double boiler mix all the above ingredients, in the bottom half fill with water until it just touches the bottom of the top pan.
Boil the water slowly and keep checking the water to make sure it doesn't completely boil out. Keep mixing the pudding occasionally.
Cook at least for an hour, maybe more.
When the rice is no longer hard or crunchy, it is done.
Remove from the heat and let cool before refrigerating. Sprinkle with cinnamon and ENJOY.

title: green olive and anchovy puree
directions: In food processor, chop parsley.
Add olives, anchovies with their oil, bread crumbs, tomato paste, capers, lemon zest and pepper.
Process until minced.
Add cream cheese and process until smooth.
Transfer to serving bowl.
Excellent with crisp vegetable dippers or as a filling for cherry tomatoes or endive spears.

title: skillet sweet potatoes
directions: Bring 1 inch of water to a boil in skillet.
Add sweet potatoes; reduce heat, cover and simmer for 20 minutes or until tender.
Drain.
In a small bowl combine orange peel, orange juice, molasses or brown sugar, salt, cinnamon and allspice and pour over potatoes.
Cook and stir gently until bubbly.
Simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes or until potatoes are glazed, spooning sauce over potatoes occasionally.
Makes 4 servings.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Place ingredients in order given in a large bowl and combine. Mix well. Transfer to greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 60 minutes until top is golden brown and splits slightly. Remove to rack. Do not double.

title: recipe for friendship
directions: Cream together friendship and thoughtfulness with a pinch of powdered tenderness and very lightly beaten in a bowl of loyalty. Add faith, hope and charity.

Be sure to add a spoonful of gaiety that sings and also the ability to laugh at little things. Moisten with the sudden tears of heartfelt sympathy and bake in a good mannered pan and serve repeatedly.

title: baked chicken breast florentine
directions: Place chicken breasts in baking dish.
Put thawed and drained spinach on top of chicken.
Put the cup of sour cream on top.

title: cranberry-apple casserole
directions: Mix apples, white sugar and cranberry sauce.
Pour into a greased casserole dish.
Mix together rest of ingredients, and sprinkle evenly over apple mixture in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: light puffy rolls
directions: Sprinkle yeast in water.
Add sugar, oil, salt and egg; blend well.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Add 2 cups flour; beat with mixer or wooden spoon until smooth.
Gradually add flour; knead about 8 minutes.
Let rise.
Make into rolls or bread; let rise, then bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: cheese delights
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in large bowl.
Stir in milk, egg, shortening and 1 1/4 cups of the flour.
Beat until smooth.
Mix enough of remaining flour to make dough easy to handle.
Turn dough onto lightly floured surface.
Knead until smooth.
Place in greased bowl.
Let rise in warm place until doubled in size.
Beat cream cheese, brown sugar, egg yolk and lemon peel until light and fluffy.
Stir in raisins and set aside.
Punch down dough.
Roll dough into rectangle 18 x 12-inch.
Cut into 24 (3-inch) squares. Place 1 tablespoon cheese mixture on each square.
Bring 2 opposite corners together.
Moisten.
Pinch to seal.
Place on greased pan. Let rise until doubled.
Bake about 15 minutes at 375°.

title: fluff frosting
directions: Boil sugar, tartar, salt and water.
Slowly add egg white and vanilla.
Beat, cool and spread.

title: peanut butter cookies (diabetic)
directions: Mix and stir all ingredients in order:
flour, baking powder, soda, salt, shortening, peanut butter, Sweet 'N Low and egg.
Drop by large teaspoons on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: cheddar cheese biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Combine ingredients and mix with wooden spoon until soft dough forms.
Beat vigorously for 30 seconds. Drop by heaping tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: corn chowder
directions: Saute bacon and onion.
Add 1 cup boiling water to sauteed mixture.
Add potatoes, carrots and celery and cook until tender. Then add milk, cream-style corn, salt and pepper.
Heat through.

title: potatoes lyonnaise
directions: Make a batch of creamy mashed potatoes; season them well with salt, pepper and butter.
Pile them in a great fluffy heap on a round platter.
Around the outer edge, make a wreath of crispy fried Danish bacon and fill the center with Frisih Stegt Log (recipe follows).
Have this very hot (you can slip it into the oven for a few minutes after it's arranged.)
Garnish platter with slices of cold pickled beets before serving.

title: sweet potato custard
directions: In a medium bowl, stir together sweet potatoes and banana. Add milk, blending well.
Add brown sugar, egg yolks and salt, mixing thoroughly.
Spray a 1-quart casserole with nonstick spray coating.
Transfer sweet potato mixture to casserole.
Combine raisins, sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over top of sweet potato mixture.
Bake in preheated 300° oven for 45 to 50 minutes or until a knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Makes 6 servings, calories 144 and total fat 2 g.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Bring to a boil margarine, water and cocoa.
Put in a large bowl; let stand 5 minutes.
Add sugar, flour, baking soda, eggs and sour cream.
Pour into ungreased jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: cream cheese brownies supreme
directions: Melt the chocolate and butter; blend in the sugar, 4 of the eggs and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Stir in the flour, baking powder and salt.
In a mixer, beat the cream cheese, remaining 2 eggs and 1 teaspoon vanilla until light and fluffy.

title: chilled fresh peach soup
directions: Puree peaches with sugar in food processor. Blend in yogurt, orange juice and lemon juice. Pour into a bowl; cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: fudge squares
directions: Cream cocoa with sugar, salt and shortening.
Add unbeaten egg, vanilla, flour, baking powder and milk.
Add chopped nuts, if desired.
Bake at 350°.

title: taco twist
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Stir in seasoning mix, tomato sauce and green pepper.
Bring to boil and remove from heat.
Combine cooked macaroni, 1/2 cup cheese and sour cream; place on bottom of 6 x 10-inch baking dish.
Top with meat mixture and remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: zucchini jam
directions: Cook zucchini and 1 cup water over medium heat until boiling. Reduce heat and cook 6 minutes.
Add sugar, juice, flavoring and pineapple.
Bring to a boil and cook 6 minutes.
Add dry Jell-O and mix well.
Pour into hot jelly jars and seal.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onions.
Drain.
Mix soup, sauce, milk, Doritos and chilies together.
Sprinkle cheese on top or mix with other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes in 2 qt. casserole dish.

title: elvira's fried pea patties
directions: Pour peas in medium bowl, mash well with a potato masher.
Add egg, spices, flour and onions; mix well. Pour oil into skillet and cook on medium-high heat.
Drop mixture by heaping tablespoonfuls into hot oil.
Brown on both sides.
Drain on paper towel. Yields 12 large patties, each serving contains 99 calories.

title: brown sugar frosting
directions: Melt oleo and add brown sugar.
Bring to a boil.
Add milk. Take off stove and add powdered sugar.
Mix well and frost.

title: fruit compote
directions: Drain and cut peaches. Mix all
fruit and stir in beverage crystals and vanilla instant pudding mix.
Stir until coated. Serves 10 to 12.

title: peter rabbit salad
directions: Wash and dry lettuce leaves.
Put on plates.
Place a pear, rounded side up, on each plate.
Use marshmallow quarters for ears; half for tail.
Nose is cherry bit; eyes are cloves.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Beat sugar and butter; mix well, then add eggs and bananas, then add flour, vanilla and pecans.
Cook at 350° for about 45 minutes in 2 small bread pans.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Mix dry ingredients together. Dip chicken in egg and milk wash and then in dry mixture. Place in baking dish and drizzle melted butter over the top. Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: sherried london broil
directions: Score the steak and place it in a shallow dish.
Make the marinade out of the rest of the ingredients.
Marinate for 6 hours or overnight, turning occasionally.
Remove from marinade.
Place on grill.
Cook and brush occasionally with sauce.
Total cooking time is about 30 minutes for rare.
When done, slice thinly across grain.

title: settlers beans
directions: In skillet, brown bacon, ground beef and onion.
Drain fat. Mix all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook on high couple hours (until boils).
Cook a couple more hours on low or simmer 6 to 8 hours.

title: chopped apple spice cake
directions: Combine oil, eggs and sugar; beat well.
Set aside.
Combine flour, baking soda, nutmeg, cinnamon, allspice, salt and baking powder.
Sift again.
Add dry ingredients to oil-egg-sugar mixture, beating well after each addition.
Mixture will seem very stiff. Add vanilla extract.
Fold in apples and pecans.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream topping.

title: burgundy beef strips
directions: Cut beef into 3/4-inch strips.
Pat dry.
Cook bacon in large skillet until crisp.
Transfer bacon to 2-quart baking dish with cover.
Add onions to bacon drippings in skillet.
Reduce heat to medium.
Cook until browned.
Add to bacon.
Brown meat in drippings, a few pieces at a time.
Transfer to bacon dish.
Add salt, pepper, wine, garlic, mushrooms, 3/4 cup water, parsley, celery, carrots and thyme to dish.
Cover.
Bake at 300° until meat is tender, about 2 hours.
Remove beef, mushrooms and onions from dish.
Strain liquid into saucepan.
Thicken with remaining flour and water.
Pour mixture over meat and vegetables.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Place sliced peaches in baking dish.
Take bread and cut in 1/2-inch strips and place on top of peaches.
Mix sugar, eggs, melted oleo and vanilla; spread over each bread strip.
Bake in 350° oven until brown.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except potato chips.
Top with chips. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix together.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown meat, onion and green chilies.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 1 hour.
Crush Doritos and put into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour mixture over Doritos.
Top with cheese. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes (until cheese melts).
Garnish with lettuce, tomato and onion.
Serves 6.

title: potato casserole
directions: Spread potatoes on bottom of greased pan.
Next sprinkle onions.
Mix rest of ingredients and place on top of potatoes. Shortly before baking, make topping of 2 cups crushed cornflakes. Sprinkle on top and drizzle with 1/4 cup melted butter.
Cook at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes in an 11 x 13-inch greased pan.
Better if prepared ahead of time.

title: raspberry jam
directions: Boil tomatoes and sugar for 20 minutes.
Add jello and Sure- Jell.
Cook a few minutes more.
Put into jars and seal.
You can use blackberry or strawberry jello.

title: orange cranberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Put paper liners in 12 muffin cups. Place dry ingredients in large bowl and stir to mix. In medium bowl, combine melted butter, eggs, buttermilk and flavorings. Add to dry mixture and fold in. Do not overbeat! Fold in oranges and cranberries. Drop batter into muffin cups. Sprinkle sugar on tops for a little crust. Bake 20 to 25 minutes. Cool in pans for 10 minutes then place on wire racks to cool.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Note: If you use a cast-iron skillet to prepare this meal, it makes it easier to melt your cheese right before you serve it.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Stir first 5 ingredients together.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Mix with all dry ingredients.
Pour into a greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Cool in pan, then on a rack.
Delicious served with whipped Philadelphia cream cheese and a few shakes of cinnamon.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown hamburg.
Remove excess grease.
Add onion and garlic to browned beef and cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Add remaining sauce ingredients and bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer for 5 to 6 hours, stirring occasionally.
Serve with cooked pasta as desired.

title: taco filling
directions: In skillet, brown beef and onion; drain excess fat.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 10 minutes, uncovered, stirring occasionally.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.
Freezes well.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into 4 pieces.
Pour sugar and cinnamon in a medium plastic bag.
Grease and flour pan.
Put 1/2 of the cut biscuits in the bag of sugar and cinnamon.
Shake until biscuits are covered.
Place 1/2 the biscuits in the pan and sprinkle half of the pecans over the biscuits.
Put the rest of the biscuits on top of the pecans.
Bring to a boil the butter and brown sugar. Pour over and place the rest of the pecans on top.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: In medium bowl, beat butter with mixer until creamy.
Add sugar; beat until pale and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Beat in vanilla, baking powder and salt.
If using fresh blueberries, mash 1/2 cup and stir into the batter.
Fold 1/2 the flour, then 1/2 the milk into the batter. Repeat with remaining flour and milk.
Fold in remaining fresh blueberries or all the frozen.
Spoon batter into the muffin cups. Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes, until golden brown.
Makes 18 to 20 muffins.

title: hors d'oeuvre crackers
directions: Boil milk, raisins and nuts until thick, about 5 to 6 minutes. Spread on Ritz crackers.
Bake at 325° for 7 to 8 minutes.
When cool, spread Cream Cheese Frosting on top.

title: corn dogs
directions: Mix all ingredients except hot dogs. Coat wieners and drop in hot oil. Cook until brown.

title: ham baked in milk
directions: Mix milk and flour, add sugar.
Add enough more milk to make 3/4 cup liquid.
Pour about 1/3 of the liquid mixture over the ham every 15 minutes, while baking, until used up.
Then turn the ham every 15 minutes until done.
Start baking at 400°, then reduce to 350° after 15 minutes.
Probably will be done in 1 hour, but depends on thickness of ham.

title: fruit slush
directions: Roll pastry thin.
Allow to dry while doing the rest.
Squeeze pulp from 2 cups scuppernong or muscadine grapes.
Place hulls and pulp in separate boilers half covered with water.
Cook hulls for 45 minutes.
Lift hulls from water with slotted spoon.
Cool some. Spread cooled hulls on pastry; roll up like a jelly roll and pinch seams and ends to keep hull inside.
Place in a medium Pyrex bowl. Bring pulp to a boil, then strain and seed.
Place strained pulp back in boiler; add 1 1/2 cups sugar, a large hunk of butter and some water from hulls to make approximately 3 cups of liquid.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Pour boiling liquid over roll to half cover it. Place in 400° oven for 10 minutes; lower heat to 350° and cook until roll is browned on top.
Serve sliced roll hot with liquid poured over.

title: microwave classic meatloaf(easy and so delicious)
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place in a microwave ring pan.
Cook on High power for 10 minutes or until done.
