For the sauce, blend ingredients well, pour over meat loaf, heat for another 3 minutes.

title: hot butter dips
directions: Melt butter in a pan in oven.
Mix ingredients. Roll out on floured wax paper. Cut in strips with a knife.
Cut into size strips desired per roll. Dip in melted butter and lay side by side in pan. Bake at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chewy peanut butter bars
directions: Cream together shortening, peanut butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla and eggs; beat well.
Mix in flour, baking powder and salt, stirring only until blended.
Stir in coconut.
Spread evenly in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake about 25 minutes or until golden brown at 350°.
Cut into bars.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Brown hamburger meat and drain well.
If using whole tomatoes, cut into small pieces.
Put all ingredients into large pot.
Add salt and pepper to taste along with seasoning meat.
Cook approximately 30 to 45 minutes on low to medium heat.
One can add or delete any amount or vegetable to your preference.
Double for larger servings.

title: saints delight(can be low-fat.)
directions: Place angel food cake pieces in the bottom of a large bowl. Mix pudding according to package directions. Pour over pieces of cake. Pour pie filling on top of the pudding. Spread Cool Whip over the pie filling and chill and serve.

title: salmon mousse
directions: In blender, blend onion, water, gelatin and lemon juice. Remove bones from salmon and blend into onion mix.
Add half and half, mayonnaise and dill.
Place in a greased mold and refrigerate.
Unmold.
Serve with a mixture of 1/2 sour cream, 1/3 mayonnaise and chopped fresh dill.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix the ingredients in a greased casserole dish.
When mixing fried onions, use only 1/2 the can; use the rest to sprinkle on top.
Bake about 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: light and cheesy broccoli casserole
directions: Grease lightly a square 8 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Spread broccoli in dish.
Beat sour cream, cottage cheese, Bisquick, margarine and eggs with hand beater 1 minute.
Pour over broccoli; arrange tomato slices on top.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake until golden brown and knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean, about 30 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
(I have made this with fat-free dairy products to make this even a lighter dish.) Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Add ingredients in order given; mix well.
Grease and flour loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: no bake cookies
directions: In a sauce pan, combine sugar, milk, cocoa, butter.
Bring to a boil and boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, oats, and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Heat corn and milk; gradually add egg and seasonings. Add 1 1/4 cups cracker crumbs. Mix well and pour in greased casserole dish. Sprinkle remaining crumbs and melted butter over top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rolls with sweet taste
directions: Mix all ingredients and let stand about 1 hour.
(Be sure to mix yeast in lukewarm water before putting in flour and cake mix.) Punch down and make into rolls.
Let rise (about another hour). Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes 40 rolls.

title: hardee's biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in water.
Mix oil and buttermilk. Add to yeast water.
Sift soda with flour and add to oil and add to buttermilk.
Mix well and refrigerate.
Use as much as needed. Roll and cut out.
Cook at 450° until brown.

title: meatball stew
directions: Form the ground chuck into small balls (about 25).
Melt the butter in a large, deep skillet or in a soup pot.
Add meat balls and cook, stirring often, until lightly browned.
In a medium bowl, combine mushroom soup, onion soup mix, and water.
Mix well and add to meatballs.
Shake pan gently to coat meat balls.
Add homestyle vegetables and tomatoes.
Cook over medium-low heat for about 15 to 20 minutes, adding more water, if needed.

title: easy custard pudding
directions: Beat all ingredients together.
In a baking dish, break up bread and add raisins.
Pour the liquid mix over and bake in 325° oven for 30 to 45 minutes or until a knife comes out clean from the middle.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Drop 4 ounces macaroni into 3 cups rapidly boiling salted water (2 teaspoons salt). Bring back to rapid boil. Cook, stirring constantly, for 3 minutes and let stand 10 minutes. Rinse with hot water; drain.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Beat eggs and add other ingredients.
Mix well and pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan or two 8-inch square pans.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
This freezes well.

title: baked ham
directions: Wash ham well.
Place in large roasting pan.
Slice into skin of ham 1 inch apart, turning ham once.
Salt and pepper well.
Pat on 1 cup brown sugar and spices.
With toothpicks, put cherries and pineapple decoratively.
Add more crushed cloves to top. Partially cover ham 1/2 time.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 30 to 35 minutes per pound.
Slice and serve.

title: ami's tater tot casserole
directions: Press ground beef into a square baking pan.
Arrange frozen Tater Tots over meat.
Spread undiluted soup over Tater Tots. Bake, uncovered, at 350° until casserole is hot and bubbly, about 30 minutes.
tags: cream of chicken and mushroom soup

title: taco pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Brown ground beef in a skillet; drain and set aside.
Saute onion until brown.
Combine ground beef, onion, taco seasoning and salt and place in a casserole dish.
Top with green chilies.
Beat milk, eggs and Bisquick together for 15 seconds at high speed with an electric mixer or beat for 1 minute by hand.
Pour mixture over green chilies and bake for 20 minutes; remove from oven and top with tomatoes and cheese.
Bake for an additional 10 minutes; remove and let cool for 5 minutes.
Slice and serve with usual taco dressing:
sour cream, lettuce (shredded), cheese (shredded) and salsa.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: springerle cookies
directions: Using an electric mixer at low speed, beat eggs in a large bowl.
Gradually stir in sugar, then beat at medium speed for 10 minutes.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt; blend into egg mixture alternately with butter, mixing well.
Cover dough with waxed paper and chill 1 hour.
Dust work surface lightly with flour and pat out half of the dough at a time to 1/2 inch thickness.
Lightly dust springerle board or sprinkle rolling pin and press it firmly down on dough.
Lightly grease baking sheet and sprinkle evenly with anise seed.
Lift dough carefully to baking sheet and let stand overnight.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes, then reduce heat to 300° and continue baking for 10 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix graham crackers and melted margarine.
Press in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat butter, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Beat until firm.
Spread over graham crackers.
Peel and slice bananas, dip in drained pineapple juice and place on butter-egg mixture.
Put pineapple over bananas.
Top with Cool Whip, walnuts and maraschino cherries.
Refrigerate.
Dribble chocolate on top. Serves 15.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix together and simmer for 20 minutes or until onions are done and mixture is thick.

title: peanut butter tandy cake
directions: While cake is hot, spread peanut butter on top.
Put in refrigerator to cool.
Melt Hershey bar and spread on top of cake. Put back in refrigerator for icing to harden.

title: mini mincemeat nut cakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and mix well.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to butter mixture alternately with milk; blend.
Stir in mincemeat and nuts.
Bake in cupcake liners 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: red rice
directions: Brown
meat;
combine
all other ingredients. Mix well. Bake in covered casserole or baking dish at 350° for one hour.

title: fruity pizza
directions: Arrange cookie dough slices on foil lined 14-inch pizza pan. Press to seal edges.
Bake in 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes. Remove from foil to serving plate to cool.
Fold whipped topping into sour cream.
Spread over crust and arrange fruit in concentric circles beginning in center with kiwi and move out in order listed.
Chill and cut wedges to serve.

title: momma's baked beans
directions: Brown meat in pan and drain fat off.
Put meat, beans, and onion soup mix in a slow cooker or crock pot and let simmer until onions are tender; stirring occasionally.
You can add as much of any and all of the ingredients as you want to fit the crowd. Kidney beans also work well.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream oil and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vinegar (sift together flour, baking soda, salt and cocoa).
Add alternately with milk.
Add food color.
Divide among 4 (9-inch) layer cake pans.
Bake in 350° oven until brown and cake's spring from sides.

title: french beef stew
directions: Place all ingredients except for peas and wine into a heavy 4-quart casserole.
Do not brown meat.
Heat oven to 350°.
Cover pan and watch it until it starts to bubble.
Turn heat down to 250° and bake for 4 1/2 hours.
Lift cover and gently press in package of frozen peas.
Do not stir at all.
Return to oven and bake for 1/2 hour.
Just before serving, add wine.
Serves 8.

title: lemon garlic chicken
directions: Mix together and marinate; olive oil, lemon juice, chopped garlic, salt, pepper and oregano.
Blend well and set aside.

title: seven-up salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add cream cheese and beat. Add pineapple, sugar, vanilla, coloring and nuts.
Stir in 7-Up. Chill.
Just before salad sets, stir again to keep nuts from coming to top.

title: quick and easy punch
directions: Mix to the consistency you want.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: apricot cake
directions: Mix cake mix, sugar, oil and nectar. Add 1 egg at a time. Beat at least 5 minutes. Bake in tube pan 1 hour at 325°. Cool for 15 minutes. Remove from pan. Pour following glaze over cake:

title: carolina pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter and crisco for 10 minutes or until fluffy. Add eggs one at a time and beat well.
Add salt and baking powder to flour and vanilla and lemon to milk. Alternately fold in flour and milk mixtures.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: everyday cookies
directions: Just put all ingredients into a large bowl and mix until well blended.
Be sure margarine is soft (not melted).
(Do not use butter.)
Chill 1 hour, then form balls and flatten with a sugared glass (flat bottom) dipped in granulated sugar.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Watch closely.

title: summer pineapple pie
directions: Drain pineapple thoroughly.
Combine first 4 ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Fold in Cool Whip; divide mixture amongst the 2 pie shells and chill for 1/2 hour.
Serves 8.

title: mandarin dinner
directions: Sprinkle steak with meat tenderizer according to package directions.
Thinly slice steak.
Heat oil in fry pan; add steak. Cool and stir only until steak has lost red color.
Add water, 1/4 cup soy sauce and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients; stir fry to crisp tender stage.
Skillet can be covered to cook at low heat. Serve meat, vegetables, and juices in bowl with rice.
Serve with soy sauce.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash with salt until tender.
Whip squash until smooth. Saute shallots, peppers, celery and mushrooms with stick of margarine.
Blend egg, milk and oatmeal.
Combine drained squash, vegetables and egg mixture.
Add pimento.
Pour into large buttered casserole and cover with bread crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: french onion and cream potatoes
directions: Peel and thinly slice potatoes.
Mix cream and French onion soup together.
Layer sliced potatoes in a casserole dish.
Pour cream and soup mixture over top.
Cook slowly in a preheated oven 350 degrees for 40 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Blend and pour into graham cracker pie shells.
Makes 2 pies. Pour strawberries on top.

title: sand tarts
directions: Cream margarine.
Sift together flour, 1/4 cup powdered sugar and baking powder.
Gradually add to margarine, mixing well.
Stir in nuts and vanilla.
Form crescents with fingers and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes until done, but not brown.
Roll in additional sifted powdered sugar while cookies are still warm.
Handle with care as they are quite flaky at this point.
Allow to cool before serving.
Yield: 4 to 5 dozen.

title: debby's chili
directions: Cook hamburger and drain well.
Cook bacon and crumble.
Save grease and cook onion until lightly brown.
Boil water and add beef cubes.
Put all ingredients in slow cooker, except beans. Heat to a boil and turn to simmer and cook 4 to 5 hours or longer. Add beans halfway through cooking.
Can add more chili powder or red pepper for hotter chili.

title: heavenly fruit salad
directions: Mix sour cream and jello. Add Cool Whip, marshmallows, nuts and fruit cocktail. Chill and serve.

title: mrs. margaret's 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Sift flour with salt and baking powder.
Add alternately with milk.
Add vanilla.
Bake in four greased and floured 9-inch cake pans or one greased and floured tube pan at 350°.
Pans will take about 25 to 30 minutes, tube pan will take longer.
Frost with favorite frosting or serve with fruit and Cool Whip.

title: sunday best bran muffins
directions: Spray muffin cups with cooking spray.
In bowl, combine flour, baking powder
and salt.
In a large bowl, combine bran cereal, milk and
brown sugar.
Let stand for 2 minutes.
Stir in mayonnaise and
egg until well blended.
Add raisins.
Stir in flour mixture
just until moistened.
Fill muffin cups half full. Bake at
for	25
minutes.
Serve warm.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: tahereh's shortcake biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. Stir baking powder and salt into sifted flour.
Cut in shortening until mixture is the consistency of coarse meal.

title: milk chocolate fudge
directions: Cook sugar, milk and butter to soft ball stage (8 minutes). Remove from heat and add the rest.
Whip and put in large buttered pan.

title: banana or pumpkin bread
directions: Combine sugar, oil and eggs.
Add bananas or pumpkin.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add to bananas or pumpkin mixture.
Add water. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Use a greased and floured loaf pan.

title: carrots in cream and dill
directions: Saute carrots, onions and garlic in oil for 5 minutes. Sprinkle with flour.
Stir in soup and milk.
Add dill and sugar. Simmer until carrots are tender, approximately 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cheesy jalapeno dip
directions: Melt and mix all ingredients in double boiler.
Serve with nacho chips or Doritos!

title: ho-ho cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed.
Use sheet cake pan.
Mix milk, shortening, sugar, butter, vanilla and salt for 10 minutes or until creamy.
Spread on cooled cake and chill.
Warm frosting and spread on top of chilled filling and cake.
Refrigerate.

title: melissa's chicken
directions: Cut chicken into strips, set aside.
Heat skillet and spray generously with Pam.
Add garlic and stir; add chicken and spray chicken with Pam.
Season with lemon pepper and cook completely. About 25 minutes.
Add white wine Worcestershire sauce and cook about 5 minutes longer; arrange on platter and serve.

title: sausage balls
directions: Grate cheese; knead together with sausage and Bisquick.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Pinch off and roll into balls.
Bake for 10 minutes at 450°.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix the first 8 ingredients together in a 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Cook on Medium-high or 80% power 8 to 10 minutes, stirring once after 5 minutes.
Remove from microwave.
Melt butter in a separate microwave-safe dish for 40 seconds on High. Mix crackers and almonds with butter.
Sprinkle on top of casserole; cook on High 3 to 5 minutes, or until bubbly.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Serves 16.

title: peach rice salad
directions: In bowl, in water, stir ascorbic-acid mixture for fruit until dissolved.
Add peaches to mixture.
Gently toss peaches until thoroughly coated.
Let mixture stand 10 minutes.

title: sunday pork chops
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, spray with Pam. Put in pork chops.
Cut up onion and bell pepper. Put on top of chops.
Put mushrooms on top.

title: waldorf chicken sandwich
directions: Chop apple and celery fine.
Mix with other ingredients. Cover and refrigerate for 1 hour.
Serve on bread.
Makes 3 servings.

title: fruit squares
directions: Cream eggs, butter and sugar.
Add vanilla and flour.
Add fruit and nuts; mix by hand.
Press into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool about 30 minutes; cut into squares.

title: baked orange roughy
directions: Place a little olive oil in bottom of baking dish, enough to coat bottom.
Place fish fillets in dish with oil.
Sprinkle all seasonings over fish.
Pour melted butter on fish.
Squeeze lemon juice over fillets.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until fillets flake easily with a fork.

title: nannie alice's rice casserole
directions: Saute onions in butter, but do not brown.
Prepare rice as usual.
Add milk, soup and pepper to onions.
Stir and pour over rice.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° covered.
Take the cover off for the last few minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: dream bars
directions: Work to a paste and spread in pan about 9 x 12-inches.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: crisco maple frosting
directions: Mix powdered sugar and salt.
Blend in syrup.
Add shortening, vanilla and milk.
Mix until smooth and creamy.
Add more sugar to thicken or milk to thin frosting.
Frost two 8 or 9 inch layers or 13 x 9 inch cake.
Excellent on spice cake.

title: vinegar cake(fast and easy)
directions: Sift together flour, cocoa, soda, sugar and salt into 9 x 9 x 2-inch greased pan.
Make three holes in this sifted mixture. Pour cooking oil into one; vinegar into another and vanilla into the third hole.
Pour cold water over it all and beat until you can no longer see the flour.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: parmesan chicken and broccoli
directions: Cook rice; stir in half the onion.
Rinse chicken; pat dry and in a skillet cook chicken, garlic, and Italian seasoning in hot oil over medium heat for 8 to 10 minutes, turning once.
Remove from skillet; reserve drippings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Grate
the
cheese
and
combine
with
softened
cream cheese,
preferably
in electric mixer.
If too stiff to blend well,
add
a
little
cream
or
milk.
Add
grated onion and Worcestershire and a little finely minced garlic; mix well and allow
to stand in refrigerator for several hours.
Shape into balls
(this recipe will make 2 large balls or 3 medium balls) and roll in chopped pecans.
Chill again and serve with crisp crackers.

title: classic latkes(6 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. Brush 2 baking sheets, preferably nonstick, each with 1 teaspoon oil. With your hands, squeeze the liquid from the potatoes, a few handfuls at a time, into a large bowl. Let the liquid stand 1 minute to allow the potato starch to settle to the bottom and then pour off and discard the liquid that rises to the top. Beat in the egg, flour, salt and pepper and then stir in the potatoes and onion. Take about 3 tablespoons of the mixture in the palm of your hand and flatten to a 3-inch pancake; place on a prepared baking sheet. Repeat with the remaining potato mixture to make 12 latkes. Bake until lightly browned on the bottom, about 12 to 15 minutes. Brush the tops with the remaining 3 teaspoons oil and then turn and bake until cooked through, 5 to 7 minutes.

title: gizzard cajun squirrel
directions: Cut each squirrel into eight pieces, including heads.
Combine peppers and sea salt together.
Season both sides of cut up squirrel with mixture.
Melt butter in 12-inch cast-iron skillet and fry squirrel until browned all over and they start to stick to the pot.
Remove the squirrel; add 1 cup onion and crushed garlic. When vegetables are soft add 1/2 cup water, 1 tablespoon Worcestershire sauce and squirrel.
Cover; let simmer until tender, about 1 hour or 2.
Add flour and green onion tops; cook 5 minutes, stirring until slightly thickened.
Serve with rice.

title: bacon-tomato angel hair
directions: In a large skillet, cook bacon until crisp. Drain, reserving 1/4 cup drippings; return to skillet. Add bacon, green onion and garlic; cook 1 minute. Stir in tomatoes, basil, salt and pepper. Simmer 5 minutes. Prepare pasta according to package directions; drain. Add tomato mixture; toss to mix. Serve immediately.

title: chicken cheese ball
directions: Combine chicken, salad dressing mix and cream cheese in a mixing bowl.
Beat on medium speed until blended.
Shape into a ball and roll in pecans.
Cover and chill.
Yields 1 (4-inch ball).

title: cream cheese cake with pineapple
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan mix butter and graham crackers to make crust.
Layer pineapple on crust.
Mix Cool Whip and cream cheese. Put on top of pineapple.
Chill.

title: cheese spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together, let refrigerate overnight at least 2 hours before serving.
Serve with crackers.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Boil broccoli.
Melt Velveeta cheese.
Pour mushroom soup in melted cheese. Pour cheese and soup over broccoli.
Crush crackers and cover casserole.
Cook at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookie bars
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream butter and sugars.
Add eggs, vanilla and water; beat until smooth.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt; gradually add to creamed mixture and mix well.
Fold in chocolate chips and nuts.
Press into 4 lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pans.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 18 minutes or until golden brown.
Yields 8 dozen.

title: baked cornbread
directions: Mix together and bake in an iron skillet in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: christmas hard candy
directions: Boil first 3 ingredients until 300°.
Add color and flavor. Pour on cookie sheet trays of powdered sugar and cut into pieces. I broke mine.

title: fried okra and potatoes
directions: Peel and dice potatoes. Wash and cut up okra. Coat with cornmeal, salt and pepper. Heat oil in skillet; add okra and potatoes and cook until tender and brown.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and beat with electric beaters until batter becomes light and fluffy, about 3 minutes.
Grease and flour tube pan and bake 1 hour and 10 minutes at 350°.

title: irish soda bread(makes 2 round soda breads)
directions: You will need 2 round cake pans.

title: d. q. buster bar dessert
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to a boil and simmer for 10 minutes; cool.

title: cheddar cheese soup
directions: Saute the onion, carrot, celery and green pepper in the butter for 10 minutes.
Stir in the flour; cook for 1 minute.
Add the chicken broth.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Stir in the grated cheese; cook until cheese melts.
Add the milk.
Season to taste.

title: chicken quesadillas
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. In a nonstick skillet over medium high heat, cook chicken 5 minutes or until done and juices evaporate, stirring often. Add soup and salsa.

Heat through. Place tortillas on 2 baking sheets. Top half of each tortilla with about 1/3 c. soup mixture. Spread to within 1/2 inch of edge. Moisten edges of tortillas with water. Fold over and seal.
Bake 5 minutes or until hot. Serve with Fiesta rice. Serves 4.

title: drop cookies
directions: Cream brown sugar and white sugar with shortening.
Add egg or eggs, beaten.
Stir soda and baking powder into flour; add flour mixture alternately with sour milk.
Stir in vanilla.
Add floured raisins and nuts and blend.
Drop by tablespoons on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° until light brown or make indentation with finger.
Remove to racks to cool.

title: hot water cornbread
directions: Heat water in a small saucepan.
Put 3 cups of corn meal in large bowl and after water is very hot, pour in bowl.
Mix.
Take handfuls of mixture and form under stream of cold water.
Use a teaspoon for putting oil in skillet.
Fry until golden brown. Enjoy!

title: broccoli quiche
directions: Cook broccoli; drain.
Mix onion, lemon, nutmeg and pepper. Pour into pie shell.
Whip eggs and milk.
Pour over broccoli mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese, orange congealed salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot pineapple juice. Add evaporated milk and cool until thickened. Add the cheese, pineapple, mayonnaise, nuts and celery. Mix well and chill until firm. The cherries may be added if desired.

title: mexican roll-ups
directions: Mix last 6 ingredients.
Spread on tortillas.
Roll and chill 2 hours.
Cut into 1-inch slices.

title: beef nacho casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Brown meat; drain.
Stir in salsa, corn, Miracle Whip and chili powder.
Layer half each of meat mixture, chips and cheese in 2-quart casserole.
Repeat layers.
Bake 20 minutes until thoroughly heated.
Top with shredded lettuce and tomatoes, if desired.

title: kentucky salad
directions: Stir all ingredients (except marshmallows and cherries) together.
Stir in nuts. Top with mini marshmallows.
Top with maraschino cherries.

title: okra stew
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Add meat, salt and turmeric and brown over medium heat 10 minutes.
Cut off both ends of washed and dried okra and slice into 4 or 5 pieces.
Place meat and onion mixture, okra, potatoes, tomatoes and water in a pot.

Bring to a boil; reduce heat to medium-low, cover and simmer 30 to 40 minutes or until meat is tender (can be done quicker in pressure cooker; reduce water to 1 cup and cook 15 to 20 minutes or until meat is tender.)
Add lemon juice.
Simmer 5 minutes more.
Serve over rice.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cut peppers in halves and remove seeds.
Boil for 5 minutes. Put butter in skillet and add chopped onion and celery.
Let cook 4 or 5 minutes, then add meat and cook until meat changes color. Add cooked rice, tomatoes and tomato sauce.
Cook until thick or suitable to put in peppers.
Add the liquid from meat for the sauce on top.

title: orange delight
directions: Dissolve jello in hot orange juice, stir.
Add drained fruit cocktail and chill until partially set.
Stir in Cool Whip and chill until firm in serving dish.
Add strawberries as desired.

title: tavern biscuits
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add brandy and mace, then flour and milk, a spoonful at a time, to make a stiff dough.
Refrigerate until dough is firm enough to roll out easily.

Roll dough to an even thickness, about 1/4 inch, and cut out in small circles. Prick with a fork, and bake in a 350° oven until they are firm. They should brown on the bottom, but the tops should remain a pale yellow color.
Store in a covered jar.

title: quick broccoli chicken roll-ups
directions: Combine soup and milk; set aside.

Combine chicken, broccoli, 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 can of onions. Stir in 3/4 cup of soup mix. Divide chicken mixture evenly between tortillas and roll up. Stir tomato in soup mixture and pour over top of tortillas.
Bake covered at 350° for 35 minutes. Top center of tortillas with remaining cheese and onions. Bake uncovered 5 minutes longer.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook pie shells and cool.
Put sugar, water and cornstarch in a saucepan.
Cook together until it comes to a rolling boil.
Add strawberry jello and bring to a boil.
Place fresh strawberries in pie shells and pour sauce over them.
Chill for 3 hours and top with whipped cream or Cool
Whip.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients, except pecans.
Shape into balls. Roll in pecans.
Makes 2 medium size balls.
Wrap in foil and freeze.
Thaw 3 to 4 hours.

title: quick corn salad
directions: In a large salad bowl, combine vegetables; stir in dressing. Cover and refrigerate until serving.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: crescent roll cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease a 9 x 13-inch pan. Press one package of crescent rolls in the bottom of the pan.
Mix cream cheese, sugar, egg yolk and vanilla.
Spread on top of rolls in the pan.
Put the other package of crescent rolls on top. Brush with egg white and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake for 30 minutes or until lightly browned at 350°.

title: newfi bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add butter and molasses (butter will melt some).
Then add salt.
Add flour, one cup at a time.
Knead for 10 minutes.
Let rise in greased bowl until doubled.
Punch down.
Place in 3 well-greased pans and let rise again.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 375° or until done.
Test for doneness and remove from pans immediately.
Yields 3 (9 x 5-inch) loaves.

title: bavarian salad
directions: Boil the sugar, cider vinegar and salt together.
Mix all ingredients; let set overnight.

title: baccala chowder
directions: In a large soup pot, cook pancetta, slightly, on medium-low heat.
Add onion, carrots and celery, about 5 minutes.
Add potatoes, clam juice and water.
Cover and cook until potatoes are a little soft.
Add pepper, parsley, milk, half and half and baccala, stirring so milk mixes smooth with clam juice, etc. Simmer about another 20 minutes on medium heat.

title: rice pudding on a platter
directions: Cook rice, water and salt from directions on rice package. Let stand a while.
Heat milk.
Beat eggs and sugar; add to hot milk.
Bring to a boil.
Lower heat and cook, while stirring, for 3 minutes.
Cool for 10 minutes.
Add vanilla.
Pour into rice and stir.
Pour on large platter.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: wedding punch(yields 100 servings)
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and sugar in 4 cups boiling water.
Add 12 cups cold water and pineapple juice and freeze.
For 7:00 p.m. wedding, take out of freezer about 2:00 p.m.
Let thaw to slush stage; add ginger ale.

title: make ahead casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in casserole.
Let stand 3 to 4 hours in refrigerator.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Place rolls in bottom of a 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan and press seams together.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Mix next 3 ingredients and spread on cooled, baked crust.
Mix vegetables and place on cream cheese layer. Press down. Top with cheese.
Chill 1 hour.
Cut in squares or make in pizza pan and cut into slices.

title: italian creme cake
directions: Cream oleo and Crisco; add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add egg yolks and beat again.
Combine flour and soda.
Add alternately with buttermilk into mixture.
Stir in vanilla; add coconut and nuts and fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour into 3 well-greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: rouladen
directions: Pour beef flat to tenderize.
Pieces should be rectangular. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Spread beef with mustard on each slice.
Add onions and bacon.
Roll slices, starting at small end and fasten with toothpicks or wrap with thread.
Brown in a little oil, add water and simmer (covered) for about one hour or so. Make gravy from liquid.
This is a popular German dish.

title: mexicali corn dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Refrigerate and serve with tortilla chips.

title: delight salad
directions: Heat fruit cocktail.
Add jello and dissolve.
Chill until almost set.
Mix cream cheese with a little milk.
Beat whipping cream and add to cream cheese.
Mix with fruit and jello.

title: supper salad
directions: Blend and chill 4 hours before eating.

title: bacon-broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli into bite-sized pieces, discard stems.
Place in large bowl.
Cut bacon into 1-inch pieces.
Cook in skillet until crisp; remove and drain, reserving 2 tablespoons drippings.
Add bacon to broccoli and toss lightly.
Cook onion in reserved drippings until tender.
Stir in sugar, vinegar, water, salt and pepper.
Heat to boiling, reduce heat and cook slowly one minute. Pour over bacon and broccoli and toss well.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: green jello salad
directions: Mix jello and water until dissolved.
Put in refrigerator until cooled.
Mix together the remaining ingredients.
Add this to the jello and chill.

title: sour cream beans
directions: Melt butter, then stir in flour, salt, pepper, sugar and onion.
Add sour cream, stirring constantly.
Cook until thickened.
Fold in green beans.
Pour into casserole.
Mix cheese and Wheaties together in a cool bowl, then sprinkle over the top of beans.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: carnation famous fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk, butter and salt in medium heavy-duty saucepan.
Bring to a full rolling boil over medium heat, stirring constantly, for 4 to 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in marshmallows, morsels, nuts and vanilla.
Stir vigorously until marshmallows are melted.
Pour into foil-lined 8-inch square baking dish.
Chill for 2 hours or until firm.
Remove foil.
Cut into pieces.

title: mexicali meat loaf
directions: Combine above ingredients.
Mix well.
Shape into a shallow 2 quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes. Drain off juice.

title: divinity candy
directions: Cook sugar, Karo and water until mixture forms a hard ball in cold water.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Pour syrup over egg whites slowly, beating fast.
When mixture loses some of its gloss, drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.
Nuts or candied cherry halves can be added.

title: jello cake
directions: Cook cake according to directions.
When cool, poke holes with handle end of wooden spoon, add jello mixed with hot water.
Pour over top of cake.
Chill.
Spoon Cool Whip on top.
Serve.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender and drain; mash squash and add salt and pepper, bouillon cube, butter and onion.
Add egg, sour cream, and cheese.
Pour into casserole dish.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over mixture and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: never fail flaky pie crust
directions: Remove 1/3 cup flour from 2 cups flour and put in small bowl. Add enough water to make a runny paste.
Set aside.
Put Crisco into remaining flour (1 2/3 cups) and salt.
Blend thoroughly and add paste.
Mix with a knife until it collects into a ball.
Makes 1 double crust or 3 shells.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: Combine
ground beef, onion and water.
With hands, mix until all
the
meat is torn apart.
Cook over low heat until most
of the water has boiled away.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Let stand for a few minutes before serving.

title: turkey soup
directions: Bring turkey carcass to simmering (remove any skum).
Boil in water just to cover.
Simmer until meat on carcass comes off easily.
Remove turkey carcass and save broth in pot that the turkey simmered in.
Take meat off carcass and put in pot, along with the celery, carrots, chicken broth, salt and pepper to taste and onion.
If you like a "thicker" soup, you may add a cup of white rice, brown rice or wild rice.
Simmer all of this for about an hour.
This makes a lot of soup, which may be put in small containers and frozen.

title: chicken stuff
directions: Put half of stuffing in bottom of baking dish.
Put in melted margarine and cut up chicken.
Put in rest of stuffing and add broth.
Bake at 325° until bubbly.
May be made ahead and kept in refrigerator until ready to cook.

title: ranch potato salad
directions: Drain	potatoes.
Crumble
bacon
in
potatoes;
slice onions, add.
Salt	and pepper to taste.
Add chives to taste. Mix with Ranch dressing, original recipe.
(Mix dressing first and chill while potatoes cook.)

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Heat pineapple and juice to boiling point.
Then remove from heat and stir in dry Jell-O until dissolved, then let cool.
Stir in buttermilk and Cool Whip and mix well.
Pour into serving bowl and refrigerate until chilled.

title: chocolate chess brownie
directions: Mix egg and cream cheese.
Add powdered sugar gradually; mix well.
Pour over crust and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Soak oatmeal in buttermilk 1/2 hour.
Cream brown sugar, egg and oil.
Stir in oatmeal.
Add flour, mixed with salt, soda and baking powder.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 12.

title: baked bean casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients. Put bacon on top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cabbage refrigerator slaw
directions: Mix together vinegar, sugar, salt and black pepper.
Let this mixture come to a boil just enough to melt sugar.
Pour over vegetable mixture and toss.
Refrigerate.
Stays good for several days.

title: marinated tomatoes
directions: Mix dressing and water together.
Cut tomatoes in quarters. Pour just enough dressing/water mixture over tomatoes to coat them. *
Need to have enough mixture in bowl to toss with.
Chill for 30 minutes, then serve.

title: dressing over chicken casserole
directions: Mix chicken breasts, bread crumbs, eggs and milk. Put in a 9 x 12-inch greased pan. Combine water, margarine and stuffing. Spread over top of chicken mix. Bake at 350° for about 45 to 60 minutes or when brown on top.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and margarine.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Bake in unbaked shell for approximately 45 minutes at 350° to 370°.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix milk, lemon juice, fruit cocktail and nuts.
Pour into crust and top with Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: crabmeat casserole
directions: Saute garlic in butter; add pepper and onions.
Add flour, milk and parsley.
Add crabmeat and bread crumbs.
Season as you like.
Sprinkle cheese.
Put in buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: delicious pork chops
directions: Spread pork chops with prepared mustard, salt and pepper; roll into flour.
Brown.
Put in baking dish and add 1 can chicken gumbo soup and 1/2 can water.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix together all ingredients; bring to a boil until thickened. Beat 2 egg whites for meringue.

title: corn sticks
directions: Sift flour; measure and re-sift 2 times with next 4 ingredients, the last time into mixing bowl.
Beat egg well; stir in milk and melted shortening and pour all at once into center of dry ingredients.
Stir quickly until dry ingredients are just dampened, then give 3 or 4 more stirs.
Batter should not be smooth.
Spoon quickly into greased, hot corn stick pans or muffin pans, filling about 2/3 full.
Bake in a hot oven (425°) for about 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from pans immediately and serve at once.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: zucchini bars
directions: Mix the zucchini, sugar, eggs, nuts and cooking oil. Gradually add the dry ingredients and mix it well.
Bake it in a well-greased jelly roll pan at 300° until it is done.

title: tomato and salami antipasto
directions: Place salami in shallow container.
Combine oil, lemon juice, lemon rind, salt and pepper, garlic, parsley and basil.
Pour over salami and let stand 1 hour, turning once.
Cut tomatoes into thick slices.
Arrange overlapping slices of tomato and salami on a serving plate.
Pour the remaining dressing over the top.
Serve on slices of fresh bread.
Yum!

title: ham and potatoes au gratin
directions: In medium saucepan melt butter; add onions and green pepper. Cook until tender.
Stir in flour and pepper; add milk all at once and bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat; add shredded cheese and mayonnaise, stirring until cheese melts.
Add ham and potatoes to sauce; mix well.
Add salt to taste.
Pour mixture into shallow baking dish and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until heated through, bubbly and lightly brown.

title: lemon bread
directions: Blend the first 3 ingredients.
Mix in lemon juice and rind. Stir in dry ingredients along with milk.
Fold in nuts.
Divide between 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes or until done.
Turn out onto wire racks.
Mix topping sugar and lemon rind and juice.
Pour over hot bread.
Great for the holidays or any special time.
Can make ahead and freeze.

title: margaret's citrus raisin strata
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease a 2-quart baking dish. Tear bread into bite sized pieces and put in baking dish. Combine all other ingredients and pour over bread. Bake 45 minutes.

title: creamy crab and artichoke dip
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
In medium mixing bowl blend together the cream cheese and mayonnaise until smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients and place mixture in a glass pie plate. Bake, uncovered, for 15-18 minutes, until heated through and lightly browned.
Serve with crackers or French bread.
Serves 4-5.

title: christmas plum pudding
directions: Mix sugar, self-rising flour, soda, nutmeg, allspice and cinnamon; set aside.
Beat eggs.
Add plums (without seeds), oil, buttermilk and vanilla.
Mix with flour mixture until well blended.
Stir in pecans.
Bake in a lightly oiled 9 x 13-inch sheath pan in 375° oven for 45 minutes.

title: hamburger stuffed with blue cheese
directions: Gently mix all ingredients except the Blue cheese and shape into 8 thick patties.
Make a pocket in the center of each patty; fill with Blue cheese and cover the cheese with meat.
Broil, saute or grill for 5 minutes on each side for rare hamburgers.

title: christmas pecan candy cake
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Grease and flour 9 X 3-inch tube pan with removable bottom.
Combine cherries, pineapple, and dates in a very large bowl.
Sprinkle with flour; toss to coat well.
Add sweetened condensed milk; stir to mix well.
Spoon evenly into prepared pan, smoothing the top.
Bake in preheated, slow oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool in pan on rack.
Remove from pan and wrap tightly in foil.
Refrigerate at least 2 weeks.
Slice very thin; slices best when cold.

title: easy crisp sweet dill pickles
directions: Add sugar,
pickling
spice and vinegar to drained dill pickles.
Invert jar daily until all sugar is dissolved (about 3 days).
Green food coloring may be added for holidays.

title: magnolia pie(buttermilk pie)
directions: In large bowl, cream together sugar, butter and flour.
Add eggs, buttermilk and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake for 1 hour at 325°
or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool and serve.

title: corned beef brisket(microwave)
directions: Bring hot water to a boil.
Add brisket, cover and cook on High 35 to 40 minutes.
Turn brisket over twice during cooking time.
Remove from liquid; cover with plastic wrap and let stand 15 minutes.
Yields 8 to 10 slices.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix well peanut butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip and toasted nuts.
Pour into prepared cookie crumb or graham cracker crust.
Chill.

title: old fashioned raisin bars
directions: Combine raisins and water in pan; bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in oil; cool to lukewarm.
Stir in sugar and egg.
Sift together dry ingredients; beat into raisin mixture.
Stir in nuts. Pour into greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes (approximately).
When cool, cut into bars. Dust with confectioners sugar or frost while slightly warm.
Makes about 4 dozen bars.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Clean and peel shrimp.
Run shrimp under cold water and then place on paper towels to dry thoroughly. Pat dry.

title: unbelievable peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix the flour ingredients with a spoon until well mixed and waxy.
Roll into small balls and place onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Press lightly with fork.
Place 1 inch apart.
Cook for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: spice cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar and gradually add eggs and milk.
Mix all dry ingredients together and add to the liquid batter.
Roll dough into balls and place on ungreased pan about 2-inches apart. Bake for 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit salad(origin: unknown)
directions: Toss all fruit together.
Mix in dressing and whipped cream. Cool for several hours before serving on a bed of lettuce.

title: friendship cake
directions: Take gallon jar.
Add 1 1/2 cups starter, 2 1/2 peaches, juice and all.
Stir daily for 10 days.
On tenth day, add large can crushed pineapple with juice and 2 1/2 cups sugar.
Stir daily for 10 days.

title: pumpkin chiffon pie
directions: Combine in saucepan the brown sugar, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and ginger.
Add egg yolks with milk, then add gelatin. Cook and stir until mixture comes to a boil.
Remove from heat and stir in pumpkin. Chill until mixture mounds slightly when spooned.
Test often so it won't be too stiff. Beat egg whites until they peak. Gradually add 1/2 cup sugar.
Fold pumpkin mixture into egg white mixture. Turn into prebaked pie crust.

title: peanut butter squares
directions: Cream margarine and peanut butter.
Add sugar and finely crushed graham crackers.
Press ingredients in 9 x 12-inch pan. Melt butter and chocolate chips over low heat.
Spread over mixture in pan.
Cool 20 minutes.
Cut into squares.
Tastes like Reese's peanut butter cups.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients together well, roll into small meatballs and brown in skillet, drain and set aside.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Boil spinach in water with 1 tablespoon salt until comes to a good boil.
Drain well.
Mix all together and put in buttered casserole dish and top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 325° for about 25 minutes until bubbly.

title: cherry berry jam
directions: Combine prepared fruit and lemon juice in large pan.
Mix pectin with fruit and place over high heat.
Bring to full boil, stirring constantly.
At once, stir in sugar.
Bring to a full, rolling boil and boil hard one minute, stirring constantly.
Skim. Ladle into clean, hot jars, filling to within one-half inch of top. Seal.
Makes six half-pints.
